[Guest 1]: a show with them also, I remember.

01:27:55.560 --> 01:27:59.120
[Guest 1]: So with Kodak, this guy Richard Fleming used to be there.

01:27:59.120 --> 01:28:03.960
[Guest 1]: And he had turned and so he used to go on when we used to go and recce a venue, he used

01:28:03.960 --> 01:28:08.920
[Guest 1]: to first go and look at the bedroom, what is the bed of the room?

01:28:08.920 --> 01:28:11.600
[Guest 1]: Then he would go and say, what food will you serve them?

01:28:11.600 --> 01:28:13.840
[Guest 1]: Don't serve me a special meal.

01:28:13.840 --> 01:28:14.840
[Guest 1]: What's your regular meal?

01:28:14.840 --> 01:28:18.400
[Guest 1]: And if he could, he would try and go without actually telling them he's coming.

01:28:18.400 --> 01:28:21.920
[Guest 1]: But he said, these are the two things that matter when you're out of your house.

01:28:21.920 --> 01:28:24.760
[Guest 1]: Ultimately, in which bed do you sleep, what do you eat?

01:28:24.760 --> 01:28:29.160
[Guest 1]: He says, the event is for two hours, four hours, you can make a spectacle out of it.

01:28:29.160 --> 01:28:31.880
[Guest 1]: 20 dancing people will come, there will be lights, there will be sound, there will be

01:28:31.880 --> 01:28:32.880
[Guest 1]: motivational speaker.

01:28:32.880 --> 01:28:36.560
[Guest 1]: Ultimately, that guy will go to that bed to sleep.

01:28:36.560 --> 01:28:38.840
[Guest 1]: And that meal that he will eat.

01:28:38.840 --> 01:28:43.680
[Guest 1]: And I have seen that change relationships and like when Amit is there, Amit is with

01:28:43.680 --> 01:28:46.960
[Guest 1]: the people till 4am because he's with them.

01:28:46.960 --> 01:28:50.760
[Guest 1]: Drinking, eating, laughing, knowing their families, knowing them by first names.

01:28:50.760 --> 01:28:56.360
[Guest 1]: I always say that, that investment that you can make in people and when people ask me

01:28:56.360 --> 01:29:01.680
[Guest 1]: saying how do you become a good anchor or a good whatever, I say, be interested or be

01:29:01.680 --> 01:29:02.680
[Guest 1]: interesting.

01:29:02.680 --> 01:29:13.000
[Guest 1]: If you are interested in the other person, that's enough.

01:29:13.000 --> 01:29:14.720
[Amit Varma]: And you know, I know Sulandan a little bit.

01:29:14.720 --> 01:29:20.480
[Amit Varma]: I've, you know, traveled with him when I was sort of touring and in the cricket scene.

01:29:20.480 --> 01:29:21.480
[Guest 2]: The Pakistan tour especially.

01:29:21.480 --> 01:29:22.480
[Amit Varma]: The Pakistan tour especially.

01:29:22.480 --> 01:29:23.960
[Amit Varma]: And I remember him as this lovely, warm person.

01:29:23.960 --> 01:29:24.960
[Amit Varma]: But that's who he is.

01:29:24.960 --> 01:29:26.640
[Amit Varma]: He's a warm, gentle person.

01:29:26.640 --> 01:29:31.920
[Amit Varma]: So everything that he tells you about the importance of meeting people, making them

01:29:31.920 --> 01:29:34.760
[Amit Varma]: happy is, I would imagine it comes naturally to him.

01:29:34.760 --> 01:29:40.240
[Amit Varma]: And it is not as if, you know, if he has put intentionality, then he has put post-facto.

01:29:40.240 --> 01:29:42.880
[Amit Varma]: To me, it seems like that's the kind of person he is.

01:29:42.880 --> 01:29:47.220
[Amit Varma]: And I'm wondering what is the feedback loop between those two?

01:29:47.220 --> 01:29:51.880
[Amit Varma]: Because if you are, for example, intentional about something and you do it all the time,

01:29:51.880 --> 01:29:54.080
[Amit Varma]: at some point it becomes a part of you.

01:29:54.080 --> 01:29:55.080
[Amit Varma]: Right?

01:29:55.080 --> 01:30:01.280
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, so Roshan, when you talk about, for example, investing in people, is it that

01:30:01.280 --> 01:30:04.160
[Amit Varma]: you've always been a warm person who's looking out for others?

01:30:04.160 --> 01:30:07.480
[Amit Varma]: Or is it that at some point you realized that this is a good thing to do?

01:30:07.480 --> 01:30:08.480
[Amit Varma]: It works for me.

01:30:08.480 --> 01:30:09.480
[Amit Varma]: It works for them.

01:30:09.480 --> 01:30:10.480
[Amit Varma]: It works for everyone.

01:30:10.480 --> 01:30:11.520
[Amit Varma]: I'm going to do more of this.

01:30:11.520 --> 01:30:12.880
[Guest 2]: And then it becomes natural to you.

01:30:12.880 --> 01:30:13.880
[Amit Varma]: Can I answer this for Roshan?

01:30:13.880 --> 01:30:14.880
[Unknown]: Sure.

01:30:14.880 --> 01:30:21.720
[Unknown]: I think he's going to say something like, I met him earlier and he was very rude.

01:30:21.720 --> 01:30:25.520
[Guest 2]: I think Roshan is hugely structured.

01:30:25.520 --> 01:30:28.040
[Guest 2]: So if he sees, so there are two aspects to it.

01:30:28.040 --> 01:30:31.240
[Guest 2]: He's a warm person and therefore he's inclined to do this.

01:30:31.240 --> 01:30:36.040
[Guest 2]: But the moment he realizes the value of it, he will routinize it.

01:30:36.040 --> 01:30:42.440
[Guest 2]: Because he is an entrepreneur at heart with a creative, three organs creative, two organs

01:30:42.440 --> 01:30:43.760
[Guest 2]: in other things.

01:30:43.760 --> 01:30:46.040
[Guest 2]: One organ continuously looking for return on investment.

01:30:46.040 --> 01:30:49.040
[Guest 2]: So he's actually left, right, middle brain, sub-combination.

01:30:49.040 --> 01:30:52.040
[Amit Varma]: How many organs are there?

01:30:52.040 --> 01:30:55.040
[Unknown]: I'm trying to identify.

01:30:55.040 --> 01:30:56.040
[Amit Varma]: Multi-organ.

01:30:56.040 --> 01:30:57.040
[Guest 2]: Multi-organ.

01:30:57.040 --> 01:31:04.920
[Guest 2]: So basically, every time you have to understand, and this is Roshan's plus and it's his minus,

01:31:04.920 --> 01:31:11.600
[Guest 2]: is because the moment you become an entrepreneur, and I've seen this in many YPO events that

01:31:11.600 --> 01:31:17.280
[Guest 2]: I perform at, where there are millionaires and trillionaires, see your lens becomes entrepreneurial.

01:31:17.280 --> 01:31:21.240
[Guest 2]: And that sometimes is good, that sometimes is bad, because you are looking at return

01:31:21.240 --> 01:31:22.840
[Guest 2]: on investment on everything.

01:31:22.840 --> 01:31:26.360
[Guest 2]: And you have to be wired like that to become a good entrepreneur.

01:31:26.360 --> 01:31:31.040
[Guest 2]: So the moment the entrepreneur realizes that this is a place of value, his checklist will

01:31:31.040 --> 01:31:32.200
[Guest 2]: have that.

01:31:32.200 --> 01:31:33.200
[Guest 2]: And which is a good thing.

01:31:33.200 --> 01:31:34.600
[Guest 2]: I'm not saying that.

01:31:34.600 --> 01:31:39.080
[Guest 2]: So it is now second nature to invest in people.

01:31:39.080 --> 01:31:44.160
[Guest 2]: Now it starts with warmth, but anything that you want to excel in has to be routinized.

01:31:44.160 --> 01:31:47.560
[Guest 2]: And that's what atomic habits is all about, for that matter.

01:31:47.560 --> 01:31:49.120
[Guest 2]: That is what sport teaches you.

01:31:49.120 --> 01:31:52.240
[Guest 2]: It's about doing the same things again and again.

01:31:52.240 --> 01:31:56.800
[Guest 2]: And that's why if you see Dhoni coming and taking strike, he will, you know, wipe his

01:31:56.800 --> 01:32:01.800
[Guest 2]: brow first, then he'll do this and that, because to come to a point of extreme concentration

01:32:01.800 --> 01:32:06.120
[Guest 2]: and effectiveness, a routine is what takes you to that point.

01:32:06.120 --> 01:32:09.600
[Guest 2]: So many people, you know, ask me, when you're imitating Sachin Tendulkar, why are you doing

01:32:09.600 --> 01:32:10.600
[Guest 2]: that?

01:32:10.600 --> 01:32:15.000
[Guest 2]: I have had a conversation with Sachin and said that if I don't make my cup of tea in

01:32:15.000 --> 01:32:20.760
[Guest 2]: the morning, till the point of time I'm taking strike, everything is the same, because that

01:32:20.760 --> 01:32:26.160
[Guest 2]: brings me to that state of consciousness where I'm facing somebody at 140 and trying to see

01:32:26.160 --> 01:32:28.760
[Guest 2]: whether the ball is reversing or going the other way.

01:32:28.760 --> 01:32:31.840
[Guest 2]: So that routine is what defines excellence.

01:32:31.840 --> 01:32:37.480
[Guest 2]: And I think with Roshan, I've seen that, that when he knows that, boss, I'm going to be

01:32:37.480 --> 01:32:41.400
[Guest 2]: useful in business, I'm going to be useful in personal relationships, I'll routinize

01:32:41.400 --> 01:32:42.400
[Guest 2]: it.

01:32:42.400 --> 01:32:44.280
[Guest 2]: And that's why it's become second nature to him.

01:32:44.280 --> 01:32:49.160
[Guest 2]: With Sunandan also, I have seen that he will not go to anybody's house without taking

01:32:49.160 --> 01:32:50.440
[Guest 2]: that small thing.

01:32:50.440 --> 01:32:55.480
[Guest 2]: And if you've said in one of the conversations that I have that saffron biryani, that's it,

01:32:55.480 --> 01:32:56.800
[Guest 2]: it's in his database.

01:32:56.800 --> 01:33:01.560
[Guest 2]: Now, if he goes to Iran, then Amit, I've brought your saffron.

01:33:01.560 --> 01:33:07.360
[Guest 2]: Now, the thing is, that's coming naturally to him now, but he realizes the significance

01:33:07.360 --> 01:33:08.880
[Guest 1]: of making other people happy.

01:33:08.880 --> 01:33:11.440
[Guest 1]: I'll add to that a little or whatever.

01:33:11.440 --> 01:33:15.640
[Guest 1]: So this, this being warm, etc. was a very Lucknow thing.

01:33:15.640 --> 01:33:20.640
[Guest 1]: My mother had this line which we used to always call her Kalyari Devi, because taking care

01:33:20.640 --> 01:33:24.800
[Guest 1]: of the whole neighborhood, right, from the maid to that person, the ironing woman, the

01:33:24.800 --> 01:33:25.800
[Guest 1]: sweeper.

01:33:25.800 --> 01:33:26.800
[Guest 1]: This is her problem.

01:33:26.800 --> 01:33:32.720
[Guest 1]: Even today, my mother, now we have a, after years, we have a live-in, you know, a help

01:33:32.720 --> 01:33:37.800
[Guest 1]: with a husband who drinks, he's nice at heart, but sometimes he drinks, whatever, that's

01:33:37.800 --> 01:33:38.800
[Guest 1]: the thing.

01:33:38.800 --> 01:33:41.360
[Guest 1]: But his two children, like they are my mother's project right now.

01:33:41.360 --> 01:33:44.680
[Guest 1]: Covering their books and all that is their project.

01:33:44.680 --> 01:33:49.920
[Guest 1]: Now, the children said to him, they came home and they said, Nani, you come to our science

01:33:49.920 --> 01:33:50.920
[Guest 1]: fair.

01:33:50.920 --> 01:33:54.800
[Guest 1]: You know, my father, who doesn't step out, went with such pride.

01:33:54.800 --> 01:34:00.120
[Guest 1]: And I said that look at what it does, it gives them a reason to be, because we all need finally

01:34:00.120 --> 01:34:01.120
[Guest 1]: that reason to be.

01:34:01.120 --> 01:34:04.120
[Guest 1]: For me, I'll tell you, and I'm telling you, I have this with me.

01:34:04.120 --> 01:34:08.440
[Guest 1]: Just to his saffron biryani story, I'll tell you, I love, I'm curious, I love discovering

01:34:08.440 --> 01:34:09.440
[Guest 1]: things.

01:34:09.440 --> 01:34:13.280
[Guest 1]: One day I discovered a place where, when somebody told me that the place called Love Fools that

01:34:13.280 --> 01:34:18.960
[Guest 1]: does this incredible sit-down dinners in Bandra, I went there for the first time, to test it

01:34:18.960 --> 01:34:22.760
[Guest 1]: myself, because I won't introduce my friend that I've tested, you know, properly there.

01:34:22.760 --> 01:34:26.280
[Guest 1]: Beautiful, lovely meal and whatever, loved it and stuff.

01:34:26.280 --> 01:34:29.320
[Guest 1]: Talked to Sarita Pereira, who was the chef, asked her life story.

01:34:29.320 --> 01:34:31.560
[Guest 1]: Now, nobody, people just appreciate the food.

01:34:31.560 --> 01:34:34.160
[Guest 1]: I sat with her for half an hour and I asked her, where did you come from?

01:34:34.160 --> 01:34:38.040
[Guest 1]: I was in Spain, I learnt here, I did this, da-da-da-da-da, whatever.

01:34:38.040 --> 01:34:39.040
[Guest 1]: I went to Turkey.

01:34:39.040 --> 01:34:44.760
[Guest 1]: I'm going to Turkey through the market and suddenly I remember that she had mentioned

01:34:44.760 --> 01:34:49.600
[Guest 1]: to me that many of the spices I used to use in my food, I can't find.

01:34:49.600 --> 01:34:53.720
[Guest 1]: And I just messaged her saying, Sarita, I'm in Turkey, I'm in the spices market, I was

01:34:53.720 --> 01:34:57.160
[Guest 1]: thinking of you, anything I can get for you.

01:34:57.160 --> 01:35:00.480
[Guest 1]: What when I was in Doha, the message I sent, I just sent you that, nothing.

01:35:00.480 --> 01:35:04.760
[Guest 1]: I just suddenly said, Amit, are you fond of football, whatever, whatever, so it's that

01:35:04.760 --> 01:35:05.760
[Guest 1]: thing.

01:35:05.760 --> 01:35:10.960
[Guest 1]: And in that, there's no, it wasn't a matter of profit.

01:35:10.960 --> 01:35:15.200
[Guest 1]: She said, I can get a pepper called Urf Biber, but I can't find it.

01:35:15.200 --> 01:35:18.600
[Guest 1]: I went, I took a box with me, when did you get Urf Biber?

01:35:18.600 --> 01:35:22.560
[Guest 1]: Love Fools is now one of the best known private dining experiences in Bombay.

01:35:22.560 --> 01:35:25.000
[Guest 1]: There are days you can't get a seat or whatever.

01:35:25.000 --> 01:35:27.640
[Guest 1]: I can get anything, anytime.

01:35:27.640 --> 01:35:29.880
[Guest 1]: But because, and but it's not just that.

01:35:29.880 --> 01:35:31.040
[Guest 1]: I will continue the relationship.

01:35:31.040 --> 01:35:34.520
[Guest 1]: Sarita will call me, I'm thinking of opening a speakeasy on top, we'll commune, come and

01:35:34.520 --> 01:35:35.520
[Guest 1]: do something.

01:35:35.520 --> 01:35:42.600
[Guest 1]: You know, this, you have to participate without this thing of, will I fit Papplu in this?

01:35:42.600 --> 01:35:44.600
[Guest 2]: One, which is a big problem.

01:35:44.600 --> 01:35:49.640
[Guest 2]: And I feel that this is not a problem, and this has to be reconciled.

01:35:49.640 --> 01:35:57.680
[Guest 2]: Fitting Papplu is not a problem, because if, and I'm struggling because I haven't done

01:35:57.680 --> 01:36:04.160
[Guest 2]: 99% of the things, because in my lens, I have a lens from Pune, that it's wrong to ask someone

01:36:04.160 --> 01:36:05.160
[Guest 2]: for work.

01:36:05.160 --> 01:36:11.720
[Guest 2]: Now, if you are born from this lens, so then what happens is that, oh man, the whole world

01:36:11.720 --> 01:36:13.720
[Guest 2]: has gone because of merchants.

01:36:13.720 --> 01:36:18.720
[Guest 2]: We have to fit Papplu and bring Columbus there, otherwise why would he have to go there?

01:36:18.720 --> 01:36:24.520
[Guest 2]: But we have to accept that as long as we are seeing win-win, as they say in Sapolsky's

01:36:24.520 --> 01:36:29.840
[Guest 2]: book, this research shows that when two people win, the dopamine production is also high.

01:36:29.840 --> 01:36:32.160
[Guest 2]: The double thank you moment.

01:36:32.160 --> 01:36:33.160
[Guest 2]: Effectively.

01:36:33.160 --> 01:36:40.000
[Guest 2]: So this means that somewhere we have to accept that if we make friends in trade, it's fine.

01:36:40.000 --> 01:36:41.000
[Guest 2]: There is nothing wrong in this.

01:36:41.000 --> 01:36:44.000
[Guest 2]: You are making friends, not enemies.

01:36:44.000 --> 01:36:49.640
[Guest 2]: So I think fitting Papplu has to be acceptable now in order to create.

01:36:49.640 --> 01:36:53.680
[Amit Varma]: I think what Roshan means, and I really agree with that, and I think there is something

01:36:53.680 --> 01:37:00.440
[Amit Varma]: to that, is that at one level you can be instrumental and you can say that I will buy this spice

01:37:00.440 --> 01:37:02.800
[Amit Varma]: so I can get a reservation when I want.

01:37:02.800 --> 01:37:04.800
[Amit Varma]: At one level, you can think like that.

01:37:04.800 --> 01:37:10.160
[Amit Varma]: But if you make it a part of the rules by which you live your life, a normative part

01:37:10.160 --> 01:37:14.560
[Amit Varma]: of you, that whenever I can, I will give a friend what she wants.

01:37:14.560 --> 01:37:19.760
[Amit Varma]: And I think that that leads to Papplu's fitting in unusual ways, which you could not have

01:37:19.760 --> 01:37:20.760
[Guest 2]: imagined.

01:37:20.760 --> 01:37:21.760
[Guest 2]: Absolutely.

01:37:21.760 --> 01:37:22.760
[Guest 2]: But I am reconciling.

01:37:22.760 --> 01:37:28.080
[Guest 2]: I want to come to a point where it's okay to say that, boss, if I give him saffron,

01:37:28.080 --> 01:37:30.520
[Guest 2]: then he will give it to me.

01:37:30.520 --> 01:37:31.520
[Guest 1]: But it is not you.

01:37:31.520 --> 01:37:34.240
[Unknown]: And don't become that.

01:37:34.240 --> 01:37:35.240
[Unknown]: I'll tell you one more thing.

01:37:35.240 --> 01:37:36.240
[Unknown]: I'm not becoming that.

01:37:36.240 --> 01:37:37.240
[Guest 2]: I will never become that.

01:37:37.240 --> 01:37:38.240
[Guest 2]: That's what I'm saying.

01:37:38.240 --> 01:37:39.240
[Guest 2]: Don't get…

01:37:39.240 --> 01:37:41.120
[Guest 2]: But it's okay if you do it.

01:37:41.120 --> 01:37:44.320
[Guest 1]: This is your YPO, EO corruption, which I'm very worried about.

01:37:44.320 --> 01:37:45.320
[Guest 1]: Kindly explain.

01:37:45.320 --> 01:37:46.320
[Unknown]: No, no, no.

01:37:46.320 --> 01:37:47.320
[Unknown]: I'll tell you.

01:37:47.320 --> 01:37:51.360
[Guest 1]: See, YPO and EO events that happen in India, which is these, you have to be a hundred crore

01:37:51.360 --> 01:37:54.040
[Guest 1]: plus or whatever, etc. to be part of one of these organizations.

01:37:54.040 --> 01:37:56.040
[Guest 1]: Vikram has told me a beautiful story.

01:37:56.040 --> 01:37:58.560
[Guest 1]: Actually, I think you should tell me about the negotiation story first.

01:37:58.560 --> 01:38:00.600
[Guest 2]: Then I will build on that.

01:38:00.600 --> 01:38:01.600
[Guest 1]: That's against.

01:38:01.600 --> 01:38:03.080
[Unknown]: Our lens will never understand this.

01:38:03.080 --> 01:38:11.080
[Guest 2]: So I was being called by these YPO, whatever that agency, and every now and then, you know,

01:38:11.080 --> 01:38:17.960
[Guest 2]: Bombay YPO, they're the trillionaire economy, they're giving you an opportunity to perform

01:38:17.960 --> 01:38:18.960
[Guest 2]: in front of the…

01:38:18.960 --> 01:38:21.120
[Guest 2]: I said, boss, I am a middle class Maharashtan.

01:38:21.120 --> 01:38:22.120
[Unknown]: I don't need opportunity.

01:38:22.120 --> 01:38:26.480
[Guest 2]: I cannot do and be happy.

01:38:26.480 --> 01:38:27.720
[Guest 2]: So don't say that.

01:38:27.720 --> 01:38:30.120
[Guest 2]: If you want a discount, I will give you the discount.

01:38:30.120 --> 01:38:33.840
[Guest 2]: It's not that I don't want to do that event.

01:38:33.840 --> 01:38:35.080
[Guest 2]: I want to.

01:38:35.080 --> 01:38:36.960
[Guest 2]: And no corporate negotiates that much.

01:38:36.960 --> 01:38:39.800
[Guest 2]: They will tell you if they want you, they'll give you the money and blah, blah, blah.

01:38:39.800 --> 01:38:42.360
[Guest 2]: But they were at it, at it, at it, at it.

01:38:42.360 --> 01:38:46.480
[Guest 2]: Finally, I told the lady there, I said that I want to do this event free of cost.

01:38:46.480 --> 01:38:49.440
[Guest 2]: No, no, sir, what are you, why are you saying that?

01:38:49.440 --> 01:38:55.320
[Guest 2]: I want to do it free of cost only so that I can tell my grandmom that I work for the

01:38:55.320 --> 01:38:56.320
[Guest 2]: trillionaire people for free.

01:38:56.320 --> 01:39:02.080
[Guest 2]: I have done a favor to them that you will also be happy that there are so many big people

01:39:02.080 --> 01:39:05.520
[Guest 2]: and I told them that you don't have money, so I will do it for free.

01:39:05.520 --> 01:39:06.520
[Amit Varma]: Buy something nice.

01:39:06.520 --> 01:39:07.520
[Guest 2]: Okay, I will do it.

01:39:07.520 --> 01:39:10.240
[Guest 2]: You are poor people, so I will do it for free.

01:39:10.240 --> 01:39:13.280
[Guest 2]: So no, no, no, sir, what are you saying, sir, no, no, we will give you whatever.

01:39:13.280 --> 01:39:15.080
[Guest 2]: And the fee was agreed.

01:39:15.080 --> 01:39:18.200
[Guest 2]: I did the show, Touchwood, it was super successful.

01:39:18.200 --> 01:39:19.760
[Guest 2]: It was a great show.

01:39:19.760 --> 01:39:24.080
[Guest 2]: Everybody who was anybody and stuff like that came and said, what a fabulous performance,

01:39:24.080 --> 01:39:25.080
[Guest 2]: blah, blah, blah.

01:39:25.080 --> 01:39:30.320
[Guest 2]: I got drunk along with three or four people who were probably one lakh crore each.

01:39:30.320 --> 01:39:31.320
[Guest 2]: I can't name them.

01:39:31.320 --> 01:39:32.320
[Guest 2]: I can, but I won't.

01:39:32.320 --> 01:39:33.320
[Guest 1]: But they were there.

01:39:33.320 --> 01:39:44.320
[Unknown]: And then one of the guys who was the organizers, I said, sir, why do you negotiate so much?

01:39:44.320 --> 01:39:48.720
[Guest 2]: Like, why did you bother me so much?

01:39:48.720 --> 01:39:51.480
[Guest 2]: So he said, son, should I tell you something?

01:39:51.480 --> 01:39:52.480
[Guest 2]: So I said, yes, tell me.

01:39:52.480 --> 01:39:59.840
[Guest 2]: He was also drunk, victory, I didn't understand, what is victory?

01:39:59.840 --> 01:40:07.640
[Guest 2]: He said, why are these people so big here, because they win, they win in every negotiation.

01:40:07.640 --> 01:40:17.360
[Guest 2]: Whether the negotiation is yours or a thousand crores, who wins, I win and it dawned to me

01:40:17.360 --> 01:40:24.360
[Guest 2]: that at one level, maybe he's right in the way, but for me, who comes from an art, culture,

01:40:24.360 --> 01:40:32.520
[Guest 2]: giving, charity, Gokhale, Agarkar, that kind of a background, I'm thinking, what a waste

01:40:32.520 --> 01:40:33.520
[Guest 2]: of life.

01:40:33.520 --> 01:40:38.560
[Unknown]: Who wants to win in a relationship, who wants to win in negotiating with an artist.

01:40:38.560 --> 01:40:44.360
[Guest 2]: But then I realized what an, I mean, I'm not saying all entrepreneurs, and it affected

01:40:44.360 --> 01:40:45.360
[Guest 2]: me for seven days.

01:40:45.360 --> 01:40:51.200
[Guest 2]: I said, he wanted to win with me, but then he explained to me, and then it explains the

01:40:51.200 --> 01:40:57.120
[Guest 2]: psychology that when you are negotiating two rupees with rickshaw wala, bhaji wale bechari

01:40:57.120 --> 01:41:01.000
[Guest 2]: itna kaam kare, de dena usko 10 rupee extra, kya farag padta hai.

01:41:01.000 --> 01:41:05.520
[Guest 2]: But that gets ingrained, which is good for entrepreneurship, but when it goes into normal

01:41:05.520 --> 01:41:07.240
[Guest 2]: human relation, it becomes so bad.

01:41:07.240 --> 01:41:12.760
[Guest 2]: And still from that part, then you know that that answered my, that thing na, ki itna 200

01:41:12.760 --> 01:41:18.040
[Guest 2]: crore tere paas tu holiday kyu nahi jata hai, it's because the psychology is not about making

01:41:18.040 --> 01:41:19.520
[Guest 2]: money to enjoy.

01:41:19.520 --> 01:41:23.240
[Guest 2]: It's about making money, because I want to show the other guy that ki main jeeta.

01:41:23.240 --> 01:41:27.880
[Guest 1]: No, no, and see, which is what I'm saying that the curse that I'm saying that he, thankfully

01:41:27.880 --> 01:41:28.880
[Guest 1]: he's not affected by it.

01:41:28.880 --> 01:41:33.400
[Guest 1]: He thinks he is at some point, but it is the thing of, you know, to build contacts because

01:41:33.400 --> 01:41:35.840
[Guest 2]: it will get you ex, blah, blah, blah, it's not him.

01:41:35.840 --> 01:41:39.480
[Guest 1]: And I'll tell you, and this thing, no, I'll tell you, this thing about paplu fit karna,

01:41:39.480 --> 01:41:43.720
[Guest 1]: I have witnessed something, I used to do an interview based show with film stars at one

01:41:43.720 --> 01:41:45.080
[Guest 1]: point in time.

01:41:45.080 --> 01:41:46.640
[Guest 1]: And one day we were doing an interview.

01:41:46.640 --> 01:41:52.280
[Guest 1]: And in that interview, another film star came, looked at this big vehicle, you know, Land

01:41:52.280 --> 01:41:56.080
[Guest 1]: Cruiser or whatever in those days, early, I'm talking late 90s.

01:41:56.080 --> 01:41:59.800
[Guest 1]: And the other actor looked at this guy and said, yeah, I love this vehicle you've got

01:41:59.800 --> 01:42:00.800
[Guest 1]: and whatever.

01:42:00.800 --> 01:42:01.800
[Guest 1]: How did you get it?

01:42:01.800 --> 01:42:02.800
[Guest 1]: He said, don't worry, I've got a great guy, he'll get it for you.

01:42:02.800 --> 01:42:06.120
[Guest 1]: And when I was watching this, I said, yaar kya camaraderie hai, you know, between the

01:42:06.120 --> 01:42:07.120
[Guest 1]: two actors.

01:42:07.120 --> 01:42:10.520
[Guest 1]: And he said, I'm giving you this guy's number, you call him after half an hour.

01:42:10.520 --> 01:42:12.240
[Guest 1]: The other actor went off.

01:42:12.240 --> 01:42:16.440
[Guest 1]: This actor who owned the vehicle, called that guy and said, sunn, main tere ke liye so and

01:42:16.440 --> 01:42:18.440
[Guest 1]: so bhej raha hoon, mera 10% rakh liye na.

01:42:18.440 --> 01:42:19.440
[Guest 1]: Wow.

01:42:19.440 --> 01:42:24.360
[Guest 1]: You know, mere saamne se saara veneer hat gaya, dosti, ye bandhan toh pyaar ka bandhan

01:42:24.360 --> 01:42:25.360
[Guest 1]: hai.

01:42:25.360 --> 01:42:26.360
[Guest 1]: And I said, okay.

01:42:26.360 --> 01:42:27.560
[Guest 1]: But I will never do that.

01:42:27.560 --> 01:42:31.160
[Guest 1]: And I cannot do that because I don't want to be remembered like that.

01:42:31.160 --> 01:42:34.800
[Guest 1]: I do not want to be known that I made a percentage in this deal.

01:42:34.800 --> 01:42:38.720
[Guest 1]: I'll tell you what the beauty is, and it is very difficult for people to understand.

01:42:38.720 --> 01:42:43.120
[Guest 1]: I have at least three people who give me equity in their company without me putting a rupee,

01:42:43.120 --> 01:42:47.920
[Guest 1]: without me asking once because they said, we're so, humaise samajh mein nahi aata, huma

01:42:47.920 --> 01:42:49.160
[Guest 1]: ko kaise payback karein?

01:42:49.160 --> 01:42:53.200
[Guest 1]: Aap humko advise karte hoon, aap humko contract padhte hoon, aap humko business dete hoon,

01:42:53.200 --> 01:42:55.560
[Guest 1]: aap karte hoon, aap kuchh maangte hi nahi hoon.

01:42:55.560 --> 01:42:58.240
[Guest 1]: So, please, we're giving you this 5% in the company.

01:42:58.240 --> 01:43:02.120
[Guest 1]: 5% in a company which is going to grow and I know it'll grow into something big.

01:43:02.120 --> 01:43:03.920
[Guest 1]: And I was like, listen, I don't need this.

01:43:03.920 --> 01:43:04.920
[Guest 1]: No, no, no.

01:43:04.920 --> 01:43:05.920
[Guest 1]: No, if you don't need it.

01:43:05.920 --> 01:43:06.920
[Unknown]: You don't need it.

01:43:06.920 --> 01:43:07.920
[Unknown]: But 2.5% for Sathegu and 2.5% for me, sir.

01:43:07.920 --> 01:43:08.920
[Unknown]: But that.

01:43:08.920 --> 01:43:09.920
[Unknown]: If you have a problem like this, we'll help you.

01:43:09.920 --> 01:43:10.920
[Unknown]: But that.

01:43:10.920 --> 01:43:11.920
[Guest 1]: That's why I befriended you.

01:43:11.920 --> 01:43:12.920
[Guest 1]: But I'm saying the same thing.

01:43:12.920 --> 01:43:13.920
[Guest 1]: But that is the, to me, that is the true joy.

01:43:13.920 --> 01:43:14.920
[Unknown]: That is the real joy.

01:43:14.920 --> 01:43:15.920
[Unknown]: And it's the same thing.

01:43:15.920 --> 01:43:29.520
[Guest 1]: Now, to bring what he said, also think that, oh, you know, I look for routine and I put

01:43:29.520 --> 01:43:30.960
[Guest 1]: it into my structure.

01:43:30.960 --> 01:43:34.580
[Guest 1]: I actually, as I'm saying, I'm an anomaly in these terms.

01:43:34.580 --> 01:43:35.960
[Guest 1]: I did the musical.

01:43:35.960 --> 01:43:40.240
[Guest 1]: I discovered that India doesn't have a musical company culture.

01:43:40.240 --> 01:43:43.560
[Guest 1]: So in America, there is a company theater thing where there'll be a company and the company

01:43:43.560 --> 01:43:46.640
[Guest 1]: will be paid for and they're rehearsing every day, which is why they can put up a musical

01:43:46.640 --> 01:43:47.640
[Guest 1]: every year.

01:43:47.640 --> 01:43:50.720
[Guest 1]: In India, we recruit what we call triple threats.

01:43:50.720 --> 01:43:52.960
[Guest 1]: Triple threats are, you can act, sing and dance.

01:43:52.960 --> 01:43:55.920
[Guest 1]: So that's a triple threat as a performer, right?

01:43:55.920 --> 01:43:59.720
[Guest 1]: And a triple threat performer is very rare to find.

01:43:59.720 --> 01:44:03.200
[Guest 1]: In Disney in the West, how do you get all these big actors?

01:44:03.200 --> 01:44:04.440
[Guest 1]: Because they start from summer camps.

01:44:04.440 --> 01:44:07.240
[Guest 1]: Now, for me, there's a problem to solve.

01:44:07.240 --> 01:44:10.000
[Guest 1]: If you want, there are eight big musicals happening in India.

01:44:10.000 --> 01:44:12.760
[Guest 1]: Believe you me, six of them are going to be disasters.

01:44:12.760 --> 01:44:19.200
[Guest 1]: Because you are trying to hum Bollywood film musical, but, you know, are you training the

01:44:19.200 --> 01:44:20.200
[Guest 1]: actors?

01:44:20.200 --> 01:44:22.080
[Guest 1]: Are you training that base talent?

01:44:22.080 --> 01:44:25.240
[Guest 1]: You will get by because you will pre-record the songs and therefore they'll lip sync.

01:44:25.240 --> 01:44:27.240
[Guest 1]: Then it's not a true musical, right?

01:44:27.240 --> 01:44:30.920
[Guest 1]: You will do it because you got pre-recorded music and not live musicians, then it is not

01:44:30.920 --> 01:44:31.920
[Guest 1]: a musical.

01:44:31.920 --> 01:44:34.560
[Guest 1]: So to preserve that form, you need to develop this.

01:44:34.560 --> 01:44:36.960
[Guest 1]: Now I found a creative problem to solve.

01:44:36.960 --> 01:44:40.040
[Guest 1]: How do you set up a musical theatre company?

01:44:40.040 --> 01:44:43.320
[Guest 1]: So I went to my community, I said, guys, I think we should, we do, we do workshops and

01:44:43.320 --> 01:44:44.320
[Guest 1]: this, this and this.

01:44:44.320 --> 01:44:45.320
[Guest 1]: Why can't we do this?

01:44:45.320 --> 01:44:46.920
[Guest 1]: Now I will solve that.

01:44:46.920 --> 01:44:52.720
[Guest 1]: This is saying trying to find a problem, trying to find a business solution for it and see

01:44:52.720 --> 01:44:53.720
[Guest 1]: if it is implemented.

01:44:53.720 --> 01:44:57.040
[Guest 1]: If it happens only once, it was a creative act of passion.

01:44:57.040 --> 01:45:00.600
[Guest 1]: If it is finds repeat business, it's a business, right?

01:45:00.600 --> 01:45:03.200
[Guest 1]: If it can be repeated, that's one part.

01:45:03.200 --> 01:45:06.680
[Guest 1]: But jumping in and doing crazy things like going and doing this play or suddenly going

01:45:06.680 --> 01:45:10.280
[Guest 1]: and doing a writing work, I mean, when I did the writing workshop with you, it was what?

01:45:10.280 --> 01:45:11.280
[Guest 1]: I have never done it.

01:45:11.280 --> 01:45:12.960
[Guest 1]: Let's do it once and see what happens.

01:45:12.960 --> 01:45:17.840
[Guest 1]: I attended Satyanshu's lectures on filmmaking because I really thought his, and today Satyanshu

01:45:17.840 --> 01:45:20.000
[Guest 1]: is a friend, we are working on something together.

01:45:20.000 --> 01:45:21.840
[Guest 1]: That was not the intention from day one.

01:45:21.840 --> 01:45:23.280
[Guest 1]: The intention was to learn.

01:45:23.280 --> 01:45:26.040
[Guest 1]: The intention was to do something crazy and new.

01:45:26.040 --> 01:45:32.320
[Guest 1]: Satyanshu does the same, but he does it in a pace of doing that now comedy is happening.

01:45:32.320 --> 01:45:33.320
[Guest 1]: It is happening.

01:45:33.320 --> 01:45:34.320
[Guest 1]: It is happening.

01:45:34.320 --> 01:45:38.360
[Guest 1]: But it reached a point where I'm telling you, he got, I told him this when he got pissed

01:45:38.360 --> 01:45:42.880
[Guest 1]: off because everybody would call him a comic, but his logic was, boss, that's a lot of intelligence

01:45:42.880 --> 01:45:44.280
[Guest 1]: and really there is.

01:45:44.280 --> 01:45:47.600
[Guest 1]: Some of his observations in shows, my God, that's a life truth.

01:45:47.600 --> 01:45:48.600
[Guest 1]: It's not comedy.

01:45:48.600 --> 01:45:51.080
[Guest 1]: Zakir today with Tathastu, everybody is going nuts.

01:45:51.080 --> 01:45:55.000
[Guest 1]: Yeah, it's life truths, which is just captured in a format.

01:45:55.000 --> 01:46:01.720
[Guest 1]: So Satya said, no, to prove that I am much more, I must write a book also, I must do

01:46:01.720 --> 01:46:02.720
[Guest 1]: this.

01:46:02.720 --> 01:46:07.560
[Guest 1]: You know, I have to tick off all the intellectual hallmarks, I have written a book, I am a motivational

01:46:07.560 --> 01:46:08.560
[Guest 1]: speaker.

01:46:08.560 --> 01:46:14.640
[Guest 1]: He does all of those things because he has the ability to, but he is a reticent, in 20

01:46:14.640 --> 01:46:16.960
[Guest 2]: years, in 10 years, he will do one thing.

01:46:16.960 --> 01:46:23.640
[Guest 2]: No, but that is the truth because the man who was not intellectual in his system and

01:46:23.640 --> 01:46:29.840
[Guest 2]: did not do the engineering and did not do the IIT and did not do the study abroad kind

01:46:29.840 --> 01:46:30.840
[Guest 2]: of a thing.

01:46:30.840 --> 01:46:35.200
[Guest 2]: There has been, again, from the background, you know, I could have been a classical singer,

01:46:35.200 --> 01:46:37.200
[Guest 2]: I could have been a good cricketer.

01:46:37.200 --> 01:46:43.800
[Guest 2]: So in my mind, boss, I have a brain, so to satisfy my inner self, I have to become intellectual.

01:46:43.800 --> 01:46:46.000
[Guest 2]: Whether it happens or not, I don't know.

01:46:46.000 --> 01:46:50.680
[Guest 2]: That's why I never, stand up comedian, we didn't know anything about that.

01:46:50.680 --> 01:46:56.480
[Guest 2]: And coming back to the chronology, I'll come to the point where I, somebody told me stand

01:46:56.480 --> 01:46:57.480
[Guest 2]: up comedy.

01:46:57.480 --> 01:46:58.480
[Guest 2]: There was no stand up comedy.

01:46:58.480 --> 01:47:05.440
[Guest 2]: 2002, if you remember, Amit, at that point of 98 to 2002, there was Cyrus Brocha, because

01:47:05.440 --> 01:47:10.080
[Guest 2]: we recruited the VJs at that point of time, I joined MTV by then.

01:47:10.080 --> 01:47:12.600
[Unknown]: Shekhar Suman, who was Shekhar?

01:47:12.600 --> 01:47:15.280
[Amit Varma]: That was still later, right?

01:47:15.280 --> 01:47:16.280
[Guest 2]: That was around that time.

01:47:16.280 --> 01:47:17.280
[Guest 2]: I traveled with them.

01:47:17.280 --> 01:47:21.840
[Guest 2]: So English stand up comedy was not there at that time.

01:47:21.840 --> 01:47:26.240
[Guest 2]: But the one great value that MTV added, and I think that changed my life.

01:47:26.240 --> 01:47:30.520
[Guest 2]: And many people don't know, and probably Roshan would know a little bit, that I was actually

01:47:30.520 --> 01:47:35.080
[Guest 2]: a socially anxious person, I had major social anxiety.

01:47:35.080 --> 01:47:37.720
[Guest 2]: And many people think, you're a comedian, how can you be like this?

01:47:37.720 --> 01:47:42.120
[Guest 2]: People don't realize that you might be a cricketer who scores in front of 80,000 people.

01:47:42.120 --> 01:47:45.960
[Guest 2]: But in a small social setup, you can be extremely anxious.

01:47:45.960 --> 01:47:49.640
[Guest 2]: Because you can't make personal one on one conversations and stuff like that.

01:47:49.640 --> 01:47:53.400
[Guest 2]: And it was because of certain incidents of you know, rejection that happened to you in

01:47:53.400 --> 01:47:54.400
[Guest 2]: school college.

01:47:54.400 --> 01:47:58.720
[Guest 2]: Again, I don't remember when and how, but it was there for sure.

01:47:58.720 --> 01:48:01.560
[Guest 2]: And that kind of changed in MTV.

01:48:01.560 --> 01:48:08.080
[Guest 2]: Because MTV was an environment where I had left Pune, and I had come to this place where

01:48:08.080 --> 01:48:10.960
[Guest 2]: and that was the first phase of MTV, right?

01:48:10.960 --> 01:48:13.860
[Guest 2]: Everybody suddenly had become creative.

01:48:13.860 --> 01:48:17.600
[Guest 2]: Everybody was acknowledging that bad jokes are good.

01:48:17.600 --> 01:48:24.360
[Guest 2]: And that bad jokes culture kind of opened my mind and said, here bad jokes are appreciated.

01:48:24.360 --> 01:48:28.380
[Guest 2]: And as Woody Allen would say that there are 100 bad jokes, and there is one good joke.

01:48:28.380 --> 01:48:33.360
[Guest 2]: And that one good joke goes into the library to make a stand up comedy act six months later.

01:48:33.360 --> 01:48:38.720
[Guest 2]: So it's a compilation of 100 good jokes, which come after 10,000 bad jokes.

01:48:38.720 --> 01:48:44.760
[Guest 2]: But that bad joke culture in MTV kind of opened my mind and I got appreciated for doing these

01:48:44.760 --> 01:48:47.080
[Guest 2]: one liners and stuff like that.

01:48:47.080 --> 01:48:52.480
[Guest 2]: Then one fine evening, a common friend Gigi George saw me imitating Sachin Tendulkar.

01:48:52.480 --> 01:48:55.840
[Guest 2]: And he said, What are you doing here, you should be a VJ.

01:48:55.840 --> 01:48:58.680
[Guest 2]: And then there was a VJ hunt next week.

01:48:58.680 --> 01:49:02.460
[Guest 2]: And Brocha called me on stage and I did a five minute act.

01:49:02.460 --> 01:49:05.400
[Guest 2]: And somebody told me it was a stand up comedy.

01:49:05.400 --> 01:49:07.240
[Guest 2]: And I said, What is this?

01:49:07.240 --> 01:49:10.760
[Guest 2]: Because there was no Google and whatever, the only people we idolized was...

01:49:10.760 --> 01:49:12.760
[Amit Varma]: This would have been 98 if I remember.

01:49:12.760 --> 01:49:13.760
[Amit Varma]: 98.

01:49:13.760 --> 01:49:14.760
[Amit Varma]: Yeah.

