[Guest 2]: I remember that.

01:49:17.760 --> 01:49:21.120
[Guest 2]: So it so happened that then I found out, you know, called for some books, Jerry Seinfeld,

01:49:21.120 --> 01:49:26.120
[Guest 2]: I think Seinfeld last season was happening at that point of time, somebody sent me some

01:49:26.120 --> 01:49:27.360
[Guest 2]: clips.

01:49:27.360 --> 01:49:29.760
[Guest 2]: So I started watching that.

01:49:29.760 --> 01:49:35.040
[Guest 2]: And that's when I realized that there is some game in these imitations that I'm doing.

01:49:35.040 --> 01:49:38.280
[Guest 2]: And this Sachin imitation just resonated.

01:49:38.280 --> 01:49:40.180
[Guest 2]: And Sharjah just happened, right?

01:49:40.180 --> 01:49:46.080
[Guest 2]: So that Tony Gregg, Sachin Tendulkar imitation, which I used to do, post the 1998 Sharjah

01:49:46.080 --> 01:49:48.360
[Guest 2]: tour, everybody started liking it.

01:49:48.360 --> 01:49:54.920
[Guest 2]: And I was like, yeah, that was the seed when, you know, I realized that this can be done.

01:49:54.920 --> 01:50:00.520
[Guest 2]: But the MTV environment and all allowed me to do these experiments on stage.

01:50:00.520 --> 01:50:02.400
[Guest 2]: And you know that imitation, right?

01:50:02.400 --> 01:50:04.920
[Guest 1]: Please, can we have it?

