[Guest 2]: So you were, what were you called?

01:51:51.360 --> 01:51:54.760
[Guest 2]: And you guys also did that for around 7-8 years.

01:51:54.760 --> 01:51:55.760
[Guest 2]: You are filler.

01:51:55.760 --> 01:52:00.440
[Unknown]: So our name for our profession was filler.

01:52:00.440 --> 01:52:01.440
[Guest 2]: So will you become a filler?

01:52:01.440 --> 01:52:02.440
[Guest 2]: I said, wherever you fill it, we will fill it.

01:52:02.440 --> 01:52:03.440
[Unknown]: We were getting paid.

01:52:03.440 --> 01:52:11.000
[Guest 2]: It was the first show, so we were not getting paid, but still we said we will pay a little.

01:52:11.000 --> 01:52:17.320
[Guest 2]: So I go to this Pancharatna building in South Mumbai, where the diamond, this thing is there.

01:52:17.320 --> 01:52:22.360
[Guest 2]: And I enter this Diamond Merchant is sitting, and there's three levels of security, I go

01:52:22.360 --> 01:52:23.360
[Guest 2]: there.

01:52:23.360 --> 01:52:24.360
[Guest 2]: What do you do?

01:52:24.360 --> 01:52:29.840
[Guest 2]: Filler, I said, you called me for filler, so I will fill it, what else should I say?

01:52:29.840 --> 01:52:31.120
[Guest 2]: So do it.

01:52:31.120 --> 01:52:35.320
[Guest 2]: So I did this imitation, and that's when I got my first show.

01:52:35.320 --> 01:52:40.520
[Guest 2]: He said, only a week later, I realized that this was a big show of the diamond industry

01:52:40.520 --> 01:52:43.280
[Guest 2]: along with the Oppenheimers of South Africa.

01:52:43.280 --> 01:52:49.120
[Guest 2]: And they were playing a cricket match, and there was Daler Mehndi, and I was a filler.

01:52:49.120 --> 01:52:54.920
[Guest 2]: That day, I realized that boss, if 200 diamond merchants are laughing for 10 to 12 minutes

01:52:54.920 --> 01:52:58.320
[Guest 2]: as a filler, there is something there.

01:52:58.320 --> 01:53:02.880
[Guest 2]: And in that MTV time, in that marketing, wherever I got this opportunity, I played Sidhu along

01:53:02.880 --> 01:53:09.320
[Guest 2]: with Cyrus Saukar in that show called MTV Fully Faltu, which did you write that show?

01:53:09.320 --> 01:53:14.760
[Guest 2]: I don't think I wrote that because I don't remember it, but my memory is a bit like yours.

01:53:14.760 --> 01:53:20.560
[Guest 2]: So I think Mrityunjay wrote that, before that, you did a couple of shows.

01:53:20.560 --> 01:53:24.000
[Guest 2]: And then that's when I realized that boss, there is something here.

01:53:24.000 --> 01:53:26.280
[Guest 2]: Something is going right here.

01:53:26.280 --> 01:53:28.120
[Guest 2]: And then the big break happened.

01:53:28.120 --> 01:53:32.100
[Guest 2]: And that was the time I had left MTV and joined the movie industry.

01:53:32.100 --> 01:53:38.600
[Guest 2]: The promoters of Sony had started a company and again, see, my thing was Metallite Productions.

01:53:38.600 --> 01:53:43.120
[Guest 2]: So we were, as marketing guys, we were the first to enter the television industry.

01:53:43.120 --> 01:53:48.320
[Guest 2]: And I said, before I experiment with these shows and all, let me do Bollywood once.

01:53:48.320 --> 01:53:51.880
[Guest 2]: And that was the time promoters of Sony started a film company.

01:53:51.880 --> 01:53:56.120
[Guest 2]: And this one and a half years were great lessons in human observations.

01:53:56.120 --> 01:53:59.320
[Guest 2]: I learned about the entertainment industry and I'll share some with you.

01:53:59.320 --> 01:54:05.120
[Guest 2]: I did marketing for three films, Nagesh Kuknoor's second film after Hyderabad Blues, which was

01:54:05.120 --> 01:54:07.360
[Guest 2]: called Teen Diware.

01:54:07.360 --> 01:54:13.200
[Guest 2]: There was Madhur Bhandar's second film after Chandni Bar called Satta with Raveena Tandon.

01:54:13.200 --> 01:54:19.760
[Guest 2]: And there was a film called Dil Wil Pyaar Pyaar, which was Anant Mahadevan's debut film.

01:54:19.760 --> 01:54:23.880
[Guest 2]: This is when I entered the movie industry before we come to that legendary moment that

01:54:23.880 --> 01:54:28.480
[Guest 2]: I had with Roshan Abbas, which kind of propelled the standup career.

01:54:28.480 --> 01:54:34.680
[Guest 2]: I spent one and a half years and I realized that this is a fascinating place just for

01:54:34.680 --> 01:54:37.720
[Guest 2]: people who like to observe other people.

01:54:37.720 --> 01:54:45.160
[Guest 2]: And here is where this, you know, small town interfacing with the established community

01:54:45.160 --> 01:54:47.880
[Guest 2]: is what I saw in real time.

01:54:47.880 --> 01:54:48.880
[Guest 2]: And it was great, right?

01:54:48.880 --> 01:54:50.560
[Guest 2]: At that point of time, there was no corporatization.

01:54:50.560 --> 01:54:53.680
[Guest 2]: I was the first marketing guy in an unorganized sector.

01:54:53.680 --> 01:54:59.360
[Guest 2]: So the old school script writers would come and, you know, show you scripts and stuff

01:54:59.360 --> 01:55:00.360
[Guest 2]: like that.

01:55:00.360 --> 01:55:03.000
[Guest 2]: And there was this funny incident that happened.

01:55:03.000 --> 01:55:05.000
[Guest 2]: A scriptwriter in Warsaw came and said,

01:55:05.000 --> 01:55:10.520
[Guest 2]: You are a new guy, I will tell you such a script, sir, you will go crazy.

01:55:10.520 --> 01:55:16.040
[Guest 2]: So now, two hours and we were still at the first shot.

01:55:16.040 --> 01:55:19.920
[Guest 2]: The man comes in, so what's next?

01:55:19.920 --> 01:55:22.560
[Guest 2]: The camera grabs the man.

01:55:22.560 --> 01:55:23.960
[Guest 2]: This went for one hour.

01:55:23.960 --> 01:55:26.360
[Guest 2]: We were still in the first scene.

01:55:26.360 --> 01:55:29.160
[Guest 2]: Then I said, sir, I have to go out a little.

01:55:29.160 --> 01:55:31.400
[Guest 2]: She won't understand people like you.

01:55:31.400 --> 01:55:33.960
[Guest 2]: So I said, what do I do now?

01:55:33.960 --> 01:55:34.960
[Guest 2]: You come later.

01:55:34.960 --> 01:55:41.960
[Guest 2]: Sir, let me tell you one thing, once you get this picture, you'll have to take it off.

01:55:41.960 --> 01:55:47.960
[Unknown]: I was like, what a life!

01:55:47.960 --> 01:55:50.960
[Unknown]: But this is full.

01:55:50.960 --> 01:55:53.960
[Unknown]: Oh man, I said, what a world this is.

01:55:53.960 --> 01:55:54.960
[Guest 2]: Unbelievable.

01:55:54.960 --> 01:55:56.960
[Unknown]: Was it ever made?

01:55:56.960 --> 01:55:59.960
[Guest 2]: I don't know, it was never made.

01:55:59.960 --> 01:56:02.960
[Guest 2]: So here I have two observations.

01:56:02.960 --> 01:56:06.960
[Guest 2]: I got to learn very closely watching a lot of actors.

01:56:06.960 --> 01:56:09.960
[Guest 2]: And I am sure Roshan relates to these observations.

01:56:09.960 --> 01:56:16.960
[Guest 2]: Because I realized that there is an amazing thing that is happening between the established community.

01:56:16.960 --> 01:56:21.960
[Guest 2]: Which is people who don't consider this as a big thing because they are born in families.

01:56:21.960 --> 01:56:26.960
[Guest 2]: Who have all the resources and they have set the benchmark of coolness.

01:56:26.960 --> 01:56:29.960
[Guest 2]: They will talk Americanism, this is the kind of cinema we watch.

01:56:29.960 --> 01:56:33.960
[Guest 2]: Yes, Bollywood wants to make the same movies but they will do all of this.

01:56:33.960 --> 01:56:38.960
[Guest 2]: Now this is a benchmark that is set and this is the value of cool that has been attached.

01:56:38.960 --> 01:56:45.960
[Guest 2]: Now the small time actors from smaller cities come and interact with them.

01:56:45.960 --> 01:56:48.960
[Guest 2]: With a lot of social anxiety.

01:56:48.960 --> 01:56:54.960
[Guest 2]: And they realize that their work or their abilities is not what is going to be judged.

01:56:54.960 --> 01:56:58.960
[Guest 2]: How they behave in this milieu is what they are going to be judged on.

01:56:58.960 --> 01:57:02.960
[Guest 2]: And this is where I see a lot of this sad thing happening.

01:57:02.960 --> 01:57:07.960
[Guest 2]: Where a Marathi actor has come from say Satara, who is a good actor.

01:57:07.960 --> 01:57:13.960
[Guest 2]: Comes and goes into a party where those standard Juhu boys and girls are behaving in a certain way.

01:57:13.960 --> 01:57:20.960
[Guest 2]: And the entire next three years this guy is practicing to be that person.

01:57:20.960 --> 01:57:24.960
[Guest 2]: So that he feels that they will now accept him and give him that first role.

01:57:24.960 --> 01:57:29.960
[Guest 2]: And that one and a half two years is so traumatic because I am seeing the Marathi.

01:57:29.960 --> 01:57:33.960
[Guest 2]: Because I am now a guy who is MBA educated, can speak English and I am this.

01:57:33.960 --> 01:57:36.960
[Guest 2]: So that my social acceptability is reasonable here.

01:57:36.960 --> 01:57:40.960
[Guest 2]: And because I can speak good Marathi, my acceptability with this guy is also good.

01:57:40.960 --> 01:57:47.960
[Guest 2]: And I see this guy from somebody who is discussing Pula Deshpande, Gadhi Madgulkar, Kumar Gandharva.

01:57:47.960 --> 01:57:50.960
[Guest 2]: To suddenly meeting me in a party one year later.

01:57:50.960 --> 01:57:52.960
[Guest 2]: Hey babes, what's up dude?

01:57:52.960 --> 01:57:55.960
[Unknown]: And I am like, what has happened to this person?

01:57:55.960 --> 01:58:00.960
[Guest 2]: And then I realized that this man is finished from inside.

01:58:00.960 --> 01:58:06.960
[Guest 2]: Because his entire focus has gone that how can this director who lives in Juhu accept me?

01:58:06.960 --> 01:58:09.960
[Guest 2]: And he goes inside that party, those people are making fun of him.

01:58:09.960 --> 01:58:18.960
[Guest 2]: And then I realized that if there was an organization which just makes these two ends meet properly, talent will be discovered.

01:58:18.960 --> 01:58:25.960
[Guest 2]: But trust me, nine out of ten talents that I met during that time was struggling to just fit in.

01:58:25.960 --> 01:58:29.960
[Guest 2]: Because they wanted to say dude and babes, rather than practice their craft.

01:58:29.960 --> 01:58:35.960
[Guest 2]: And unfortunately, that is the part I saw and I realized that this the Haryana factor that you are talking about.

01:58:35.960 --> 01:58:40.960
[Guest 2]: That time 20 years back I thought that I wish there were stars in their own domain.

01:58:40.960 --> 01:58:42.960
[Guest 2]: And they didn't have to suffer this.

01:58:42.960 --> 01:58:45.960
[Guest 2]: That was one thing I learned which I saw very closely.

01:58:45.960 --> 01:58:50.960
[Guest 2]: The second thing was the dynamics of actors coming late.

01:58:50.960 --> 01:58:53.960
[Guest 2]: Or behaving in a particular manner.

01:58:53.960 --> 01:58:57.960
[Unknown]: And I used to say that dude, what is the problem of coming on time?

01:58:57.960 --> 01:59:00.960
[Guest 2]: And then there was this celebration culture.

01:59:00.960 --> 01:59:04.960
[Guest 2]: That sir, this actor comes at least 6 hours late.

01:59:04.960 --> 01:59:06.960
[Guest 2]: And he is a big actor.

01:59:06.960 --> 01:59:08.960
[Guest 2]: And this was getting celebrated.

01:59:08.960 --> 01:59:12.960
[Guest 2]: And I said, what is this psychology of people celebrating bad behavior?

01:59:12.960 --> 01:59:16.960
[Guest 2]: And then one actress, she started to behave very badly on the set.

01:59:16.960 --> 01:59:21.960
[Guest 2]: So I went to her and I said that ma'am, I mean, everybody is normal.

01:59:21.960 --> 01:59:23.960
[Guest 2]: If you have any issues, just let me know. I'll sort it out.

01:59:23.960 --> 01:59:25.960
[Guest 2]: And I was trying to be structured.

01:59:25.960 --> 01:59:28.960
[Guest 2]: Because that's the only thing I knew coming from a corporate background.

01:59:28.960 --> 01:59:31.960
[Guest 2]: And if you were structured, you were considered uncool.

01:59:31.960 --> 01:59:33.960
[Guest 2]: But I told her that this is what.

01:59:33.960 --> 01:59:36.960
[Guest 2]: And one day she got drunk and she called me to the set.

01:59:36.960 --> 01:59:39.960
[Guest 2]: And then we went to the vanity van and she told me that.

01:59:39.960 --> 01:59:41.960
[Guest 2]: Dude, come here.

01:59:41.960 --> 01:59:44.960
[Guest 2]: Let me explain to you what industry is.

01:59:44.960 --> 01:59:47.960
[Guest 2]: And I said, yes, ma'am, explain.

01:59:47.960 --> 01:59:49.960
[Guest 2]: Did you find anything lacking on the set?

01:59:49.960 --> 01:59:54.960
[Guest 2]: She said, if I behave well, you all will take me for granted.

01:59:54.960 --> 01:59:59.960
[Guest 2]: So I make sure that every day of my film, first day, I break a glass.

01:59:59.960 --> 02:00:02.960
[Guest 2]: I do something so that I start getting respect.

02:00:02.960 --> 02:00:06.960
[Guest 2]: If I don't do that, even the spot boy won't give me tea.

02:00:06.960 --> 02:00:11.960
[Guest 2]: When I do the first day, then I will get respect in the industry.

02:00:11.960 --> 02:00:15.960
[Guest 2]: And I was like, what kind of behavior is this?

02:00:15.960 --> 02:00:19.960
[Guest 2]: But then I realized that all this creative ecosystem here.

02:00:19.960 --> 02:00:22.960
[Guest 2]: Was about getting attention to yourself.

02:00:22.960 --> 02:00:25.960
[Guest 2]: And therefore it was important to behave badly.

02:00:25.960 --> 02:00:27.960
[Guest 2]: And that became culture.

02:00:27.960 --> 02:00:31.960
[Guest 2]: So if an actor came on time, he was considered an idiot.

02:00:31.960 --> 02:00:33.960
[Guest 2]: So he came three hours late.

02:00:33.960 --> 02:00:35.960
[Guest 2]: So that there was this danger and stuff like that.

02:00:35.960 --> 02:00:38.960
[Guest 2]: And this human behavior was great to watch.

02:00:38.960 --> 02:00:42.960
[Guest 2]: Because this was exactly what is the opposite of what is taught to you in management school.

02:00:42.960 --> 02:00:45.960
[Guest 2]: That systems and data and all of that.

02:00:45.960 --> 02:00:50.960
[Guest 2]: And then I realized the creative industry is about interplay of all these emotions put together.

02:00:50.960 --> 02:00:54.960
[Guest 2]: And to give structure to this emotional ecosystem.

02:00:54.960 --> 02:00:57.960
[Guest 2]: Is going to be the biggest challenge for the future.

02:00:57.960 --> 02:00:59.960
[Guest 2]: And that point of time there was no corporatization.

02:00:59.960 --> 02:01:03.960
[Guest 2]: So these were observations that kind of made me interested in this.

02:01:03.960 --> 02:01:05.960
[Guest 2]: And say like how do people behave.

02:01:05.960 --> 02:01:08.960
[Guest 2]: And that point of time the magic moment happened.

02:01:08.960 --> 02:01:11.960
[Guest 2]: When I got a call from Mr. Roshan Abbas.

02:01:11.960 --> 02:01:14.960
[Guest 2]: And said that, he didn't know me at that time.

02:01:14.960 --> 02:01:17.960
[Guest 2]: He said, I have heard that you do filler-biller.

02:01:17.960 --> 02:01:21.960
[Guest 2]: So can you do it for 12-15 minutes?

02:01:21.960 --> 02:01:23.960
[Guest 2]: So I said yes, I can do stuff like that.

02:01:23.960 --> 02:01:25.960
[Guest 1]: And this is for the Seat Cricket Awards.

02:01:25.960 --> 02:01:27.960
[Guest 1]: This is for the Seat Cricket Awards, which is the biggest property.

02:01:27.960 --> 02:01:30.960
[Guest 2]: And this is the property I had worked in professional management through.

02:01:30.960 --> 02:01:34.960
[Guest 2]: Where you know how the rating systems is created for cricketers and stuff like that.

02:01:34.960 --> 02:01:38.960
[Guest 2]: Now there were, Roshan said, there is no English stand-up.

02:01:38.960 --> 02:01:40.960
[Guest 2]: He doesn't know what I do.

02:01:40.960 --> 02:01:43.960
[Guest 2]: So he says, you come to my house.

02:01:43.960 --> 02:01:44.960
[Guest 2]: Okay.

02:01:44.960 --> 02:01:48.960
[Guest 2]: Whatever you are going to do, you have to do it in front of me.

02:01:48.960 --> 02:01:49.960
[Guest 2]: I had no benchmark.

02:01:49.960 --> 02:01:51.960
[Guest 2]: I said okay, I will dance at his house.

02:01:51.960 --> 02:01:53.960
[Guest 2]: What's the big deal in this?

02:01:53.960 --> 02:01:57.960
[Guest 2]: At the same time, he said that after doing it in my house,

02:01:57.960 --> 02:02:01.960
[Guest 2]: Harsh Goenka, who is the chairman of Seat, his people will also call you.

02:02:01.960 --> 02:02:02.960
[Guest 2]: You have to go there too.

02:02:02.960 --> 02:02:07.960
[Guest 2]: So imagine a time where the stand-up comedian first goes to the event agency.

02:02:07.960 --> 02:02:11.960
[Guest 2]: Roshan Abbas is sitting there with his friend and says, do it.

02:02:11.960 --> 02:02:13.960
[Unknown]: Very sure.

02:02:13.960 --> 02:02:15.960
[Guest 2]: Very sure.

02:02:15.960 --> 02:02:17.960
[Guest 2]: Like, dance.

02:02:17.960 --> 02:02:19.960
[Guest 2]: And I did the act.

02:02:19.960 --> 02:02:21.960
[Guest 2]: Roshan has no idea about cricket.

02:02:21.960 --> 02:02:25.960
[Guest 2]: But Roshan knows that it is working.

02:02:25.960 --> 02:02:28.960
[Guest 2]: So he says that I think this is fine.

02:02:28.960 --> 02:02:29.960
[Guest 2]: Whatever he is doing.

02:02:29.960 --> 02:02:32.960
[Guest 2]: But obviously, because imitations and all is something that he would know.

02:02:32.960 --> 02:02:35.960
[Guest 2]: He said that tomorrow you have to go to Mr. Harsh Goenka.

02:02:35.960 --> 02:02:39.960
[Guest 2]: Now Mr. Harsh Goenka with six people are sitting in a boardroom.

02:02:39.960 --> 02:02:45.960
[Guest 2]: And I suddenly feel I am in MBA entrance exam going for my first job.

02:02:45.960 --> 02:02:48.960
[Guest 2]: And they say that, because nobody knows, right?

02:02:48.960 --> 02:02:51.960
[Guest 2]: What is a stand-up English comedian going to do?

02:02:51.960 --> 02:02:54.960
[Guest 2]: Because what is the line-up for the Seat Awards?

02:02:54.960 --> 02:02:57.960
[Guest 2]: Akshay Kumar, Priyanka Chopra, Urmila Matondkar, Mahima Chaudhary.

02:02:57.960 --> 02:02:59.960
[Amit Varma]: And to put an item in between.

02:02:59.960 --> 02:03:01.960
[Guest 1]: This is 2001, I am guessing.

02:03:01.960 --> 02:03:02.960
[Guest 1]: Three.

02:03:02.960 --> 02:03:03.960
[Guest 1]: Three.

02:03:03.960 --> 02:03:07.960
[Guest 1]: And our line-up was Priyanka Chopra doing her first event.

02:03:07.960 --> 02:03:09.960
[Unknown]: First event.

02:03:09.960 --> 02:03:13.960
[Guest 1]: There was Gauhar, there was Mandira, there was Priyanka, there was Ramona.

02:03:13.960 --> 02:03:15.960
[Unknown]: I forget the main actor.

02:03:15.960 --> 02:03:16.960
[Guest 1]: No, no, there was Akshay Kumar.

02:03:16.960 --> 02:03:18.960
[Guest 1]: Urmila Matondkar was there.

02:03:18.960 --> 02:03:19.960
[Guest 1]: But it was a big line-up.

02:03:19.960 --> 02:03:20.960
[Guest 2]: Big line-up.

02:03:20.960 --> 02:03:23.960
[Guest 2]: So I go there, I do my 10 minutes.

02:03:23.960 --> 02:03:26.960
[Guest 2]: I am still working in MetLight.

02:03:26.960 --> 02:03:29.960
[Guest 2]: So I remember the day when this happened.

02:03:29.960 --> 02:03:32.960
[Guest 2]: My boss was not letting me go fast.

02:03:32.960 --> 02:03:34.960
[Guest 2]: So I said no, I have to go to perform at the Seat Awards.

02:03:34.960 --> 02:03:36.960
[Guest 2]: So finally he left me.

02:03:36.960 --> 02:03:40.960
[Guest 2]: I came to Taj Crystal where the Seat Awards were there.

02:03:40.960 --> 02:03:42.960
[Guest 2]: And I was so badly dressed.

02:03:42.960 --> 02:03:44.960
[Guest 2]: Because I was in like corporate apna trouser.

02:03:44.960 --> 02:03:47.960
[Guest 2]: And there only I realized everybody is in jacket.

02:03:47.960 --> 02:03:51.960
[Guest 2]: That was my first exposure to the fact that this stand-up comedian is like this.

02:03:51.960 --> 02:03:54.960
[Guest 2]: I just wore my Jeffrey Boycott cap there.

02:03:54.960 --> 02:03:58.960
[Guest 2]: But thankfully Roshan said that we need a little bit of design in your act.

02:03:58.960 --> 02:04:01.960
[Guest 2]: Since then they were thinking.

02:04:01.960 --> 02:04:07.960
[Guest 2]: So he got me a bar where I could hang my caps.

02:04:07.960 --> 02:04:10.960
[Guest 2]: So that every time I do an impersonation, I wear that.

02:04:10.960 --> 02:04:11.960
[Unknown]: Change the cap.

02:04:11.960 --> 02:04:12.960
[Guest 2]: Wow.

02:04:12.960 --> 02:04:14.960
[Guest 2]: And I met Ian Chappell there.

02:04:14.960 --> 02:04:20.960
[Guest 2]: And that was my, you know, all these years of cricket.

02:04:20.960 --> 02:04:23.960
[Guest 2]: I was very happy to meet Ian Chappell there.

02:04:23.960 --> 02:04:25.960
[Guest 2]: And he said, you know, so I got myself introduced.

02:04:25.960 --> 02:04:27.960
[Guest 2]: I said I am doing this act and stuff like that.

02:04:27.960 --> 02:04:32.960
[Guest 2]: And I reached there and I found out that the India and the Australian team are going to be in the audience.

02:04:32.960 --> 02:04:33.960
[Guest 2]: Which I was not told.

02:04:33.960 --> 02:04:35.960
[Guest 2]: I thought there would be ex-cricketers and stuff like that.

02:04:35.960 --> 02:04:38.960
[Guest 2]: But these two and the God himself.

02:04:38.960 --> 02:04:44.960
[Guest 2]: I mean people who we have idolized got exasperated bowling to him and so on and so forth.

02:04:44.960 --> 02:04:45.960
[Guest 2]: And they are all sitting there.

02:04:45.960 --> 02:04:49.960
[Guest 2]: And I am Jamureh Natch.

02:04:49.960 --> 02:04:53.960
[Guest 2]: That 15 minutes changed my life.

02:04:53.960 --> 02:04:59.960
[Guest 2]: Because when you see a Sunil Gavaskar, Bishan Bedi and Ricky Ponting laughing.

02:04:59.960 --> 02:05:03.960
[Guest 2]: And you've been propelled into a world which was actually your world, right?

02:05:03.960 --> 02:05:07.960
[Guest 2]: This is all the precursor to that world that you wanted to be part of.

02:05:07.960 --> 02:05:11.960
[Guest 2]: Not only as a player but as somebody who loved the game so much.

02:05:11.960 --> 02:05:15.960
[Guest 2]: And that 15 minutes and imitation of Gavaskar's walk.

02:05:15.960 --> 02:05:16.960
[Guest 2]: And I came down.

02:05:16.960 --> 02:05:18.960
[Guest 2]: Bishan Singh Bedi hugged me.

02:05:18.960 --> 02:05:24.960
[Guest 2]: And Chappelli came and told me that, you know, next time in your act I should be there and stuff like that.

02:05:24.960 --> 02:05:26.960
[Guest 2]: I said, boss.

02:05:26.960 --> 02:05:29.960
[Guest 2]: This is what I was born for.

02:05:29.960 --> 02:05:31.960
[Guest 2]: This is my domain.

02:05:31.960 --> 02:05:38.960
[Guest 2]: I didn't interact with Akshay Kumar and Amitabh Bachchan.

02:05:38.960 --> 02:05:41.960
[Guest 2]: But for me I was a failed sports person.

02:05:41.960 --> 02:05:43.960
[Guest 2]: So I had to live the dream in another way.

02:05:43.960 --> 02:05:47.960
[Guest 2]: And that kind of got me thinking.

02:05:47.960 --> 02:05:50.960
[Guest 2]: And I think another one month I gave my resignation.

02:05:50.960 --> 02:05:55.960
[Guest 2]: But the beauty of that, no YouTube generation, no Google.

02:05:55.960 --> 02:05:57.960
[Guest 2]: That actually clip went viral.

02:05:57.960 --> 02:06:01.960
[Guest 2]: Because they showed that show some 50 times on Sony.

02:06:01.960 --> 02:06:04.960
[Guest 2]: And because of that I started getting calls.

02:06:04.960 --> 02:06:08.960
[Guest 2]: Roshan got me a show with Castrol if I am not wrong.

02:06:08.960 --> 02:06:11.960
[Guest 2]: Sahara Golf and Castrol became your regular.

02:06:11.960 --> 02:06:13.960
[Guest 2]: We were very big in corporate.

02:06:13.960 --> 02:06:15.960
[Guest 1]: That was a little later.

02:06:15.960 --> 02:06:16.960
[Guest 1]: But it just kept rolling.

02:06:16.960 --> 02:06:23.960
[Guest 1]: I remember every 6 months Sathe's rates used to double because he would have done so many shows that his marketing bite would work.

02:06:23.960 --> 02:06:27.960
[Guest 1]: He knows that agencies have their own little layer.

02:06:27.960 --> 02:06:29.960
[Unknown]: There is so much demand.

02:06:29.960 --> 02:06:31.960
[Guest 2]: Boom, boom, boom, boom.

02:06:31.960 --> 02:06:33.960
[Guest 2]: At that time I was in 10-12 minutes.

02:06:33.960 --> 02:06:35.960
[Guest 2]: I had to take this for 40 minutes.

02:06:35.960 --> 02:06:38.960
[Guest 2]: And now I only had cricket stuff.

02:06:38.960 --> 02:06:41.960
[Guest 2]: By this time I had increased my reading.

02:06:41.960 --> 02:06:44.960
[Guest 2]: I had started writing on observations.

02:06:44.960 --> 02:06:46.960
[Guest 2]: Whether those were the standard observations.

02:06:46.960 --> 02:06:49.960
[Guest 2]: I had started following what is the concept of the American.

02:06:49.960 --> 02:06:55.960
[Guest 2]: I believe that no comedian ever in the history of mankind can touch him.

02:06:55.960 --> 02:06:58.960
[Guest 2]: Because there was no standard thing of premise and punchline.

02:06:58.960 --> 02:07:00.960
[Guest 2]: This is a very bore concept.

02:07:00.960 --> 02:07:01.960
[Guest 2]: Premise and punchline.

02:07:01.960 --> 02:07:05.960
[Guest 2]: It is basically very populist way of getting a laughter.

02:07:05.960 --> 02:07:11.960
[Guest 2]: Pula Deshpande would talk 2 hours on walking in Vele Parle and he would make you laugh.

02:07:11.960 --> 02:07:14.960
[Guest 2]: It was that quality of humor.

02:07:14.960 --> 02:07:17.960
[Guest 2]: But then I realized that this is literary humor.

02:07:17.960 --> 02:07:24.960
[Guest 2]: Your understanding of life and society should be so high that you pick so many nuances.

02:07:24.960 --> 02:07:29.960
[Guest 2]: So then I followed the quintessential American model of that build the story and then the punchline.

02:07:29.960 --> 02:07:31.960
[Guest 2]: Build story, get punchline.

02:07:31.960 --> 02:07:33.960
[Guest 2]: I started doing that in cricket as well.

02:07:33.960 --> 02:07:36.960
[Guest 2]: And while I was doing this writing and stuff like that.

02:07:36.960 --> 02:07:40.960
[Guest 2]: I realized that my corporate job was now coming to an end.

02:07:40.960 --> 02:07:45.960
[Guest 2]: Though I have started enjoying putting a movie project together and seeing it till the end.

02:07:45.960 --> 02:07:49.960
[Guest 2]: I said that this looks like a far better in my zone.

02:07:49.960 --> 02:07:51.960
[Guest 2]: And then I quit my job.

02:07:51.960 --> 02:07:56.960
[Guest 2]: And just before quitting my job I got a call from the Sony network.

02:07:56.960 --> 02:07:59.960
[Guest 2]: This was 2003 World Cup.

02:07:59.960 --> 02:08:02.960
[Guest 2]: So my last film was still to release.

02:08:02.960 --> 02:08:08.960
[Guest 2]: And one of the shows that I had performed in MTV, the Sony chairman was there and Kapil Dev was also there.

02:08:08.960 --> 02:08:15.960
[Guest 2]: And these two guys had said that we are launching this kid with extra innings.

02:08:15.960 --> 02:08:22.960
[Guest 2]: I always joke in my initial years that nobody noticed me on extra innings because of Mandira Bedi.

02:08:22.960 --> 02:08:27.960
[Guest 2]: Even Bishan Singh Bedi didn't get noticed for years after taking 266 wickets.

02:08:27.960 --> 02:08:30.960
[Guest 2]: But to me that extra innings moment changed my life.

02:08:30.960 --> 02:08:35.960
[Guest 2]: I went to South Africa for the Cricket World Cup 2003.

02:08:35.960 --> 02:08:37.960
[Guest 2]: We stayed in Cape Town for two months.

02:08:37.960 --> 02:08:42.960
[Guest 2]: I witnessed the Centurion, Big Game, India, Pakistan as a cricket presenter.

02:08:42.960 --> 02:08:46.960
[Guest 2]: And the first day, Amit, I land in Cape Town.

02:08:46.960 --> 02:08:48.960
[Guest 2]: I don't know what I'm going to do, right?

02:08:48.960 --> 02:08:51.960
[Guest 2]: I've been told extra innings, you have to be a filler.

02:08:51.960 --> 02:08:54.960
[Guest 2]: And you have to fill in between the broadcast.

02:08:54.960 --> 02:09:03.960
[Guest 2]: And as soon as I land, this studio head takes me to a room where I enter and I see the mighty Tony Gregg.

02:09:03.960 --> 02:09:08.960
[Guest 2]: Six feet, seven inches, and I'm like, wow, this is something.

02:09:08.960 --> 02:09:12.960
[Guest 2]: And it's South Africa 2003, India touted to win the World Cup.

02:09:12.960 --> 02:09:17.960
[Guest 2]: The big team, Tendulkar, John Wright saying that, you know, this is the team that will win the World Cup.

02:09:17.960 --> 02:09:22.960
[Guest 2]: And I'm sitting there and saying that, boss, I don't know about comedy.

02:09:22.960 --> 02:09:25.960
[Guest 2]: But what has got me into cricket is these impersonations.

02:09:25.960 --> 02:09:33.960
[Guest 2]: So I have to continue stand-up comedy in the way it is, because that is going to get me to this world, which I've always wanted to be part of.

02:09:33.960 --> 02:09:37.960
[Guest 2]: So when, you know, sometimes journalists ask me, what does comedy mean?

02:09:37.960 --> 02:09:39.960
[Guest 2]: I'm like, man, this happened.

02:09:39.960 --> 02:09:40.960
[Guest 2]: I had to go here.

02:09:40.960 --> 02:09:43.960
[Guest 2]: Then it continued because it had a financial model.

02:09:43.960 --> 02:09:44.960
[Guest 2]: I continued.

02:09:44.960 --> 02:09:48.960
[Guest 2]: And then a few amazing things happened.

02:09:48.960 --> 02:09:51.960
[Guest 2]: Tony Gregg called me and said, hi, how are you doing?

02:09:51.960 --> 02:09:52.960
[Guest 2]: Good, Tony Gregg.

02:09:52.960 --> 02:09:57.960
[Guest 2]: And I imitated him and my first episode was with Tony Gregg himself.

02:09:57.960 --> 02:09:58.960
[Amit Varma]: Wow.

02:09:58.960 --> 02:10:00.960
[Amit Varma]: Is it online somewhere?

02:10:00.960 --> 02:10:01.960
[Amit Varma]: I think it's online.

02:10:01.960 --> 02:10:07.960
[Guest 2]: And we were talking about Inzamam Ullah, who was in prime form during the World Cup.

02:10:07.960 --> 02:10:10.960
[Guest 2]: Please, please.

02:10:10.960 --> 02:10:16.960
[Guest 2]: So Inzamam, at that time, I always say that whatever may be the question, you had the same answer.

02:10:16.960 --> 02:10:17.960
[Guest 2]: It was like Azruddin, right?

02:10:17.960 --> 02:10:22.960
[Guest 2]: So Shastri would go, Azruddin, it's a great wicket out here.

02:10:22.960 --> 02:10:24.960
[Guest 2]: What did you, what was your strategy?

02:10:24.960 --> 02:10:25.960
[Guest 2]: Yeah, the boss played well, right?

02:10:25.960 --> 02:10:26.960
[Guest 2]: That's not important.

02:10:26.960 --> 02:10:28.960
[Guest 2]: But do you think the Duckworth Lewis will cover?

02:10:28.960 --> 02:10:29.960
[Guest 2]: Yeah, the boss played well, right?

02:10:29.960 --> 02:10:31.960
[Guest 2]: That's not important.

02:10:31.960 --> 02:10:34.960
[Guest 2]: But Azhar Sehwag at five, right?

02:10:34.960 --> 02:10:37.960
[Guest 2]: Will you do whatever same?

02:10:37.960 --> 02:10:39.960
[Guest 2]: And Inzamam was exactly the same.

02:10:39.960 --> 02:10:43.960
[Guest 2]: Inzi, Razak is your key bowler.

02:10:43.960 --> 02:10:47.960
[Guest 2]: Thank God, the boys are working hard.

02:10:47.960 --> 02:10:49.960
[Guest 2]: The boys didn't get disheartened.

02:10:49.960 --> 02:10:52.960
[Guest 2]: But Inzamam Afridi is your key weapon.

02:10:52.960 --> 02:10:54.960
[Guest 2]: The boys are working hard.

02:10:54.960 --> 02:10:56.960
[Guest 2]: The boys didn't get disheartened.

02:10:56.960 --> 02:11:00.960
[Guest 2]: But if you can get Tendulkar out, the boys are working hard.

02:11:00.960 --> 02:11:02.960
[Unknown]: So he would not end.

02:11:02.960 --> 02:11:08.960
[Guest 2]: And we did an India Park review with Tony Gregg, where I am Inzamam and he is Tony Gregg.

02:11:08.960 --> 02:11:10.960
[Amit Varma]: This is a dream come true.

02:11:10.960 --> 02:11:13.960
[Unknown]: Is Tony Gregg's imitation of Tony Gregg as good as yours?

02:11:13.960 --> 02:11:18.960
[Guest 2]: That was his first reaction as well.

02:11:18.960 --> 02:11:19.960
[Guest 2]: That it was great.

02:11:19.960 --> 02:11:22.960
[Guest 2]: And then look at the thing, right?

02:11:22.960 --> 02:11:24.960
[Guest 2]: Next episode I'm doing with Ian Chappell.

02:11:24.960 --> 02:11:27.960
[Guest 2]: After that, I'm doing an episode with Michael Arthurton.

02:11:27.960 --> 02:11:30.960
[Guest 2]: Then I'm doing an episode with Nasir Hussain.

02:11:30.960 --> 02:11:33.960
[Guest 2]: Then I'm doing an episode with Tiger Pattodi.

02:11:33.960 --> 02:11:35.960
[Guest 2]: Then I'm doing an episode with Kapil Dev.

02:11:35.960 --> 02:11:37.960
[Guest 2]: This is like a dream come true.

02:11:37.960 --> 02:11:39.960
[Guest 2]: And I'm discussing cricket with them.

02:11:39.960 --> 02:11:40.960
[Guest 1]: Being paid for it.

02:11:40.960 --> 02:11:41.960
[Guest 2]: Paid for it.

02:11:41.960 --> 02:11:44.960
[Unknown]: More importantly, I'm not paid too much for that at that point of time.

02:11:44.960 --> 02:11:48.960
[Guest 2]: But what worked for me was my knowledge of the game.

02:11:48.960 --> 02:11:51.960
[Guest 2]: And that kind of, I could befriend anybody.

02:11:51.960 --> 02:11:55.960
[Guest 2]: And I remember having a conversation with Soha Ali Khan years later.

02:11:55.960 --> 02:11:59.960
[Guest 2]: And I told her that Tiger Pattodi had become a good friend of mine.

02:11:59.960 --> 02:12:00.960
[Guest 2]: And she said, impossible.

02:12:00.960 --> 02:12:02.960
[Guest 2]: My dad was a very private person.

02:12:02.960 --> 02:12:03.960
[Guest 2]: He would not befriend anybody.

02:12:03.960 --> 02:12:08.960
[Guest 2]: And I said, I'm really telling you, I spent the best two months of my life chatting cricket with him.

02:12:08.960 --> 02:12:11.960
[Guest 2]: And she said, no, impossible.

02:12:11.960 --> 02:12:12.960
[Guest 2]: He will not talk to you.

02:12:12.960 --> 02:12:14.960
[Guest 2]: I said, I'll tell you the story.

02:12:14.960 --> 02:12:20.960
[Guest 2]: Second day, I'm there and Tiger Pattodi calls me and says that,

02:12:20.960 --> 02:12:23.960
[Guest 2]: after I'd done an imitation of Jeffrey Boycott, he said, can you do that again?

02:12:23.960 --> 02:12:28.960
[Guest 2]: And I said, I'll tell you Tiger Pattodi, absolute legend of the game.

02:12:28.960 --> 02:12:30.960
[Guest 2]: And he started laughing.

02:12:30.960 --> 02:12:33.960
[Guest 2]: And from that day onwards, I became his best friend.

02:12:33.960 --> 02:12:41.960
[Guest 2]: That same evening, Vikram Sathe, Tiger Pattodi, Kapil Dev having a glass of wine, discussing Tiger's career.

02:12:41.960 --> 02:12:43.960
[Guest 2]: Can it be bigger than this for me?

02:12:43.960 --> 02:12:47.960
[Guest 2]: Who has not even been close to the world of cricket so far.

02:12:47.960 --> 02:12:53.960
[Guest 2]: And now, and joined by Ian Chappell and they're talking about those times and the Ashes and the Kerry Packer.

02:12:53.960 --> 02:12:57.960
[Guest 2]: And I was like, boss, pinch me because this is like big stuff.

02:12:57.960 --> 02:13:03.960
[Guest 2]: And that when I came back after the Centurion game, I said, that's it, brother.

02:13:03.960 --> 02:13:05.960
[Guest 2]: This is what you want to do in your life.

02:13:05.960 --> 02:13:09.960
[Guest 2]: Till the time you can extend and do what you can around this world.

02:13:09.960 --> 02:13:11.960
[Guest 2]: I think that will be life.

02:13:11.960 --> 02:13:13.960
[Guest 2]: And that I came back.

02:13:13.960 --> 02:13:14.960
[Guest 2]: I gave my resignation.

02:13:14.960 --> 02:13:17.960
[Guest 2]: Thankfully, I was called by the Sri Lanka Cricket Board.

02:13:17.960 --> 02:13:18.960
[Guest 2]: Oh, very funny story.

02:13:18.960 --> 02:13:21.960
[Guest 2]: 2004 Sri Lanka Cricket Board.

02:13:21.960 --> 02:13:28.960
[Guest 2]: I get called to do a stand up in the India versus, sorry, India, Pakistan and Bangladesh.

02:13:28.960 --> 02:13:30.960
[Guest 2]: For playing that Asia Cup.

02:13:30.960 --> 02:13:36.960
[Guest 2]: I was told that except for president, I think Kumar Tunga was the president of Sri Lanka at that time.

02:13:36.960 --> 02:13:39.960
[Guest 2]: I said, apart from that, you can imitate anybody in Sri Lanka.

02:13:39.960 --> 02:13:42.960
[Guest 2]: And otherwise, we'll throw you back from the airport.

02:13:42.960 --> 02:13:44.960
[Guest 2]: So I went for the Asia Cup.

02:13:44.960 --> 02:13:46.960
[Guest 2]: I think 2004, 2005.

02:13:46.960 --> 02:13:47.960
[Guest 2]: I don't remember.

02:13:47.960 --> 02:13:51.960
[Guest 2]: And that's the first time I got friendly with Tendulkar.

02:13:51.960 --> 02:13:55.960
[Guest 2]: And I called Sameer Dighe and told him that, you know, I'm doing this act in Sri Lanka.

02:13:55.960 --> 02:13:56.960
[Guest 2]: Just tell Sachin.

02:13:56.960 --> 02:13:58.960
[Guest 2]: He said, don't need to tell Sachin anything.

02:13:58.960 --> 02:14:01.960
[Guest 2]: You go and chat with him before the show and tell him that you know me.

02:14:01.960 --> 02:14:02.960
[Guest 2]: Blah, blah.

02:14:02.960 --> 02:14:05.960
[Guest 2]: He's anyway seen you at the Seattle Awards a little bit.

02:14:05.960 --> 02:14:07.960
[Guest 2]: He'll be fine.

02:14:07.960 --> 02:14:13.960
[Guest 2]: I land there and I go to Sachin at the show and say, Sachin, I'm going to imitate a little bit.

02:14:13.960 --> 02:14:14.960
[Guest 2]: He said, what are you going to do?

02:14:14.960 --> 02:14:16.960
[Guest 2]: I've seen you for five minutes.

02:14:16.960 --> 02:14:17.960
[Guest 2]: That's okay.

02:14:17.960 --> 02:14:18.960
[Guest 2]: No problem.

02:14:18.960 --> 02:14:22.960
[Guest 2]: And I do a 20-minute act there, 20-25 minutes.

02:14:22.960 --> 02:14:28.960
[Guest 2]: I mean, to see the Indian team, Pakistani team, Bangladeshi team, Sri Lankan team, sorry,

02:14:28.960 --> 02:14:30.960
[Guest 2]: enjoying and stuff like that.

02:14:30.960 --> 02:14:32.960
[Guest 2]: I said, boss, it's just getting reinforced.

02:14:32.960 --> 02:14:34.960
[Guest 2]: And then I am walking outside.

02:14:34.960 --> 02:14:37.960
[Guest 2]: I did the Imsamam imitation in front of Imsamam.

02:14:37.960 --> 02:14:44.960
[Guest 2]: So I remember walking out of the banquet area and suddenly I bump into Imsamam.

02:14:44.960 --> 02:14:48.960
[Guest 2]: And I think it was Yasir Hameed, if I'm not mistaken, the opening batsman of Pakistan.

02:14:48.960 --> 02:14:51.960
[Guest 2]: And Imsamam comes and looks at me.

02:14:51.960 --> 02:14:54.960
[Guest 2]: It's fun to take off your pants in front of everyone.

02:14:54.960 --> 02:15:00.960
[Guest 2]: And I said, what an evening.

02:15:00.960 --> 02:15:03.960
[Guest 2]: And next day I was to fly back to India.

02:15:03.960 --> 02:15:09.960
[Guest 2]: I was at the breakfast table and Sachin Yuvraj Singh and Harbhajan Singh were sitting out there.

02:15:09.960 --> 02:15:14.960
[Guest 2]: And that was my first taste of a cricket story, you know,

02:15:14.960 --> 02:15:18.960
[Guest 2]: and that's what I realized that this is what I want to experience all my life.

02:15:18.960 --> 02:15:20.960
[Guest 2]: This comedy and all is okay, that will continue.

02:15:20.960 --> 02:15:24.960
[Guest 2]: And about the Sri Lanka wicket or something like that,

02:15:24.960 --> 02:15:30.960
[Guest 2]: I had this conversation and Sachin gave a five to eight minute explanation on how to play Murali Tharan.

02:15:30.960 --> 02:15:31.960
[Guest 2]: Wow.

02:15:31.960 --> 02:15:32.960
[Guest 2]: On that table.

02:15:32.960 --> 02:15:36.960
[Guest 2]: So I was asking him that, you know, how do you pick it and stuff like that.

02:15:36.960 --> 02:15:40.960
[Guest 2]: So the moment he realized that this was a relevant question.

02:15:40.960 --> 02:15:45.960
[Guest 2]: So I remember Yuvraj Singh saying, this is a cricket story, he will cook it.

02:15:45.960 --> 02:15:46.960
[Guest 2]: He said that.

02:15:46.960 --> 02:15:48.960
[Guest 2]: But he said something, something.

02:15:48.960 --> 02:15:51.960
[Guest 2]: And then Sachin said that, you know, you pick him from the arm, you'll be able to.

02:15:51.960 --> 02:15:57.960
[Guest 2]: And I realized that there was some chemistry brewing between somebody who you idolized

02:15:57.960 --> 02:16:01.960
[Guest 2]: and kind of became friends with later on.

02:16:01.960 --> 02:16:07.960
[Guest 2]: And that's when he knew that this is my kind of a guy and my friendship started with Tendulkar.

02:16:07.960 --> 02:16:14.960
[Guest 2]: And in that journey to discover a champion and a whole lot of champions all over,

02:16:14.960 --> 02:16:17.960
[Guest 2]: starting to tour with Sunandan, with me.

02:16:17.960 --> 02:16:23.960
[Guest 2]: And the big moment was obviously when I was part of the ESPN commentary team in 2006.

02:16:23.960 --> 02:16:27.960
[Guest 2]: So yeah, coming back from the 2004 Asia Cup performance,

02:16:27.960 --> 02:16:32.960
[Guest 2]: it got reinforced that boss, you're here to stay, it was my gateway to the world of cricket.

02:16:32.960 --> 02:16:35.960
[Guest 2]: Comedy was just one way to reach there.

02:16:35.960 --> 02:16:38.960
[Unknown]: Cricket was never a way to reach there.

02:16:38.960 --> 02:16:42.960
[Guest 2]: But yeah, at least making fun of cricketers and creating jokes around the game

02:16:42.960 --> 02:16:44.960
[Guest 2]: kind of made me go closer to the game.

02:16:44.960 --> 02:16:48.960
[Guest 2]: And that's when, you know, things started happening, corporate shows started happening

02:16:48.960 --> 02:16:52.960
[Guest 2]: and the big break happened, which was 2006 ESPN,

02:16:52.960 --> 02:16:55.960
[Guest 2]: when they called me to be part of the commentary box.

02:16:55.960 --> 02:17:00.960
[Guest 2]: Now, up until now, you have to understand that Harsha Bhogle is the only external person

02:17:00.960 --> 02:17:01.960
[Guest 2]: who's in the commentary box.

02:17:01.960 --> 02:17:05.960
[Guest 2]: Gautam Bhimani is doing picture stories, but he's still not in the commentary box.

02:17:05.960 --> 02:17:08.960
[Guest 2]: But I have been called to be in the commentary box,

02:17:08.960 --> 02:17:13.960
[Guest 2]: obviously with a view of making Test Cricket interesting in terms of, you know,

02:17:13.960 --> 02:17:15.960
[Guest 2]: what's happening with the broadcast.

02:17:15.960 --> 02:17:18.960
[Guest 2]: So though I was in the comm box for certain periods,

02:17:18.960 --> 02:17:21.960
[Guest 2]: I was mainly doing a show called T-Spot,

02:17:21.960 --> 02:17:25.960
[Guest 2]: which was in tea at the TA interval break along with Alan Wilkins.

02:17:25.960 --> 02:17:30.960
[Guest 2]: But I was in conversation with Waseem Akram during the game in between and so on and so forth.

02:17:30.960 --> 02:17:33.960
[Guest 2]: And Gavaskar and Shastri and Harsha and all of that.

02:17:33.960 --> 02:17:38.960
[Guest 2]: That was a big, big break for me because I thought that now they are kind of accepting me

02:17:38.960 --> 02:17:41.960
[Guest 2]: as somebody who understands the game beyond the comedy.

02:17:41.960 --> 02:17:42.960
[Guest 2]: And this is 2006.

02:17:42.960 --> 02:17:47.960
[Guest 2]: So two years of active comedy had already happened.

02:17:47.960 --> 02:17:52.960
[Guest 2]: And so looking forward to going to South Africa, three test match series.

02:17:52.960 --> 02:17:54.960
[Guest 2]: There was a chance everybody was saying that,

02:17:54.960 --> 02:17:57.960
[Guest 2]: hey, there's a good chance that India will beat South Africa in South Africa.

02:17:57.960 --> 02:17:59.960
[Guest 2]: So there was this buzz in the commentary box.

02:17:59.960 --> 02:18:02.960
[Guest 2]: And it so happened that we reached there.

02:18:02.960 --> 02:18:05.960
[Guest 2]: Indian team was in good spirits and we won the first test match.

02:18:05.960 --> 02:18:07.960
[Guest 2]: If you remember, that was that big test.

02:18:07.960 --> 02:18:11.960
[Guest 2]: And we thought that from there on, things will go good for us, which didn't happen.

02:18:11.960 --> 02:18:16.960
[Guest 2]: Now I am there. I'm doing my stuff, slowly getting popularity.

02:18:16.960 --> 02:18:20.960
[Guest 2]: Because see, at the end of the day, cricket experts are a lot.

02:18:20.960 --> 02:18:25.960
[Guest 2]: But when you add humor to it, suddenly there's this vibe in the box and the broadcast,

02:18:25.960 --> 02:18:28.960
[Guest 2]: which everybody is enjoying and stuff like that.

02:18:28.960 --> 02:18:35.960
[Guest 2]: But one incident happened there that kind of put me off commentary forever.

02:18:35.960 --> 02:18:38.960
[Guest 2]: And that was during, I think, the second test match.

02:18:38.960 --> 02:18:41.960
[Guest 2]: I don't remember whether it was at Durban or was it the first test match.

02:18:41.960 --> 02:18:47.960
[Guest 2]: I think the last day of the first test match, where I was doing a small piece on the ground,

02:18:47.960 --> 02:18:52.960
[Guest 2]: near the pitch, which was kind of a humorous take on the first test match.

02:18:52.960 --> 02:18:58.960
[Guest 2]: And I was wearing India colors because I'd been told when I was going to South Africa by the Sony team.

02:18:58.960 --> 02:19:02.960
[Guest 2]: I mean, I was lucky to go to South Africa because earlier they wanted to shoot everything here.

02:19:02.960 --> 02:19:06.960
[Guest 2]: But because there was paucity of time, I finally got to come to South Africa.

02:19:06.960 --> 02:19:10.960
[Guest 2]: And I got these clothes from the Nike shop, which was the Indian attire.

02:19:10.960 --> 02:19:14.960
[Guest 2]: And by that time, that big deal with Nike had happened with the BCCI.

02:19:14.960 --> 02:19:16.960
[Guest 2]: So I wore that outfit.

02:19:16.960 --> 02:19:24.960
[Guest 2]: I went into the middle of the pitch and I was just about to record and walk in Sunil Gavaskar.

02:19:24.960 --> 02:19:27.960
[Guest 2]: And he says, why are you wearing these colors?

02:19:27.960 --> 02:19:33.960
[Guest 2]: So I got a shock of my life that in front of the entire crew and all these guys shouting at me.

02:19:33.960 --> 02:19:42.960
[Guest 2]: And I was 29-30, so I just stopped for a moment, but I didn't say anything to him.

02:19:42.960 --> 02:19:45.960
[Guest 2]: He continued, you've not played test cricket for India.

02:19:45.960 --> 02:19:47.960
[Guest 2]: Why are you wearing the India colors?

02:19:47.960 --> 02:19:50.960
[Guest 2]: And this is just ridiculous what this has come to.

02:19:50.960 --> 02:19:55.960
[Guest 2]: Test match cricket has certain value and started giving me a lecture on the ground in front of everybody.

02:19:55.960 --> 02:20:01.960
[Guest 2]: Now, I am thinking this is an official merchandise that I've picked up from a Nike showroom.

02:20:01.960 --> 02:20:03.960
[Amit Varma]: Anybody can wear it.

02:20:03.960 --> 02:20:04.960
[Amit Varma]: Exactly.

02:20:04.960 --> 02:20:09.960
[Guest 2]: So the producer is there and I'm asking him that, what is the story?

02:20:09.960 --> 02:20:13.960
[Guest 2]: Suddenly I see Harsha Bhogle walk and Ravi Shastri walk close and say that,

02:20:13.960 --> 02:20:15.960
[Guest 2]: Sunny bhai, this is available in the shop.

02:20:15.960 --> 02:20:17.960
[Guest 2]: This is a Nike deal.

02:20:17.960 --> 02:20:19.960
[Guest 2]: Anybody in the audience can wear it also.

02:20:19.960 --> 02:20:26.960
[Guest 2]: No, no, this is just, you know, you test cricket is for pride and some shit he gave me for 20 seconds.

02:20:26.960 --> 02:20:28.960
[Guest 2]: I kept quiet.

02:20:28.960 --> 02:20:30.960
[Guest 2]: Did that episode a little bit.

02:20:30.960 --> 02:20:34.960
[Guest 2]: Now, that's when I realized that this guy is extremely moody.

02:20:34.960 --> 02:20:37.960
[Guest 2]: I walk up to the commentary box.

02:20:37.960 --> 02:20:41.960
[Guest 2]: I tell the producer that, you know, this is not something I'll appreciate.

02:20:41.960 --> 02:20:46.960
[Guest 2]: But he said, nahi yaar, moody aadmi hai, don't get upset and stuff like that.

02:20:46.960 --> 02:20:56.960
[Guest 2]: That same evening, if I'm not mistaken, was a small episode that I had to do with Gavaskar only along with Wasim Akram and Alan Wilkins.

02:20:56.960 --> 02:21:01.960
[Guest 2]: So at that point of time, there was this thing about wives and girlfriends coming to cricket tournaments.

02:21:01.960 --> 02:21:07.960
[Guest 2]: So when Alan asked me this question in that segment in On Tee Spot, I said that this is a question I cannot answer.

02:21:07.960 --> 02:21:10.960
[Guest 2]: I think I'll leave it to Wasim bhai and Sunny bhai.

02:21:10.960 --> 02:21:13.960
[Guest 2]: I don't know what Sunny bhai thought.

02:21:13.960 --> 02:21:16.960
[Guest 2]: He gave the answer and then he threw a big tantrum after that.

02:21:16.960 --> 02:21:19.960
[Unknown]: This is not right. Who are these people?

02:21:19.960 --> 02:21:22.960
[Guest 2]: And remember, I have worked with this guy in professional management group in my first job.

02:21:22.960 --> 02:21:24.960
[Guest 2]: So he knows me.

02:21:24.960 --> 02:21:28.960
[Guest 2]: And he started behaving so I went and said, Sunny bhai, did I say something wrong?

02:21:28.960 --> 02:21:30.960
[Guest 2]: I'll apologize and all of that.

02:21:30.960 --> 02:21:33.960
[Guest 2]: And then he said he didn't acknowledge me and he just walked away.

02:21:33.960 --> 02:21:37.960
[Guest 2]: That's when I went to the producer and I said, listen, give me my ticket back.

02:21:37.960 --> 02:21:40.960
[Guest 2]: I'm not going to take this shit anymore.

02:21:40.960 --> 02:21:42.960
[Guest 2]: I never wanted to be a broadcaster.

02:21:42.960 --> 02:21:45.960
[Guest 2]: You got me into broadcasting. I'm here to entertain.

02:21:45.960 --> 02:21:47.960
[Guest 2]: I will do a stand up act for your guests and whatever.

02:21:47.960 --> 02:21:49.960
[Guest 2]: But this is the behavior I will not tolerate.

02:21:49.960 --> 02:21:51.960
[Guest 2]: And the worst thing is he's my hero.

02:21:51.960 --> 02:21:54.960
[Guest 2]: I mean, we've idolized this guy.

02:21:54.960 --> 02:21:57.960
[Guest 2]: And he said, nahi yaar, wo aisa hi hai, yeh, wo, yeh, wo karke.

02:21:57.960 --> 02:22:00.960
[Guest 2]: But I said, chalo, theek hai, maan jate hain.

02:22:00.960 --> 02:22:02.960
[Guest 2]: So second test match, I had a good time.

02:22:02.960 --> 02:22:04.960
[Guest 2]: Third test match, we unfortunately kept down, we lost.

02:22:04.960 --> 02:22:07.960
[Guest 2]: But there were some good innings, great cricket to watch.

02:22:07.960 --> 02:22:14.960
[Guest 2]: But the baggage was still there because he was behaving very rudely.

02:22:14.960 --> 02:22:15.960
[Unknown]: Throughout?

02:22:15.960 --> 02:22:18.960
[Guest 2]: Throughout. Means he was not acknowledging me only.

02:22:18.960 --> 02:22:21.960
[Guest 2]: And then that day, I decided on my flight back.

02:22:21.960 --> 02:22:24.960
[Guest 2]: And interestingly, on the flight back, just before the flight,

02:22:24.960 --> 02:22:29.960
[Guest 2]: when I was driving to the airport, I got stopped by cops.

02:22:29.960 --> 02:22:35.960
[Guest 2]: And this is like, you know, I'm an ICC, whatever, ESPN commentator.

02:22:35.960 --> 02:22:39.960
[Guest 2]: They stopped me in the middle of the journey to the airport.

02:22:39.960 --> 02:22:42.960
[Guest 2]: And those two cops looked at me and said, you know, open, open, open.

02:22:42.960 --> 02:22:44.960
[Guest 2]: Drugs, drugs, drugs.

02:22:44.960 --> 02:22:46.960
[Guest 2]: And I'm like, what is wrong?

02:22:46.960 --> 02:22:48.960
[Guest 2]: And they're like, I'm going to the airport to catch my flight.

02:22:48.960 --> 02:22:51.960
[Guest 2]: And they take all of the money out of my wallet.

02:22:51.960 --> 02:22:53.960
[Guest 2]: And say that, you know, you go like this.

02:22:53.960 --> 02:22:57.960
[Guest 2]: These are cops doing it to a commentator in South Africa.

02:22:57.960 --> 02:22:59.960
[Guest 2]: Going, somebody going to the airport.

02:22:59.960 --> 02:23:02.960
[Guest 2]: Itna open pagalpan chal raha tha uss time.

02:23:02.960 --> 02:23:06.960
[Guest 2]: Anyway, airport mein main gaya, flight pe baitha.

02:23:06.960 --> 02:23:11.960
[Guest 2]: Aur maine kaha ki, broadcasting ke nazdeek, life mein kabhi nahi aane ka.

02:23:11.960 --> 02:23:17.960
[Guest 2]: Because what I had seen, Amit, was that Harsha had gone through all of this for a long time.

02:23:17.960 --> 02:23:21.960
[Guest 2]: But Harsha is obsessed by cricket and commentary.

02:23:21.960 --> 02:23:23.960
[Guest 2]: He can't do anything else.

02:23:23.960 --> 02:23:25.960
[Guest 2]: So he did not have the option that I had.

02:23:25.960 --> 02:23:28.960
[Guest 2]: Where I said, boss, yeh mereko yeh click ke nazdeek aane ka hi nahi.

02:23:28.960 --> 02:23:32.960
[Guest 2]: Because they will not accept anybody from the outside.

02:23:32.960 --> 02:23:34.960
[Guest 2]: It's not, means they're insecure.

02:23:34.960 --> 02:23:38.960
[Guest 2]: And specially Sunny bhai was insecure about any, that's what I thought.

02:23:38.960 --> 02:23:41.960
[Guest 2]: What was I going to do to Sunny Gavaskar?

02:23:41.960 --> 02:23:42.960
[Guest 2]: He's a living legend.

02:23:42.960 --> 02:23:45.960
[Guest 2]: And why am I going to do anything that is going to affect him?

02:23:45.960 --> 02:23:49.960
[Guest 2]: But then I realized that this is how it's going to be in commentary.

02:23:49.960 --> 02:23:53.960
[Guest 2]: If you are able to, and Harsha has taken all of this stress and the insults

02:23:53.960 --> 02:23:57.960
[Guest 2]: over a period of 24, 30, 40 years or whatever he's done broadcasting.

02:23:57.960 --> 02:23:58.960
[Guest 2]: But he knows this is his calling.

02:23:58.960 --> 02:24:00.960
[Guest 2]: There's nothing else I'll do.

02:24:00.960 --> 02:24:01.960
[Guest 2]: And therefore he did that.

02:24:01.960 --> 02:24:03.960
[Guest 2]: I said, I'm not going to do it.

02:24:03.960 --> 02:24:07.960
[Guest 2]: I came back and I'd heard that a lot of things happened in ESPN after that.

02:24:07.960 --> 02:24:12.960
[Guest 2]: I said, boss, stand up comedy karenge and I'll create my own ecosystem of content,

02:24:12.960 --> 02:24:15.960
[Guest 2]: which I will do on live shows.

02:24:15.960 --> 02:24:18.960
[Guest 2]: Luckily, YouTube had just started.

02:24:18.960 --> 02:24:24.960
[Guest 2]: So that clip of Seat Awards now was the first comedy clip on YouTube to go viral.

02:24:24.960 --> 02:24:27.960
[Guest 2]: So everybody knew what I was doing.

02:24:27.960 --> 02:24:32.960
[Guest 2]: And therefore I said that any content that comes, which is apart from broadcasting,

02:24:32.960 --> 02:24:33.960
[Guest 2]: I will do on cricket.

02:24:33.960 --> 02:24:36.960
[Guest 2]: And hopefully at some point of time, create my own content on YouTube.

02:24:36.960 --> 02:24:41.960
[Guest 2]: And I will leave this game from that point of view, because I realized that this is

02:24:41.960 --> 02:24:45.960
[Guest 2]: the only country where the board decides who the commentator is.

02:24:45.960 --> 02:24:47.960
[Guest 2]: It's not the broadcaster's prerogative.

02:24:47.960 --> 02:24:51.960
[Guest 2]: And these guys are not going to accept any outsider coming and stuff like that.

02:24:51.960 --> 02:24:52.960
[Guest 2]: And that's what changed my life.

02:24:52.960 --> 02:24:55.960
[Guest 2]: And I'm very happy that I didn't stay in broadcasting because I would not have

02:24:55.960 --> 02:25:00.960
[Guest 2]: been able to live this under pressure kind of life.

02:25:00.960 --> 02:25:02.960
[Guest 2]: Came back home.

02:25:02.960 --> 02:25:03.960
[Guest 2]: Thankfully, the corporate boom.

02:25:03.960 --> 02:25:10.960
[Guest 2]: And that was that period of great fun because every corporate was taking their

02:25:10.960 --> 02:25:15.960
[Guest 2]: dealers and listing employees to South Africa, to Greece.

02:25:15.960 --> 02:25:20.960
[Guest 2]: So with that 2007-12 period, I probably would have done hundreds and thousands of

02:25:20.960 --> 02:25:25.960
[Guest 2]: shows, 200-300 shows, just traveling abroad with 500 dealers.

02:25:25.960 --> 02:25:27.960
[Guest 2]: And sometimes I do it in my jokes.

02:25:27.960 --> 02:25:33.960
[Guest 2]: And I think that's to say that Gujarat became more vibrant, not because of the

02:25:33.960 --> 02:25:36.960
[Guest 2]: chief minister there, but because of Bangkok.

02:25:36.960 --> 02:25:42.960
[Guest 2]: Because all sales targets were dependent on going to Bangkok.

02:25:42.960 --> 02:25:47.960
[Guest 2]: And if you did well, and Gujaratis who had never gone beyond Bhavsar and Nadiad,

02:25:47.960 --> 02:25:49.960
[Guest 2]: they went to Bangkok and they were happy.

02:25:49.960 --> 02:25:50.960
[Guest 2]: They doubled their turnover.

02:25:50.960 --> 02:25:53.960
[Guest 2]: And sometimes I feel that we revived the Thailand economy.

02:25:53.960 --> 02:25:55.960
[Unknown]: They turned over and they turned over.

02:25:55.960 --> 02:25:58.960
[Unknown]: It was a family show.

02:25:58.960 --> 02:26:02.960
[Guest 2]: But Amit, you will not believe and Roshan will agree to this.

02:26:02.960 --> 02:26:07.960
[Unknown]: Every weekend we were in Bangkok because every corporate did gigs only in Bangkok.

02:26:07.960 --> 02:26:12.960
[Guest 2]: Thailand hates India because the kind of rada that Indian dealers have done in

02:26:12.960 --> 02:26:14.960
[Guest 1]: Bangkok is unbelievable.

02:26:14.960 --> 02:26:16.960
[Guest 1]: I'll just tell you one small incident.

02:26:16.960 --> 02:26:19.960
[Guest 1]: We're doing one event together.

02:26:19.960 --> 02:26:24.960
[Guest 1]: And this is for a erstwhile computer company.

02:26:24.960 --> 02:26:25.960
[Guest 1]: And we've done the thing and whatever.

02:26:25.960 --> 02:26:26.960
[Guest 1]: And the show's gone very well.

02:26:26.960 --> 02:26:27.960
[Guest 1]: Award night has happened.

02:26:27.960 --> 02:26:29.960
[Guest 1]: We guys are back at the hotel.

02:26:29.960 --> 02:26:34.960
[Guest 1]: And the marketing director of the company is a good friend of ours.

02:26:34.960 --> 02:26:35.960
[Guest 1]: And she's very happy.

02:26:35.960 --> 02:26:37.960
[Guest 1]: Everything's gone well.

02:26:37.960 --> 02:26:40.960
[Guest 1]: Now all these dealers after the show have gone to town.

02:26:40.960 --> 02:26:42.960
[Guest 1]: And they've come back with people.

02:26:42.960 --> 02:26:45.960
[Guest 1]: And as they're entering the hotel or whatever, suddenly they see that in the

02:26:45.960 --> 02:26:49.960
[Guest 1]: lobby is standing the marketing director and we all are behind.

02:26:49.960 --> 02:26:51.960
[Guest 1]: Now they have told all the women to buzz off.

02:26:51.960 --> 02:26:53.960
[Guest 1]: And they've entered the lobby.

02:26:53.960 --> 02:26:55.960
[Guest 1]: And these girls are holding their passports saying, I'm clean.

02:26:55.960 --> 02:26:56.960
[Guest 1]: I'm clean.

02:26:56.960 --> 02:26:58.960
[Guest 1]: I can come to your room.

02:26:58.960 --> 02:27:00.960
[Unknown]: And they're saying, no, no.

02:27:00.960 --> 02:27:01.960
[Unknown]: Madam.

02:27:01.960 --> 02:27:02.960
[Unknown]: Sister.

02:27:02.960 --> 02:27:03.960
[Unknown]: Madam.

02:27:03.960 --> 02:27:04.960
[Unknown]: Sister, madam.

02:27:04.960 --> 02:27:05.960
[Unknown]: Sister, madam.

02:27:05.960 --> 02:27:07.960
[Guest 1]: I mean, you've seen so many of these scenes.

02:27:07.960 --> 02:27:08.960
[Guest 1]: It's crazy.

02:27:08.960 --> 02:27:12.960
[Guest 1]: People would, you know, some dealers would shoplift.

02:27:12.960 --> 02:27:13.960
[Unknown]: They would do.

02:27:13.960 --> 02:27:14.960
[Guest 1]: People would because, you know.

02:27:14.960 --> 02:27:16.960
[Unknown]: They picked her up.

02:27:16.960 --> 02:27:17.960
[Guest 1]: They picked her up.

02:27:17.960 --> 02:27:19.960
[Guest 1]: I mean, they're stopping her.

02:27:19.960 --> 02:27:20.960
[Guest 1]: They're saving her from arrest.

02:27:20.960 --> 02:27:21.960
[Guest 2]: What a story.

02:27:21.960 --> 02:27:22.960
[Unknown]: No, no.

02:27:22.960 --> 02:27:25.960
[Guest 1]: Indians had not traveled abroad to that extent.

02:27:25.960 --> 02:27:28.960
[Guest 2]: And now all these companies were taking, which is good for us, right?

02:27:28.960 --> 02:27:30.960
[Guest 2]: Because we were entertaining these people abroad.

02:27:30.960 --> 02:27:36.960
[Guest 2]: But many of the stories were, they did not know how to use an Indian.

02:27:36.960 --> 02:27:37.960
[Guest 2]: Sorry.

02:27:37.960 --> 02:27:38.960
[Guest 1]: Western toilet.

02:27:38.960 --> 02:27:39.960
[Guest 1]: Western toilet.

02:27:39.960 --> 02:27:45.960
[Guest 2]: And they would do things on that toilet which had to be sorted by the company

02:27:45.960 --> 02:27:47.960
[Guest 2]: heads before they had exited the hotel.

02:27:47.960 --> 02:27:49.960
[Guest 2]: It was a chaotic time.

02:27:49.960 --> 02:27:51.960
[Amit Varma]: What would they do in the toilets?

02:27:51.960 --> 02:27:54.960
[Guest 1]: Just let your imagination wander.

02:27:54.960 --> 02:27:55.960
[Guest 1]: No, no.

02:27:55.960 --> 02:27:56.960
[Guest 1]: Not just that.

02:27:56.960 --> 02:27:57.960
[Guest 1]: I'm telling you.

02:27:57.960 --> 02:28:02.960
[Guest 1]: So, occasionally when people used to go through security check and they had to open their bags,

02:28:02.960 --> 02:28:07.960
[Guest 1]: they would have bath towels, bathrobes, soaps.

02:28:07.960 --> 02:28:11.960
[Guest 1]: Someone even carried the safe from the hotel.

02:28:11.960 --> 02:28:13.960
[Unknown]: It was crazy.

02:28:13.960 --> 02:28:15.960
[Unknown]: Sir, was it in the room?

02:28:15.960 --> 02:28:17.960
[Unknown]: It was in the room.

02:28:17.960 --> 02:28:19.960
[Unknown]: They've taken everything from the room.

02:28:19.960 --> 02:28:20.960
[Unknown]: Oh, my God.

02:28:20.960 --> 02:28:22.960
[Guest 2]: But it was crazy.

02:28:22.960 --> 02:28:23.960
[Guest 2]: Cruises, performing.

02:28:23.960 --> 02:28:30.960
[Guest 2]: And you know, we were always, the fillers were always just before the item number performed.

02:28:30.960 --> 02:28:35.960
[Guest 2]: So all the actresses or whatever, it was called item number show.

02:28:35.960 --> 02:28:39.960
[Guest 2]: And after the stand-up comedy would come the item number.

02:28:39.960 --> 02:28:42.960
[Guest 2]: And so I was always in trouble.

02:28:42.960 --> 02:28:46.960
[Guest 2]: Because dealers, internal audience, they would still listen to humor and all of that.

02:28:46.960 --> 02:28:50.960
[Unknown]: But the dealers would want the item number to come.

02:28:50.960 --> 02:28:54.960
[Guest 2]: So for that 20 minutes for me in between, I was the big wall between them.

02:28:54.960 --> 02:28:59.960
[Guest 2]: But still I managed to do 3,000 shows, which shows how hot I am.

02:28:59.960 --> 02:29:00.960
[Amit Varma]: 3,000 shows?

02:29:00.960 --> 02:29:01.960
[Amit Varma]: Yeah.

02:29:01.960 --> 02:29:02.960
[Amit Varma]: My God.

02:29:02.960 --> 02:29:04.960
[Guest 2]: So that was a fun journey.

02:29:04.960 --> 02:29:09.960
[Guest 2]: But this is where my intellectual part of the story started.

02:29:09.960 --> 02:29:11.960
[Guest 2]: The touring was going on.

02:29:11.960 --> 02:29:16.960
[Guest 2]: So because I had befriended the cricketers by now, in the middle of a tour,

02:29:16.960 --> 02:29:23.960
[Guest 2]: having a nice meal or dinner with, say, Rahul Dravid, or for that matter, Asaurav Ganguly,

02:29:23.960 --> 02:29:30.960
[Guest 2]: maybe sometimes members from the opposition team who had seen me perform in probably an ICC cricket event somewhere.

02:29:30.960 --> 02:29:34.960
[Guest 2]: This was where my actual journey started.

02:29:34.960 --> 02:29:38.960
[Guest 2]: To live international sport at the time when the action is happening.

02:29:38.960 --> 02:29:43.960
[Guest 2]: So when you know the next session for the test match is interesting,

02:29:43.960 --> 02:29:46.960
[Guest 2]: and you've had dinner with, say, Anil Kumble the night before,

02:29:46.960 --> 02:29:50.960
[Guest 2]: because you bumped into him in some Indian restaurant,

02:29:50.960 --> 02:29:52.960
[Guest 2]: and then he's kind of sharing the dynamics.

02:29:52.960 --> 02:29:59.960
[Guest 2]: That's when the games kind of started opening up for me,

02:29:59.960 --> 02:30:02.960
[Guest 2]: where I started understanding the psychology of sport,

02:30:02.960 --> 02:30:07.960
[Guest 2]: the physicality of sport, the human behavior side of it,

02:30:07.960 --> 02:30:11.960
[Guest 2]: the competitive advantage that people get out of sledging.

02:30:11.960 --> 02:30:13.960
[Guest 2]: What is purposeful practice?

02:30:13.960 --> 02:30:15.960
[Guest 2]: What is team dynamics?

02:30:15.960 --> 02:30:18.960
[Guest 2]: What is advantage during sessions?

02:30:18.960 --> 02:30:20.960
[Guest 2]: What is mental makeup?

02:30:20.960 --> 02:30:21.960
[Guest 2]: What is routine?

02:30:21.960 --> 02:30:23.960
[Guest 2]: What is visualization?

02:30:23.960 --> 02:30:27.960
[Guest 2]: So this started getting easier and easier for me to understand,

02:30:27.960 --> 02:30:31.960
[Guest 2]: because I was hearing it from the horse's mouth at the time when the action was happening.

02:30:31.960 --> 02:30:37.960
[Guest 2]: So 2006 onwards to 2013 till Sachin retired,

02:30:37.960 --> 02:30:41.960
[Guest 2]: that seven years I lived cricket in its totality.

02:30:41.960 --> 02:30:45.960
[Guest 2]: Because even before the Sydney Gate happened,

02:30:45.960 --> 02:30:48.960
[Guest 2]: or after the Sydney Gate happened, I was in that press conference,

02:30:48.960 --> 02:30:51.960
[Guest 2]: what Robak was writing about Ricky Ponting,

02:30:51.960 --> 02:30:54.960
[Guest 2]: my interaction with Ricky Ponting during that particular tour.

02:30:54.960 --> 02:30:57.960
[Guest 2]: So this was like gold dust coming to me and saying,

02:30:57.960 --> 02:31:00.960
[Guest 2]: forget the comedy, this is what you've been waiting for.

02:31:00.960 --> 02:31:03.960
[Guest 2]: And that was the reason that book happened,

02:31:03.960 --> 02:31:06.960
[Guest 2]: because I thought that, hey, I am privy to so many of these stories,

02:31:06.960 --> 02:31:11.960
[Guest 2]: real time, let me try and see if I can use humor and put it in a book format.

02:31:11.960 --> 02:31:15.960
[Guest 2]: That is where I got interested in sports psychology,

02:31:15.960 --> 02:31:19.960
[Guest 2]: where I said, boss, the dynamics of understanding human behavior

02:31:19.960 --> 02:31:23.960
[Guest 2]: in the context of high performance sport is the ultimate you can ever get.

02:31:23.960 --> 02:31:27.960
[Guest 2]: And cricket is a very amazing game because it has so many facets,

02:31:27.960 --> 02:31:30.960
[Guest 2]: unlike football where, you know, whatever,

02:31:30.960 --> 02:31:32.960
[Guest 2]: number of people playing for one and a half hours and it's over.

02:31:32.960 --> 02:31:35.960
[Guest 2]: There's a wicketkeeper who has his own story.

02:31:35.960 --> 02:31:38.960
[Guest 2]: There is a third man who has his own story.

02:31:38.960 --> 02:31:42.960
[Guest 2]: There is a spin bowler who's coming with a new ball who has his own story,

02:31:42.960 --> 02:31:44.960
[Guest 2]: which Ashwin beautifully explains in What The Duck,

02:31:44.960 --> 02:31:47.960
[Guest 2]: my show where he talks about, you know, Ajinkya Rahane giving him a new ball

02:31:47.960 --> 02:31:51.960
[Guest 2]: because he realized that there's moisture and spin might help him in Melbourne.

02:31:51.960 --> 02:31:53.960
[Guest 2]: And that's how he got Steve Smith out.

02:31:53.960 --> 02:31:58.960
[Guest 2]: So all these stories, imagine happening to you while the process is on,

02:31:58.960 --> 02:32:00.960
[Unknown]: was like, means I was learning and learning.

02:32:00.960 --> 02:32:02.960
[Guest 2]: I said, cricket is life.

02:32:02.960 --> 02:32:05.960
[Guest 2]: So many things are being taught to me through this wonderful game.

02:32:05.960 --> 02:32:07.960
[Guest 2]: And I was growing as a person.

02:32:07.960 --> 02:32:12.960
[Guest 2]: And I thought that cricket is actually the real subject I should have learned in school.

02:32:12.960 --> 02:32:14.960
[Guest 2]: And then the unraveling of Tendulkar.

02:32:14.960 --> 02:32:17.960
[Guest 2]: And I'm understanding why this happened.

02:32:17.960 --> 02:32:19.960
[Guest 2]: Attention to detail, the preparation.

02:32:19.960 --> 02:32:23.960
[Guest 2]: 2011, I remember Sachin Tendulkar was not in form.

02:32:23.960 --> 02:32:25.960
[Guest 2]: Rahul Dravid was getting bold to Hilfenhaus.

02:32:25.960 --> 02:32:30.960
[Guest 2]: Every test match that he played, we lost that series after winning,

02:32:30.960 --> 02:32:33.960
[Guest 2]: after losing a close game at Melbourne.

02:32:33.960 --> 02:32:36.960
[Guest 2]: I remember going with Sachin to a vineyard,

02:32:36.960 --> 02:32:39.960
[Guest 2]: and he explaining to me the dynamics of how we lost that test.

02:32:39.960 --> 02:32:44.960
[Guest 2]: And, you know, talking to Rahul about how his mental frame was extremely good

02:32:44.960 --> 02:32:45.960
[Guest 2]: during the Melbourne test.

02:32:45.960 --> 02:32:47.960
[Guest 2]: And after that, it started going down.

02:32:47.960 --> 02:32:49.960
[Guest 2]: This was a lesson in psychology.

02:32:49.960 --> 02:32:52.960
[Guest 2]: This was a lesson in human behavior,

02:32:52.960 --> 02:32:53.960
[Guest 2]: which I was just grasping.

02:32:53.960 --> 02:32:58.960
[Guest 2]: I said, hey, let me just continue my comedy till the time I can

02:32:58.960 --> 02:33:01.960
[Guest 2]: in order to get a sense of what is happening in the world.

02:33:01.960 --> 02:33:05.960
[Guest 2]: But I realized that my money was coming through corporate India.

02:33:05.960 --> 02:33:08.960
[Guest 2]: And that's when, as Roshan said, that the musical part of it,

02:33:08.960 --> 02:33:13.960
[Guest 2]: I started developing observations, politics, current affairs,

02:33:13.960 --> 02:33:17.960
[Guest 2]: all these things I started writing on my own so that my act would become more robust.

02:33:17.960 --> 02:33:19.960
[Guest 2]: Because at any given point of time,

02:33:19.960 --> 02:33:21.960
[Guest 2]: a stand-up comedian should have three hours of material.

02:33:21.960 --> 02:33:25.960
[Guest 2]: So your 20 minutes get repeated, which is your best,

02:33:25.960 --> 02:33:27.960
[Guest 2]: because you're safe,

02:33:27.960 --> 02:33:30.960
[Guest 2]: unless you know the audience is a little open with experimentation.

02:33:30.960 --> 02:33:32.960
[Guest 2]: Because unlike the comedy movement,

02:33:32.960 --> 02:33:37.960
[Guest 2]: which started with say Veer Das and Papa CJ sometime in 2008-9,

02:33:37.960 --> 02:33:40.960
[Guest 2]: I had no concept of experimenting in a club,

02:33:40.960 --> 02:33:43.960
[Guest 2]: getting my material tested and doing it in a corporate show.

02:33:43.960 --> 02:33:46.960
[Guest 2]: All my testing was happening on real-time shows.

02:33:46.960 --> 02:33:49.960
[Guest 2]: So my risk-taking ability went down

02:33:49.960 --> 02:33:53.960
[Guest 2]: because I could not have risked material in an Asian paint show.

02:33:53.960 --> 02:33:57.960
[Guest 2]: So what I would do is make three to five minutes of new material.

02:33:57.960 --> 02:34:00.960
[Guest 2]: If I would go from Asian paints to Procter & Gamble,

02:34:00.960 --> 02:34:02.960
[Guest 2]: I would test this five minutes.

02:34:02.960 --> 02:34:07.960
[Guest 2]: From Procter & Gamble to ICICI, I would test another two minutes.

02:34:07.960 --> 02:34:11.960
[Guest 2]: But it took me six months to make 30 new minutes.

02:34:11.960 --> 02:34:13.960
[Guest 2]: Whereas if I was a club comedian,

02:34:13.960 --> 02:34:15.960
[Guest 2]: I would have tested material every day.

02:34:15.960 --> 02:34:17.960
[Guest 2]: But by the time this culture happened,

02:34:17.960 --> 02:34:19.960
[Guest 2]: I had already done 8-10 years of work.

02:34:19.960 --> 02:34:21.960
[Guest 2]: And then again, inertia had set in.

02:34:21.960 --> 02:34:23.960
[Guest 1]: And I was saying that I had bargained for comedy.

02:34:23.960 --> 02:34:25.960
[Guest 1]: It was input-output.

02:34:25.960 --> 02:34:27.960
[Guest 1]: I told him, why don't you do a TV special?

02:34:27.960 --> 02:34:31.960
[Guest 1]: He says, I will do the same joke 100 times in different corporate shows.

02:34:31.960 --> 02:34:33.960
[Guest 1]: It's new.

02:34:33.960 --> 02:34:35.960
[Guest 1]: Once I did it on TV, everyone heard it.

02:34:35.960 --> 02:34:37.960
[Guest 1]: And it's a philosophy.

02:34:37.960 --> 02:34:39.960
[Guest 1]: Because I work with Veer and Zakir and all these guys.

02:34:39.960 --> 02:34:41.960
[Guest 1]: And I see them.

02:34:41.960 --> 02:34:43.960
[Guest 1]: They will develop material for a year.

02:34:43.960 --> 02:34:45.960
[Guest 1]: They will test it.

02:34:45.960 --> 02:34:47.960
[Guest 1]: Possibly take another year to hone it.

02:34:47.960 --> 02:34:49.960
[Guest 1]: And it's got a two-year kind of cycle.

02:34:49.960 --> 02:34:51.960
[Guest 1]: At the end of the two years, they'll do a TV special.

02:34:51.960 --> 02:34:53.960
[Guest 1]: Then that material is over.

02:34:53.960 --> 02:34:55.960
[Guest 1]: And then it moves on to a new chunk or whatever.

02:34:55.960 --> 02:34:57.960
[Guest 2]: I really think Saty could have done that.

02:34:57.960 --> 02:34:59.960
[Guest 2]: But what happened was that this was not in my prime.

02:34:59.960 --> 02:35:01.960
[Unknown]: I had done my prime.

02:35:01.960 --> 02:35:03.960
[Guest 2]: And I was excited by this other thing.

02:35:03.960 --> 02:35:05.960
[Guest 2]: Then that comedy movement started.

02:35:05.960 --> 02:35:07.960
[Guest 2]: And Roshan used to tell me that

02:35:07.960 --> 02:35:09.960
[Guest 2]: Saty, you come in this zone.

02:35:09.960 --> 02:35:11.960
[Guest 2]: You are way ahead of them.

02:35:11.960 --> 02:35:13.960
[Guest 2]: I said, I am not in the game.

