[Amit Varma]: look at is that

03:28:45.960 --> 03:28:47.960
[Amit Varma]: if you think about the biggest

03:28:47.960 --> 03:28:49.960
[Amit Varma]: sort of endeavor that

03:28:49.960 --> 03:28:51.960
[Amit Varma]: human beings have embarked upon in the last

03:28:51.960 --> 03:28:53.960
[Amit Varma]: few hundred years. It is the

03:28:53.960 --> 03:28:55.960
[Amit Varma]: endeavor to mitigate

03:28:55.960 --> 03:28:57.960
[Amit Varma]: our programming with our culture.

03:28:57.960 --> 03:28:59.960
[Amit Varma]: We are the only species

03:28:59.960 --> 03:29:01.960
[Amit Varma]: which can actually reflect on our programming

03:29:01.960 --> 03:29:03.960
[Amit Varma]: by which I mean our genes that can

03:29:03.960 --> 03:29:05.960
[Amit Varma]: think about our instincts and say that

03:29:05.960 --> 03:29:07.960
[Amit Varma]: no this is wrong I won't do it. For example a choice

03:29:07.960 --> 03:29:09.960
[Amit Varma]: not to have kids is actually against

03:29:09.960 --> 03:29:11.960
[Amit Varma]: our programming. We are wired

03:29:11.960 --> 03:29:13.960
[Amit Varma]: at some levels to be tribalistic.

03:29:13.960 --> 03:29:15.960
[Amit Varma]: We are also wired for the opposite. We are also

03:29:15.960 --> 03:29:17.960
[Amit Varma]: wired to be altruistic. Now the point

03:29:17.960 --> 03:29:19.960
[Amit Varma]: is like I love Steven Pinker's

03:29:19.960 --> 03:29:21.960
