[Amit Varma]: more a life lesson that I think just comes

05:06:22.960 --> 05:06:24.960
[Amit Varma]: with growing older and not necessarily because

05:06:24.960 --> 05:06:26.960
[Amit Varma]: of the show.

05:06:26.960 --> 05:06:28.960
[Amit Varma]: But I've also learned,

05:06:28.960 --> 05:06:30.960
[Amit Varma]: over the last year, especially as I've done

05:06:30.960 --> 05:06:32.960
[Amit Varma]: these long oral history kind of

05:06:32.960 --> 05:06:34.960
[Amit Varma]: episodes, is that

05:06:34.960 --> 05:06:36.960
[Amit Varma]: what I really like best is the stories

05:06:36.960 --> 05:06:38.960
[Amit Varma]: of people. The stories that

05:06:38.960 --> 05:06:40.960
[Amit Varma]: people tell about themselves. And I find many

05:06:40.960 --> 05:06:42.960
[Amit Varma]: of my listeners will echo this and some won't.

05:06:42.960 --> 05:06:44.960
[Amit Varma]: Where, you know, my thing

05:06:44.960 --> 05:06:46.960
[Amit Varma]: is, if you want to listen to subject X

05:06:46.960 --> 05:06:48.960
[Amit Varma]: on... to person X

05:06:48.960 --> 05:06:50.960
[Unknown]: on subject Y, you can search

05:06:50.960 --> 05:06:52.960
[Amit Varma]: on YouTube. You'll find thousands.

05:06:52.960 --> 05:06:54.960
[Amit Varma]: But if you really want to understand

05:06:54.960 --> 05:06:56.960
[Amit Varma]: someone's life, how they grew up,

05:06:56.960 --> 05:06:58.960
[Amit Varma]: their vulnerabilities, their insecurities,

05:06:58.960 --> 05:07:00.960
[Amit Varma]: their turning points, you don't really

05:07:00.960 --> 05:07:02.960
[Amit Varma]: get that anywhere else. Just

05:07:02.960 --> 05:07:04.960
[Amit Varma]: that personal touch. Like Ninal Pandey

05:07:04.960 --> 05:07:06.960
[Amit Varma]: came on the show and I asked my

05:07:06.960 --> 05:07:08.960
[Amit Varma]: first question about her childhood. She spoke for

05:07:08.960 --> 05:07:10.960
[Unknown]: one hour, ten minutes. She spoke

05:07:10.960 --> 05:07:12.960
[Amit Varma]: for one hour, ten minutes and she took

05:07:12.960 --> 05:07:14.960
[Amit Varma]: me from the 50s to the 70s. She

05:07:14.960 --> 05:07:16.960
[Amit Varma]: covered 30 years and it was

05:07:16.960 --> 05:07:18.960
[Amit Varma]: magical. Talking about her

05:07:18.960 --> 05:07:20.960
[Amit Varma]: mother, talking about her sister, talking

05:07:20.960 --> 05:07:22.960
[Amit Varma]: about her early childhood years.

05:07:22.960 --> 05:07:24.960
[Amit Varma]: You know, the first time they were at a balcony and

05:07:24.960 --> 05:07:26.960
[Amit Varma]: a group of people were going past in the early

05:07:26.960 --> 05:07:28.960
[Amit Varma]: 50s and she asked her mother,

05:07:28.960 --> 05:07:30.960
[Amit Varma]: what is that? Or her grandmother, what are

05:07:30.960 --> 05:07:32.960
[Amit Varma]: these people? And the grandmother

05:07:32.960 --> 05:07:34.960
[Amit Varma]: said, Re-pu-jis.

05:07:34.960 --> 05:07:36.960
[Amit Varma]: You know, and she repeats it like that to me

05:07:36.960 --> 05:07:38.960
[Amit Varma]: 70 years later. And

05:07:38.960 --> 05:07:40.960
[Amit Varma]: for me, those moments are magical

05:07:40.960 --> 05:07:42.960
[Amit Varma]: when you have a person

05:07:42.960 --> 05:07:44.960
[Amit Varma]: revealing themselves. Like Nikhil did so much

05:07:44.960 --> 05:07:46.960
[Amit Varma]: in his episode. Nikhil Taneja,

05:07:46.960 --> 05:07:48.960
[Amit Varma]: The Loneliness of the Indian Man. And I think

05:07:48.960 --> 05:07:50.960
[Amit Varma]: that, for me, that's

05:07:50.960 --> 05:07:52.960
[Amit Varma]: kind of special. Just listening to these

05:07:52.960 --> 05:07:54.960
[Amit Varma]: and these human connections.

05:07:54.960 --> 05:07:56.960
[Amit Varma]: And many of my listeners agree, you know.

05:07:56.960 --> 05:07:58.960
[Amit Varma]: I'm sure I've lost

05:07:58.960 --> 05:08:00.960
[Amit Varma]: some listeners because I don't do two hour

05:08:00.960 --> 05:08:02.960
[Amit Varma]: deep dives into subjects, I do five hour deep

05:08:02.960 --> 05:08:04.960
[Amit Varma]: dives into people. But that's just

05:08:04.960 --> 05:08:06.960
[Amit Varma]: a direction that I like to go

05:08:06.960 --> 05:08:08.960
[Amit Varma]: and I think that's kind of

05:08:08.960 --> 05:08:10.960
[Amit Varma]: value to me. And I'm wondering

05:08:10.960 --> 05:08:12.960
[Amit Varma]: if that's also

05:08:12.960 --> 05:08:14.960
[Amit Varma]: something that happened with you

05:08:14.960 --> 05:08:16.960
[Amit Varma]: Vikram, in the course of, as we get back to your

05:08:16.960 --> 05:08:18.960
[Amit Varma]: cricket lessons, but in the course of your

05:08:18.960 --> 05:08:20.960
[Amit Varma]: interacting with cricket,

05:08:20.960 --> 05:08:22.960
[Amit Varma]: where at one level

05:08:22.960 --> 05:08:24.960
[Amit Varma]: when you go into it, you

05:08:24.960 --> 05:08:26.960
[Amit Varma]: see that these guys are almost larger

05:08:26.960 --> 05:08:28.960
[Amit Varma]: than life, right? Tendulkar,

05:08:28.960 --> 05:08:30.960
[Amit Varma]: Dravid, Kumle. I mean, they're just, you know,

05:08:30.960 --> 05:08:32.960
[Amit Varma]: I still remember Kumle with

05:08:32.960 --> 05:08:34.960
[Amit Varma]: you know, we were doing live

05:08:34.960 --> 05:08:36.960
[Amit Varma]: bulletins for a test match in the West Indies

05:08:36.960 --> 05:08:38.960
[Amit Varma]: where he broke his jaw and he went out to bowl with

05:08:38.960 --> 05:08:40.960
[Amit Varma]: that, you know. And that makes him so

05:08:40.960 --> 05:08:42.960
[Amit Varma]: much larger than life. But then you're responding to

05:08:42.960 --> 05:08:44.960
[Amit Varma]: them as people and you're seeing their frailties

05:08:44.960 --> 05:08:46.960
[Amit Varma]: and their weaknesses and you're learning

05:08:46.960 --> 05:08:48.960
[Amit Varma]: lessons from that, which of course we'll go back to

05:08:48.960 --> 05:08:50.960
[Amit Varma]: now. But what has been

05:08:50.960 --> 05:08:52.960
[Amit Varma]: your sense through this time

05:08:52.960 --> 05:08:54.960
[Amit Varma]: of relating to people as people? And the reason

05:08:54.960 --> 05:08:56.960
[Amit Varma]: I ask that is that I think

05:08:56.960 --> 05:08:58.960
[Amit Varma]: what I did when I was younger,

05:08:58.960 --> 05:09:00.960
[Amit Varma]: and I don't want to generalize about whether young people

05:09:00.960 --> 05:09:02.960
[Amit Varma]: do it, but I think all people do it to an extent,

05:09:02.960 --> 05:09:04.960
[Amit Varma]: is that you are the

05:09:04.960 --> 05:09:06.960
[Amit Varma]: center of the world, right?

05:09:06.960 --> 05:09:08.960
[Amit Varma]: You are the, you're playing the lead role

05:09:08.960 --> 05:09:10.960
[Amit Varma]: in the play in your head. Everybody

05:09:10.960 --> 05:09:12.960
[Amit Varma]: else is a prop or a side character, but

05:09:12.960 --> 05:09:14.960
[Amit Varma]: you are everything. You look at people

05:09:14.960 --> 05:09:16.960
[Amit Varma]: only in the sense that they are instrumental

05:09:16.960 --> 05:09:18.960
[Amit Varma]: to you or they are important for your story,

05:09:18.960 --> 05:09:20.960
[Amit Varma]: but not as people themselves.

05:09:20.960 --> 05:09:22.960
[Amit Varma]: And then I think what I have

05:09:22.960 --> 05:09:24.960
[Amit Varma]: learnt most of all through my journey

05:09:24.960 --> 05:09:26.960
[Amit Varma]: is to just have

05:09:26.960 --> 05:09:28.960
[Amit Varma]: that humility and to respond to

05:09:28.960 --> 05:09:30.960
[Amit Varma]: people as people, which obviously

05:09:30.960 --> 05:09:32.960
[Amit Varma]: listening to their stories

05:09:32.960 --> 05:09:34.960
[Amit Varma]: helps me do a lot. So how has that

05:09:34.960 --> 05:09:36.960
[Guest 2]: journey been for you guys? Absolutely.

05:09:36.960 --> 05:09:38.960
[Guest 2]: And the joy that you

05:09:38.960 --> 05:09:40.960
[Guest 2]: get unraveling people and

05:09:40.960 --> 05:09:42.960
[Guest 2]: kind of understanding

05:09:42.960 --> 05:09:44.960
[Guest 2]: their stories is exactly the joy

05:09:44.960 --> 05:09:46.960
[Guest 2]: I got in the journey of covering cricket

05:09:46.960 --> 05:09:48.960
[Guest 2]: is because

05:09:48.960 --> 05:09:50.960
[Guest 2]: when you meet people who you

05:09:50.960 --> 05:09:52.960
[Guest 2]: admire because of the nature of the profession

05:09:52.960 --> 05:09:54.960
[Guest 2]: they are in, you realize that

05:09:54.960 --> 05:09:56.960
[Guest 2]: you in your normal

05:09:56.960 --> 05:09:58.960
[Guest 2]: life are noticing people

05:09:58.960 --> 05:10:00.960
[Guest 2]: in relatively low pressure

05:10:00.960 --> 05:10:02.960
[Guest 2]: zones. But sport

05:10:02.960 --> 05:10:04.960
[Guest 2]: is, it's gladiatorial,

05:10:04.960 --> 05:10:06.960
[Guest 2]: right? You notice people in high

05:10:06.960 --> 05:10:08.960
[Guest 2]: pressure zones. And unlike

05:10:08.960 --> 05:10:10.960
[Guest 2]: your profession,

05:10:10.960 --> 05:10:12.960
[Guest 2]: that is why, what is the most exciting

05:10:12.960 --> 05:10:14.960
[Guest 2]: thing about high performance careers, right?

05:10:14.960 --> 05:10:16.960
[Guest 2]: People who are astronauts, or for that

05:10:16.960 --> 05:10:18.960
[Guest 2]: matter, mountaineers and cricketers

05:10:18.960 --> 05:10:20.960
[Guest 2]: and stuff like that, that when you

05:10:20.960 --> 05:10:22.960
[Guest 2]: unravel them,

05:10:22.960 --> 05:10:24.960
[Guest 2]: the quality of the insight

05:10:24.960 --> 05:10:26.960
[Guest 2]: is phenomenal.

05:10:26.960 --> 05:10:28.960
[Guest 2]: It just opens your mind and says,

05:10:28.960 --> 05:10:30.960
[Guest 2]: Oh, this can also happen. In normal

05:10:30.960 --> 05:10:32.960
[Guest 2]: circumstances, how much do we visualize?

05:10:32.960 --> 05:10:34.960
[Guest 2]: But when you hear a story of a

05:10:34.960 --> 05:10:36.960
[Guest 2]: cricketer or a basketball player visualizing,

05:10:36.960 --> 05:10:38.960
[Guest 2]: the impact

05:10:38.960 --> 05:10:40.960
[Guest 2]: of that concept hits you harder.

05:10:40.960 --> 05:10:42.960
[Guest 2]: So when you talk to maybe

05:10:42.960 --> 05:10:44.960
[Guest 2]: an economist or for that matter, somebody who

05:10:44.960 --> 05:10:46.960
[Guest 2]: has been a foreign secretary, you know

05:10:46.960 --> 05:10:48.960
[Guest 2]: it's a high pressure zone that the person

05:10:48.960 --> 05:10:50.960
[Guest 2]: has performed. And therefore, the

05:10:50.960 --> 05:10:52.960
[Guest 2]: higher the pressure, the

05:10:52.960 --> 05:10:54.960
[Guest 2]: more interesting the story gets.

05:10:54.960 --> 05:10:56.960
[Guest 2]: This is what I have realized. And because

05:10:56.960 --> 05:10:58.960
[Guest 2]: you love a particular sport

05:10:58.960 --> 05:11:00.960
[Guest 2]: or for that matter, a particular

05:11:00.960 --> 05:11:02.960
[Guest 2]: profession, when you start

05:11:02.960 --> 05:11:04.960
[Guest 2]: entering their world

05:11:04.960 --> 05:11:06.960
[Guest 2]: and what is our joy, right? And I think

05:11:06.960 --> 05:11:08.960
[Guest 2]: we share this thing.

05:11:08.960 --> 05:11:10.960
[Guest 2]: We like to go into other people's world.

05:11:10.960 --> 05:11:12.960
[Guest 2]: And that's why you read so many books,

05:11:12.960 --> 05:11:14.960
[Guest 2]: right? What is a book? A book

05:11:14.960 --> 05:11:16.960
[Guest 2]: basically is transporting you to

05:11:16.960 --> 05:11:18.960
[Guest 2]: a different profession, a different person,

05:11:18.960 --> 05:11:20.960
[Guest 2]: a different thought process where you are

05:11:20.960 --> 05:11:22.960
[Guest 2]: saying, Boss, if I read

05:11:22.960 --> 05:11:24.960
[Guest 2]: a book by an economist, I became an economist.

05:11:24.960 --> 05:11:26.960
[Guest 2]: If I read a book by a cricketer, I became a cricketer.

05:11:26.960 --> 05:11:28.960
[Guest 2]: So somewhere it's a voyeuristic

05:11:28.960 --> 05:11:30.960
[Guest 2]: way in which

05:11:30.960 --> 05:11:32.960
[Guest 2]: you live other people. And that's why I like

05:11:32.960 --> 05:11:34.960
[Guest 2]: autobiographies. And that's why when I went into

05:11:34.960 --> 05:11:36.960
[Guest 2]: his world and I'm saying that, Boss, I'm

05:11:36.960 --> 05:11:38.960
[Guest 2]: sitting with a guy

05:11:38.960 --> 05:11:40.960
[Guest 2]: who's actually scored the 100 100s.

05:11:40.960 --> 05:11:42.960
[Guest 2]: And now he

05:11:42.960 --> 05:11:44.960
[Guest 2]: will tell me, Boss, what happened?

05:11:44.960 --> 05:11:46.960
[Guest 2]: Now when he tells me what happened,

05:11:46.960 --> 05:11:48.960
[Guest 2]: my dopamine

05:11:48.960 --> 05:11:50.960
[Guest 2]: goes to the dope level.

05:11:52.960 --> 05:11:54.960
[Unknown]: Because I'm thinking,

05:11:54.960 --> 05:11:56.960
[Guest 2]: he told me that story.

05:11:56.960 --> 05:11:58.960
[Guest 2]: It feels good to hear a story.

05:11:58.960 --> 05:12:00.960
[Guest 2]: We are all in the story business.

05:12:00.960 --> 05:12:02.960
[Guest 2]: So

05:12:02.960 --> 05:12:04.960
[Guest 2]: that is why when What the Duck happened,

05:12:04.960 --> 05:12:06.960
[Guest 2]: What the Duck moment for me

05:12:06.960 --> 05:12:08.960
[Guest 2]: was like your scene and the unseen moment.

05:12:08.960 --> 05:12:10.960
[Guest 2]: Where you're going and asking them questions

05:12:10.960 --> 05:12:12.960
[Guest 2]: and they are putting down

05:12:12.960 --> 05:12:14.960
[Guest 2]: their entire life story.

05:12:14.960 --> 05:12:16.960
[Guest 2]: But I don't deep dive that much.

05:12:16.960 --> 05:12:18.960
[Guest 2]: I had 45 minutes to an hour.

05:12:18.960 --> 05:12:20.960
[Guest 2]: So my curation was way more

05:12:20.960 --> 05:12:22.960
[Guest 2]: because they are people with limited

05:12:22.960 --> 05:12:24.960
[Guest 2]: time and they would not like to share their life.

05:12:24.960 --> 05:12:26.960
[Guest 2]: And they would not like

05:12:26.960 --> 05:12:28.960
[Guest 2]: to share their life in public. They would share that

05:12:28.960 --> 05:12:30.960
[Guest 2]: with me over a drink or whatever

05:12:30.960 --> 05:12:32.960
[Guest 2]: and stuff like that. But when you

05:12:32.960 --> 05:12:34.960
[Guest 2]: hear those insights, the joy you

05:12:34.960 --> 05:12:36.960
[Guest 2]: get is what makes this

05:12:36.960 --> 05:12:38.960
[Guest 2]: entire activity special.

05:12:38.960 --> 05:12:40.960
[Guest 2]: You talk about work ethic. One of the biggest

05:12:40.960 --> 05:12:42.960
[Guest 2]: events I have done from a

05:12:42.960 --> 05:12:44.960
[Guest 2]: sheer happiness point of

05:12:44.960 --> 05:12:46.960
[Guest 2]: view is a concert that

05:12:46.960 --> 05:12:48.960
[Guest 2]: we did where

05:12:48.960 --> 05:12:50.960
[Guest 1]: Sachin Tendulkar was in conversation with

05:12:50.960 --> 05:12:52.960
[Guest 2]: Ustad Zakir Hussain.

05:12:52.960 --> 05:12:54.960
[Guest 2]: Man, to me that three days

05:12:54.960 --> 05:12:56.960
[Guest 2]: of sitting with Zakir Hussain and Sachin

05:12:56.960 --> 05:12:58.960
[Guest 2]: Tendulkar curating this show

05:12:58.960 --> 05:13:00.960
[Guest 2]: and what they will be speaking. It's a tough

05:13:00.960 --> 05:13:02.960
[Guest 2]: one, right? One is a cricketer, one is a tabla

05:13:02.960 --> 05:13:04.960
[Guest 2]: maestro. But I

05:13:04.960 --> 05:13:06.960
[Guest 2]: want to get them to

05:13:06.960 --> 05:13:08.960
[Guest 2]: common points where they talk about them

05:13:08.960 --> 05:13:10.960
[Guest 2]: and then the final

05:13:10.960 --> 05:13:12.960
[Guest 2]: output should be, oh my god.

05:13:12.960 --> 05:13:14.960
[Guest 2]: So it was just amazing

05:13:14.960 --> 05:13:16.960
[Guest 2]: because Zakir Hussain was saying things

05:13:16.960 --> 05:13:18.960
[Guest 2]: about his life which were like

05:13:18.960 --> 05:13:20.960
[Guest 2]: wow, what a story that he told.

05:13:20.960 --> 05:13:22.960
[Guest 2]: Imagine, this is Sachin, this is Zakir

05:13:22.960 --> 05:13:24.960
[Guest 2]: Hussain, this is me, this is Sunandan

05:13:24.960 --> 05:13:26.960
[Guest 2]: and a conversation is happening

05:13:26.960 --> 05:13:28.960
[Guest 2]: where Zakir Hussain is saying that

05:13:28.960 --> 05:13:30.960
[Guest 2]: Sachin, first show me your hands.

05:13:30.960 --> 05:13:32.960
[Guest 2]: And he showed his hands and

05:13:32.960 --> 05:13:34.960
[Guest 2]: Zakir Hussain touched his hand

05:13:34.960 --> 05:13:36.960
[Guest 2]: and said that just give me 30 seconds.

05:13:36.960 --> 05:13:38.960
[Guest 2]: The hands

05:13:38.960 --> 05:13:40.960
[Guest 2]: that made 100

05:13:40.960 --> 05:13:42.960
[Guest 2]: let the power of those hands go into my hands.

05:13:42.960 --> 05:13:44.960
[Guest 2]: By doing this, he held his

05:13:44.960 --> 05:13:46.960
[Guest 2]: hand for 30 seconds. And Zakir is a

05:13:46.960 --> 05:13:48.960
[Guest 2]: maestro, right? At all levels

05:13:48.960 --> 05:13:50.960
[Guest 2]: he is a charming man.

05:13:50.960 --> 05:13:52.960
[Guest 2]: And then he said that actually

05:13:52.960 --> 05:13:54.960
[Guest 2]: these hands were also mine.

05:13:54.960 --> 05:13:56.960
[Guest 2]: So I said, Zakir bhai, why are you saying this?

05:13:56.960 --> 05:13:58.960
[Guest 2]: I was a wicket keeper in Shivaji Park.

05:13:58.960 --> 05:14:00.960
[Guest 2]: And we used to live in Mahim.

05:14:00.960 --> 05:14:02.960
[Guest 2]: I used to play regular cricket.

05:14:02.960 --> 05:14:04.960
[Guest 2]: I was a good wicket keeper.

05:14:04.960 --> 05:14:06.960
[Guest 2]: One day, while collecting the ball

05:14:06.960 --> 05:14:08.960
[Guest 2]: on my left hand,

05:14:08.960 --> 05:14:10.960
[Guest 2]: when I came home,

05:14:10.960 --> 05:14:12.960
[Guest 2]: Baba said

05:14:12.960 --> 05:14:14.960
[Guest 2]: that son, come here.

05:14:14.960 --> 05:14:16.960
[Guest 2]: Your hands

05:14:16.960 --> 05:14:18.960
[Guest 2]: are not made to collect the ball.

05:14:20.960 --> 05:14:22.960
[Guest 2]: What you can see

05:14:22.960 --> 05:14:24.960
[Guest 2]: your hands are made to

05:14:24.960 --> 05:14:26.960
[Guest 2]: collect the ball.

05:14:26.960 --> 05:14:28.960
[Guest 2]: And he said for me that was a day where I felt

05:14:28.960 --> 05:14:30.960
[Guest 2]: really hurt because my cricket was being

05:14:30.960 --> 05:14:32.960
[Guest 2]: taken away from me because I loved wicket keeping.

05:14:32.960 --> 05:14:34.960
[Guest 2]: And then they had a conversation

05:14:34.960 --> 05:14:36.960
[Guest 2]: about

05:14:36.960 --> 05:14:38.960
[Guest 2]: the sound of the tabla.

05:14:38.960 --> 05:14:40.960
[Guest 2]: And then Sachin said,

05:14:40.960 --> 05:14:42.960
[Guest 2]: for both of us, sound is important.

05:14:42.960 --> 05:14:44.960
[Guest 2]: Because there is

05:14:44.960 --> 05:14:46.960
[Guest 2]: twice in the net when you get that.

05:14:46.960 --> 05:14:48.960
[Guest 2]: And you know the sound

05:14:48.960 --> 05:14:50.960
[Guest 2]: is where an indicator

05:14:50.960 --> 05:14:52.960
[Guest 2]: of whether you are in form or not.

05:14:52.960 --> 05:14:54.960
[Guest 2]: And he said exactly, when we come to the sum,

05:14:54.960 --> 05:14:56.960
[Guest 2]: when we play the tabla

05:14:56.960 --> 05:14:58.960
[Guest 2]: with that sound.

05:14:58.960 --> 05:15:00.960
[Guest 2]: Amit, this went on and I am like

05:15:00.960 --> 05:15:02.960
[Amit Varma]: wow, wow, wow, wow.

05:15:02.960 --> 05:15:04.960
[Guest 2]: And you are also a tabla player and a batsman yourself.

05:15:04.960 --> 05:15:06.960
[Guest 2]: Again, I am a failed tabla player

05:15:06.960 --> 05:15:08.960
[Guest 2]: and a failed cricketer. So I appreciate this more.

05:15:08.960 --> 05:15:10.960
[Guest 2]: And then Zakir Bhai said

05:15:10.960 --> 05:15:12.960
[Guest 2]: something interesting. He said,

05:15:12.960 --> 05:15:14.960
[Guest 2]: Sachin, do you remember you made 241

05:15:14.960 --> 05:15:16.960
[Guest 2]: when you

05:15:16.960 --> 05:15:18.960
[Guest 2]: hit the upper cut

05:15:18.960 --> 05:15:20.960
[Guest 2]: of Brett Lee's short ball.

05:15:20.960 --> 05:15:22.960
[Guest 2]: In our profession,

05:15:22.960 --> 05:15:24.960
[Guest 2]: that is called coming to the sum.

05:15:24.960 --> 05:15:26.960
[Guest 2]: When

05:15:26.960 --> 05:15:28.960
[Guest 2]: that sound comes,

05:15:28.960 --> 05:15:30.960
[Guest 2]: when it comes out of the tabla,

05:15:30.960 --> 05:15:32.960
[Guest 2]: then you are in form.

05:15:32.960 --> 05:15:34.960
[Unknown]: And then they went on.

05:15:34.960 --> 05:15:36.960
[Guest 1]: And then Tendulkar played that instrument.

05:15:36.960 --> 05:15:38.960
[Guest 2]: He played that instrument.

05:15:38.960 --> 05:15:40.960
[Guest 2]: We curated that as well.

05:15:40.960 --> 05:15:42.960
[Guest 2]: And then it went on

05:15:42.960 --> 05:15:44.960
[Guest 2]: and then I, standard work

05:15:44.960 --> 05:15:46.960
[Guest 2]: ethic question, so I asked

05:15:46.960 --> 05:15:48.960
[Guest 2]: Zakir Bhai that

05:15:48.960 --> 05:15:50.960
[Guest 2]: how many hours do you practice?

05:15:50.960 --> 05:15:52.960
[Guest 2]: I was looking for 12 hours

05:15:52.960 --> 05:15:54.960
[Guest 2]: and 14 hours. He looked

05:15:54.960 --> 05:15:56.960
[Guest 2]: at me and said, sometimes

05:15:56.960 --> 05:15:58.960
[Guest 2]: we stop.

05:15:58.960 --> 05:16:00.960
[Guest 2]: Then I went

05:16:00.960 --> 05:16:02.960
[Guest 2]: and said, what are you saying?

05:16:02.960 --> 05:16:04.960
[Guest 2]: He said that a good artist

05:16:04.960 --> 05:16:06.960
[Guest 2]: never stops practicing.

05:16:06.960 --> 05:16:08.960
[Guest 2]: When you

05:16:08.960 --> 05:16:10.960
[Guest 2]: sit on the tabla, it comes out.

05:16:10.960 --> 05:16:12.960
[Guest 2]: But

05:16:12.960 --> 05:16:14.960
[Guest 2]: when you practice so many ragas

05:16:14.960 --> 05:16:16.960
[Guest 2]: in your mind, then

05:16:16.960 --> 05:16:18.960
[Guest 2]: there is no time for you

05:16:18.960 --> 05:16:20.960
[Guest 2]: to not be in it.

05:16:20.960 --> 05:16:22.960
[Guest 2]: When you sit on a concert,

05:16:22.960 --> 05:16:24.960
[Guest 2]: your image is already there

05:16:24.960 --> 05:16:26.960
[Guest 2]: and you join it

05:16:26.960 --> 05:16:28.960
[Guest 2]: and it comes out through the tabla.

05:16:28.960 --> 05:16:30.960
[Guest 2]: So work ethic

05:16:30.960 --> 05:16:32.960
[Guest 2]: is the same thing

05:16:32.960 --> 05:16:34.960
[Guest 2]: in whose mind it goes on.

05:16:34.960 --> 05:16:36.960
[Guest 2]: Imagine Sachin Tendulkar said, yeah, you are always

05:16:36.960 --> 05:16:38.960
[Guest 2]: batting. And to me,

05:16:38.960 --> 05:16:40.960
[Guest 2]: he

05:16:40.960 --> 05:16:42.960
[Guest 2]: making one point, this guy

05:16:42.960 --> 05:16:44.960
[Guest 2]: making and he said that, you know,

05:16:44.960 --> 05:16:46.960
[Guest 2]: as a kid, I didn't know when I was stopping

05:16:46.960 --> 05:16:48.960
[Guest 2]: batting because I was always playing

05:16:48.960 --> 05:16:50.960
[Guest 2]: the ball in my head.

05:16:50.960 --> 05:16:52.960
[Guest 2]: Even Kohli talks about it.

05:16:52.960 --> 05:16:54.960
[Guest 2]: The fact that my success

05:16:54.960 --> 05:16:56.960
[Guest 2]: he says is because of the fact that

05:16:56.960 --> 05:16:58.960
[Guest 2]: I am constantly practicing.

05:16:58.960 --> 05:17:00.960
[Guest 2]: Whether you are practicing actually or

05:17:00.960 --> 05:17:02.960
[Guest 2]: practicing in your brain does not matter.

05:17:02.960 --> 05:17:04.960
[Guest 2]: And that kind of

05:17:04.960 --> 05:17:06.960
[Guest 2]: you know,

05:17:06.960 --> 05:17:08.960
[Guest 2]: this entire journey of experiencing

05:17:08.960 --> 05:17:10.960
[Guest 2]: both professions

05:17:10.960 --> 05:17:12.960
[Guest 2]: but reaching to the common goal of

05:17:12.960 --> 05:17:14.960
[Guest 2]: excellence. When you said work ethic

05:17:14.960 --> 05:17:16.960
[Guest 2]: kind of these were memories that I could

05:17:16.960 --> 05:17:18.960
[Guest 2]: not forget. And there was another one

05:17:18.960 --> 05:17:20.960
[Guest 2]: very interesting memory. Martina Navratilova

05:17:20.960 --> 05:17:22.960
[Guest 2]: I was interviewing in Thailand.

05:17:22.960 --> 05:17:24.960
[Guest 2]: And so

05:17:24.960 --> 05:17:26.960
[Guest 1]: this is again, you know.

05:17:26.960 --> 05:17:28.960
[Guest 1]: While all the dealers are taking massages.

05:17:30.960 --> 05:17:32.960
[Guest 2]: Yeah, and this is

05:17:32.960 --> 05:17:34.960
[Guest 2]: the most important lesson I have

05:17:34.960 --> 05:17:36.960
[Guest 2]: learned in life.

05:17:36.960 --> 05:17:38.960
[Guest 2]: And which has come through sport

05:17:38.960 --> 05:17:40.960
[Guest 2]: but in a sense it kind of is

05:17:40.960 --> 05:17:42.960
[Guest 2]: the most important lesson everybody should

05:17:42.960 --> 05:17:44.960
[Guest 2]: learn about and that is being in the moment.

05:17:44.960 --> 05:17:46.960
[Guest 2]: Right?

05:17:46.960 --> 05:17:48.960
[Guest 2]: So

05:17:48.960 --> 05:17:50.960
[Guest 2]: I asked Martina that you know

05:17:50.960 --> 05:17:52.960
[Guest 2]: when does a sports person

05:17:52.960 --> 05:17:54.960
[Guest 2]: decide to call it a day?

05:17:54.960 --> 05:17:56.960
[Guest 2]: She said it's a very

05:17:56.960 --> 05:17:58.960
[Guest 2]: simple answer.

05:17:58.960 --> 05:18:00.960
[Guest 2]: And it happened to me at Wimbledon.

05:18:00.960 --> 05:18:02.960
[Guest 2]: I was about to serve

05:18:02.960 --> 05:18:04.960
[Guest 2]: and I could hear the plane pass by.

05:18:06.960 --> 05:18:08.960
[Guest 2]: I stopped, again I

05:18:08.960 --> 05:18:10.960
[Guest 2]: tossed the ball and I could hear the plane

05:18:10.960 --> 05:18:12.960
[Guest 2]: pass by again.

05:18:12.960 --> 05:18:14.960
[Guest 2]: And that day she said I decided

05:18:14.960 --> 05:18:16.960
[Amit Varma]: to retire. What an answer.

05:18:16.960 --> 05:18:18.960
[Guest 2]: She said because in my life

05:18:18.960 --> 05:18:20.960
[Guest 2]: when I was at play

05:18:20.960 --> 05:18:22.960
[Guest 2]: I could not hear anything.

05:18:22.960 --> 05:18:24.960
[Guest 2]: And the day I heard

05:18:24.960 --> 05:18:26.960
[Guest 2]: the plane I knew it was time for me.

05:18:26.960 --> 05:18:28.960
[Guest 2]: Ian Chappell said the same thing.

05:18:28.960 --> 05:18:30.960
[Guest 2]: He said Chapelle when did you retire? He said

05:18:30.960 --> 05:18:32.960
[Guest 2]: there was a match in Adelaide

05:18:32.960 --> 05:18:34.960
[Guest 2]: when I was in second slip.

05:18:34.960 --> 05:18:36.960
[Guest 2]: And at around 4.30

05:18:36.960 --> 05:18:38.960
[Guest 2]: I looked at the watch.

05:18:38.960 --> 05:18:40.960
[Guest 2]: And I looked at the watch again at 4.45.

05:18:40.960 --> 05:18:42.960
[Guest 2]: 5.15 I had decided to retire.

05:18:42.960 --> 05:18:44.960
[Guest 2]: Because Martina said

05:18:44.960 --> 05:18:46.960
[Guest 2]: the human mind

05:18:46.960 --> 05:18:48.960
[Guest 2]: has the ability to focus only on

05:18:48.960 --> 05:18:50.960
[Guest 2]: one thing. It's the past, present

05:18:50.960 --> 05:18:52.960
[Guest 2]: or the future. If something is

05:18:52.960 --> 05:18:54.960
[Guest 2]: disturbing your current moment

05:18:54.960 --> 05:18:56.960
[Guest 2]: it's an area of concern.

05:18:56.960 --> 05:18:58.960
[Guest 2]: And you have to evaluate it and you know that

05:18:58.960 --> 05:19:00.960
[Guest 2]: it's not the right day.

05:19:00.960 --> 05:19:02.960
[Guest 2]: And that brings me to an amazing story

05:19:02.960 --> 05:19:04.960
[Guest 2]: of Virendra Sehwag.

05:19:04.960 --> 05:19:06.960
[Guest 2]: Everybody knows about

05:19:06.960 --> 05:19:08.960
[Guest 2]: Veeru singing.

05:19:08.960 --> 05:19:10.960
[Guest 2]: I had a chat with him one day and said

05:19:10.960 --> 05:19:12.960
[Guest 2]: what's the theory of singing?

05:19:12.960 --> 05:19:14.960
[Guest 2]: Before this I had read a very interesting book

05:19:14.960 --> 05:19:16.960
[Guest 2]: by a guy called I think John Galway.

05:19:16.960 --> 05:19:18.960
[Guest 2]: He talks about

05:19:18.960 --> 05:19:20.960
[Guest 2]: the mental state in tennis.

05:19:20.960 --> 05:19:22.960
[Guest 2]: So it's a very interesting thing.

05:19:22.960 --> 05:19:24.960
[Guest 2]: He said when you are playing tennis

05:19:24.960 --> 05:19:26.960
[Guest 2]: you will normally hear

05:19:26.960 --> 05:19:28.960
[Guest 2]: players say what are you doing?

05:19:28.960 --> 05:19:30.960
[Guest 2]: Hit the shot.

05:19:30.960 --> 05:19:32.960
[Guest 2]: I also play tennis so I know that

05:19:32.960 --> 05:19:34.960
[Guest 2]: what he is doing.

05:19:34.960 --> 05:19:36.960
[Guest 2]: So he said there are two states of play

05:19:36.960 --> 05:19:38.960
[Guest 2]: in a human body when you are playing sport.

05:19:38.960 --> 05:19:40.960
[Guest 2]: One is that

05:19:40.960 --> 05:19:42.960
[Guest 2]: self-one which is that guy

05:19:42.960 --> 05:19:44.960
[Guest 2]: who is playing tennis who has honed his skill

05:19:44.960 --> 05:19:46.960
[Guest 2]: over the years and he has allowed

05:19:46.960 --> 05:19:48.960
[Guest 2]: the body to react.

05:19:48.960 --> 05:19:50.960
[Guest 2]: So your ball is coming, you are reacting

05:19:50.960 --> 05:19:52.960
[Guest 2]: because you have learnt it.

05:19:52.960 --> 05:19:54.960
[Guest 2]: The whole system is geared to pick

05:19:54.960 --> 05:19:56.960
[Guest 2]: the ball, length, drive, play the

05:19:56.960 --> 05:19:58.960
[Guest 2]: drop shot or whatever.

05:19:58.960 --> 05:20:00.960
[Guest 2]: Now this is what is

05:20:00.960 --> 05:20:02.960
[Guest 2]: the machine.

05:20:02.960 --> 05:20:04.960
[Guest 2]: Second is a guy called self-two

05:20:04.960 --> 05:20:06.960
[Guest 2]: which is there in the body which is the mind.

05:20:06.960 --> 05:20:08.960
[Guest 2]: This is the most dangerous guy

05:20:08.960 --> 05:20:10.960
[Guest 2]: because this is the guy who is creating

05:20:10.960 --> 05:20:12.960
[Guest 2]: self-doubt in self-one and disallowing

05:20:12.960 --> 05:20:14.960
[Guest 2]: him to play.

05:20:14.960 --> 05:20:16.960
[Guest 2]: So the whole journey of a sportsman

05:20:16.960 --> 05:20:18.960
[Guest 2]: is to keep self-two away

05:20:18.960 --> 05:20:20.960
[Guest 2]: from self-one.

05:20:20.960 --> 05:20:22.960
[Guest 2]: And sledging, and my analysis

05:20:22.960 --> 05:20:24.960
[Guest 2]: is sledging is exactly to

05:20:24.960 --> 05:20:26.960
[Guest 2]: activate self-two. So the moment

05:20:26.960 --> 05:20:28.960
[Guest 2]: a batsman comes into bat and a wicket keeper

05:20:28.960 --> 05:20:30.960
[Guest 2]: says, hey mate, yesterday you couldn't take the

05:20:30.960 --> 05:20:32.960
[Guest 2]: bouncer.

05:20:32.960 --> 05:20:34.960
[Guest 2]: Will tell self-two.

05:20:34.960 --> 05:20:36.960
[Guest 2]: And the moment self-two has said

05:20:36.960 --> 05:20:38.960
[Guest 2]: boss you can't play the bouncer

05:20:38.960 --> 05:20:40.960
[Guest 2]: the entire mind will shift to the fact

05:20:40.960 --> 05:20:42.960
[Guest 2]: that you can't play the bouncer and you

05:20:42.960 --> 05:20:44.960
[Guest 2]: will get out on a bouncer.

05:20:44.960 --> 05:20:46.960
[Guest 2]: So how do you deactivate this

05:20:46.960 --> 05:20:48.960
[Guest 2]: self-doubt fellow to allow your body

05:20:48.960 --> 05:20:50.960
[Guest 2]: to be in the natural state so

05:20:50.960 --> 05:20:52.960
[Guest 2]: that it reacts to the ball at play is

05:20:52.960 --> 05:20:54.960
[Guest 2]: the entire journey of being in the moment.

05:20:54.960 --> 05:20:56.960
[Guest 2]: And that is what a sports

05:20:56.960 --> 05:20:58.960
[Guest 2]: person is trying. And now in

05:20:58.960 --> 05:21:00.960
[Guest 2]: that context, I had read this and that's why if you

05:21:00.960 --> 05:21:02.960
[Guest 2]: see what you have to do is once you play

05:21:02.960 --> 05:21:04.960
[Guest 2]: a tennis shot, tennis players are told to

05:21:04.960 --> 05:21:06.960
[Guest 2]: count the strings of the racket.

05:21:06.960 --> 05:21:08.960
[Guest 2]: This allows you to

05:21:08.960 --> 05:21:10.960
[Guest 2]: worry about the bad shot that you

05:21:10.960 --> 05:21:12.960
[Guest 2]: played and you reduce the

05:21:12.960 --> 05:21:14.960
[Guest 2]: anxiety of the next shot you are going to play.

05:21:14.960 --> 05:21:16.960
[Guest 2]: So that's the logic of being in play.

05:21:16.960 --> 05:21:18.960
[Guest 2]: So when I asked Sehwag

05:21:18.960 --> 05:21:20.960
[Guest 2]: he said, Mr. Sathe, see what happens

05:21:20.960 --> 05:21:22.960
[Guest 2]: your wicket goes between one ball

05:21:22.960 --> 05:21:24.960
[Guest 2]: and the other ball.

05:21:24.960 --> 05:21:26.960
[Guest 2]: I said, explain.

