[Amit Varma]: athletes choke, I think I was basing

05:38:38.960 --> 05:38:40.960
[Amit Varma]: it on something Gladwell wrote

05:38:40.960 --> 05:38:42.960
[Amit Varma]: and it's exactly the same thing, that there is one

05:38:42.960 --> 05:38:44.960
[Amit Varma]: part of your decision making brain which is

05:38:44.960 --> 05:38:46.960
[Amit Varma]: just automating everything, so if I'm

05:38:46.960 --> 05:38:48.960
[Amit Varma]: driving on the street, where to turn

05:38:48.960 --> 05:38:50.960
[Amit Varma]: I'm not even thinking, actually it's really

05:38:50.960 --> 05:38:52.960
[Amit Varma]: complicated driving you know, there are the laws of

05:38:52.960 --> 05:38:54.960
[Amit Varma]: physics, different objects of different

05:38:54.960 --> 05:38:56.960
[Amit Varma]: masses moving from different angles at

05:38:56.960 --> 05:38:58.960
[Amit Varma]: different velocities, it's incredibly

05:38:58.960 --> 05:39:00.960
[Amit Varma]: complicated but the part of our brain

05:39:00.960 --> 05:39:02.960
[Amit Varma]: handles it, but the moment the other part of the

05:39:02.960 --> 05:39:04.960
[Amit Varma]: brain comes in where you begin to overthink it

05:39:04.960 --> 05:39:06.960
[Amit Varma]: you are screwed, like I

05:39:06.960 --> 05:39:08.960
[Amit Varma]: can type anything I want but if you ask me

05:39:08.960 --> 05:39:10.960
[Amit Varma]: where is Y on the keyboard, you know

05:39:10.960 --> 05:39:12.960
[Amit Varma]: without looking down, I can't tell you

05:39:12.960 --> 05:39:14.960
[Amit Varma]: even though I obviously know because I'm always

05:39:14.960 --> 05:39:16.960
[Amit Varma]: typing without looking at the keyboard or

05:39:16.960 --> 05:39:18.960
[Amit Varma]: if I say, how do you sign, show me

05:39:18.960 --> 05:39:20.960
[Amit Varma]: you know and you'll suddenly find

05:39:20.960 --> 05:39:22.960
[Amit Varma]: the other part of your brain has come in and you're having

05:39:22.960 --> 05:39:24.960
[Amit Varma]: trouble signing and you know

05:39:24.960 --> 05:39:26.960
[Amit Varma]: you no longer control your bank

05:39:26.960 --> 05:39:28.960
[Amit Varma]: account and everything's gone to hell

05:39:28.960 --> 05:39:30.960
[Amit Varma]: but you know, leaving that

05:39:30.960 --> 05:39:32.960
[Amit Varma]: aside, that

05:39:32.960 --> 05:39:34.960
[Amit Varma]: aspect of being in the moment, right

05:39:34.960 --> 05:39:36.960
[Amit Varma]: is super important

05:39:36.960 --> 05:39:38.960
[Amit Varma]: not just for a Martin and Avratilova

05:39:38.960 --> 05:39:40.960
[Amit Varma]: or for a Virender Sehwag

05:39:40.960 --> 05:39:42.960
[Amit Varma]: but it's important

05:39:42.960 --> 05:39:44.960
[Amit Varma]: for all of us and it's something that

05:39:44.960 --> 05:39:46.960
[Amit Varma]: I try to do but it's incredibly

05:39:46.960 --> 05:39:48.960
[Amit Varma]: hard because most of the time

05:39:48.960 --> 05:39:50.960
[Amit Varma]: you're just a little bit in the past or a little bit

05:39:50.960 --> 05:39:52.960
[Amit Varma]: in the future and earlier

05:39:52.960 --> 05:39:54.960
[Amit Varma]: you spoke about Roshan routinizing

05:39:54.960 --> 05:39:56.960
[Amit Varma]: everything and this is something I also

05:39:56.960 --> 05:39:58.960
[Amit Varma]: want to ask about, that boss

05:39:58.960 --> 05:40:00.960
[Amit Varma]: if I hadn't met you, I wouldn't have believed you're one person

05:40:00.960 --> 05:40:02.960
[Amit Varma]: I would have thought it's a collective of people

05:40:02.960 --> 05:40:04.960
[Amit Varma]: who call themselves Roshan Abbas and do all this

05:40:04.960 --> 05:40:06.960
[Amit Varma]: He's a pent-a-polar man

05:40:06.960 --> 05:40:08.960
[Amit Varma]: In fact, after this recording, I'm going to

05:40:08.960 --> 05:40:10.960
[Amit Varma]: check if during this recording he's posted something

