[Unknown]: on Twitter because then I will

05:40:12.960 --> 05:40:14.960
[Unknown]: know that there's someone else

05:40:14.960 --> 05:40:16.960
[Amit Varma]: It's a team of people who call themselves Roshan Abbas

05:40:16.960 --> 05:40:18.960
[Amit Varma]: This guy is a front

05:40:20.960 --> 05:40:22.960
[Amit Varma]: So I want to understand

05:40:22.960 --> 05:40:24.960
[Amit Varma]: a little bit from both of you

05:40:24.960 --> 05:40:26.960
[Amit Varma]: In your case, it's your mastery of work

05:40:26.960 --> 05:40:28.960
[Amit Varma]: ethic and discipline and

05:40:28.960 --> 05:40:30.960
[Amit Varma]: staying in the moment, each of the times you do

05:40:30.960 --> 05:40:32.960
[Amit Varma]: this and in your case, it would be like

05:40:32.960 --> 05:40:34.960
[Amit Varma]: in my case, an attempt

05:40:34.960 --> 05:40:36.960
[Amit Varma]: to be sort of like that

05:40:36.960 --> 05:40:38.960
[Amit Varma]: So I'd like to hear of both your

05:40:38.960 --> 05:40:40.960
[Amit Varma]: sort of experiences with this aspect

05:40:40.960 --> 05:40:42.960
[Amit Varma]: and then we'll get back to the cricket and to Meera Nairji

05:40:42.960 --> 05:40:44.960
[Guest 1]: And we've forgotten the singing

05:40:44.960 --> 05:40:46.960
[Amit Varma]: That will come in the end

05:40:46.960 --> 05:40:48.960
[Guest 2]: Right now, it's night time

05:40:48.960 --> 05:40:50.960
[Guest 2]: Being in the moment, I've spoken about this

05:40:50.960 --> 05:40:52.960
[Guest 2]: so I'll sum it up my way

05:40:52.960 --> 05:40:54.960
[Guest 2]: and then you can take on because you're actually

05:40:54.960 --> 05:40:56.960
[Amit Varma]: practicing it. But I'm actually asking about you

05:40:56.960 --> 05:40:58.960
[Amit Varma]: like what have been your experiences

05:40:58.960 --> 05:41:00.960
[Amit Varma]: How do you find a work ethic

05:41:00.960 --> 05:41:02.960
[Amit Varma]: for yourself? Because I have the same problem

05:41:02.960 --> 05:41:04.960
[Amit Varma]: as you in terms of attention span

05:41:04.960 --> 05:41:06.960
[Amit Varma]: and mind always wandering and seeking

05:41:06.960 --> 05:41:08.960
[Guest 2]: dopamine through various

05:41:08.960 --> 05:41:10.960
[Guest 2]: Amit, you are at least

05:41:10.960 --> 05:41:12.960
[Guest 2]: a thousand times better than me. I have

05:41:12.960 --> 05:41:14.960
[Guest 2]: had this problem since I was a child

05:41:14.960 --> 05:41:16.960
[Guest 2]: where my ability to

05:41:16.960 --> 05:41:18.960
[Guest 2]: read more than 10 minutes is

05:41:18.960 --> 05:41:20.960
[Guest 2]: not there. And I've struggled

05:41:20.960 --> 05:41:22.960
[Guest 2]: but because I've been a lazy person, this I could

05:41:22.960 --> 05:41:24.960
[Guest 2]: have won over only by

05:41:24.960 --> 05:41:26.960
[Guest 2]: discipline and routinizing, which Roshan now

05:41:26.960 --> 05:41:28.960
[Guest 2]: it comes naturally to him. So

05:41:28.960 --> 05:41:30.960
[Guest 2]: if I would have practiced, maybe today

05:41:30.960 --> 05:41:32.960
[Guest 2]: I decide to go home and I do

05:41:32.960 --> 05:41:34.960
[Guest 2]: the routine like, you know, you look

05:41:34.960 --> 05:41:36.960
[Guest 2]: at any cricketers post-match

05:41:36.960 --> 05:41:38.960
[Guest 2]: interview, it's the two words routine

05:41:38.960 --> 05:41:40.960
[Guest 2]: and process because that's the only

05:41:40.960 --> 05:41:42.960
[Guest 2]: way to come to the moment. There is no other

05:41:42.960 --> 05:41:44.960
[Guest 2]: way, right? So if we

05:41:44.960 --> 05:41:46.960
[Guest 2]: for example, you and me have to come

05:41:46.960 --> 05:41:48.960
[Guest 2]: to a point, we will have to

05:41:48.960 --> 05:41:50.960
[Guest 2]: design our life from 6 am

05:41:50.960 --> 05:41:52.960
[Guest 2]: in the morning, do that for 100

05:41:52.960 --> 05:41:54.960
[Guest 2]: days to get that behavioral delta

05:41:54.960 --> 05:41:56.960
[Guest 2]: going and only then we will be able

05:41:56.960 --> 05:41:58.960
[Guest 2]: to get that, you know, as Gulzar

05:41:58.960 --> 05:42:00.960
[Guest 2]: says to one of my friends

05:42:00.960 --> 05:42:02.960
[Guest 2]: that irrespective of

05:42:02.960 --> 05:42:04.960
[Guest 2]: what I do in my life

05:42:04.960 --> 05:42:06.960
[Guest 2]: 8 to

05:42:06.960 --> 05:42:08.960
[Guest 2]: 12 I write.

05:42:08.960 --> 05:42:10.960
[Guest 2]: That's routine. So

05:42:10.960 --> 05:42:12.960
[Guest 2]: once you write for 4 hours every

05:42:12.960 --> 05:42:14.960
[Guest 2]: day, you might write the worst

05:42:14.960 --> 05:42:16.960
[Guest 2]: thing in the world, but on your 100th

05:42:16.960 --> 05:42:18.960
[Guest 2]: day, you'll realize that the quality

05:42:18.960 --> 05:42:20.960
[Guest 2]: is improving. But I don't reach that process.

05:42:20.960 --> 05:42:22.960
[Guest 2]: I don't do it for a day

05:42:22.960 --> 05:42:24.960
[Guest 2]: and then I don't do it again.

05:42:24.960 --> 05:42:26.960
[Guest 2]: That is purely work ethic

05:42:26.960 --> 05:42:28.960
[Guest 2]: and discipline. And the moment you do it,

05:42:28.960 --> 05:42:30.960
[Guest 2]: I have been told by people who are

05:42:30.960 --> 05:42:32.960
[Guest 2]: performing at the highest level that you

05:42:32.960 --> 05:42:34.960
[Guest 2]: will be surprised with the power of routine.

05:42:34.960 --> 05:42:36.960
[Guest 2]: And that's what Atomic Habits also

05:42:36.960 --> 05:42:38.960
[Guest 2]: talks about, right? It is just about

05:42:38.960 --> 05:42:40.960
[Guest 2]: doing that drill again and again, playing

05:42:40.960 --> 05:42:42.960
[Guest 2]: those 200 balls on a daily basis

05:42:42.960 --> 05:42:44.960
[Guest 2]: and then you are also surprised

05:42:44.960 --> 05:42:46.960
[Guest 2]: how you hit that. That's why if you see Virat

05:42:46.960 --> 05:42:48.960
[Guest 2]: Kohli after that Haris

05:42:48.960 --> 05:42:50.960
[Guest 2]: Rao shot, you see

05:42:50.960 --> 05:42:52.960
[Guest 2]: him react in that post-match interview

05:42:52.960 --> 05:42:54.960
[Guest 2]: and I do post-match, I listen to post-match

05:42:54.960 --> 05:42:56.960
[Guest 2]: interviews very clearly because it's a

05:42:56.960 --> 05:42:58.960
[Guest 2]: good representation of the state of mind

05:42:58.960 --> 05:43:00.960
[Guest 2]: of the player at that point of time.

05:43:00.960 --> 05:43:02.960
[Guest 2]: He says, I don't know how it happened,

05:43:02.960 --> 05:43:04.960
[Guest 2]: which means he's in the moment.

05:43:04.960 --> 05:43:06.960
[Guest 2]: The moment you are in the moment,

05:43:06.960 --> 05:43:08.960
[Guest 2]: that's what in sporting parlance

05:43:08.960 --> 05:43:10.960
[Guest 2]: is called a zone, where you actually

05:43:10.960 --> 05:43:12.960
[Guest 2]: are not able to think of anything

05:43:12.960 --> 05:43:14.960
[Guest 2]: and that is where your anxiety is the least.

05:43:14.960 --> 05:43:16.960
[Guest 2]: Why do people say that,

05:43:16.960 --> 05:43:18.960
[Guest 2]: boss, in the moment when you are there, then

05:43:18.960 --> 05:43:20.960
[Guest 2]: there is no anxiety and stress in your life

05:43:20.960 --> 05:43:22.960
[Guest 2]: because the past and present have been eliminated.

05:43:22.960 --> 05:43:24.960
[Guest 2]: So philosophically also,

05:43:24.960 --> 05:43:26.960
[Guest 2]: Patanjali 4000 years was trying to tell you

05:43:26.960 --> 05:43:28.960
[Guest 2]: the same thing, that if you

05:43:28.960 --> 05:43:30.960
[Guest 2]: stay on your breath, then you can't stay anywhere else.

05:43:30.960 --> 05:43:32.960
[Guest 2]: Humanly it's not possible

05:43:32.960 --> 05:43:34.960
[Guest 2]: that when I'm talking to you, I'm

05:43:34.960 --> 05:43:36.960
[Guest 2]: on Twitter. Roshan is different.

05:43:38.960 --> 05:43:40.960
[Guest 2]: But I'm saying generally for a person,

05:43:40.960 --> 05:43:42.960
[Guest 2]: one thing at a time,

05:43:42.960 --> 05:43:44.960
[Guest 2]: but you have to come to that work

05:43:44.960 --> 05:43:46.960
[Guest 2]: and look at that ball.

05:43:46.960 --> 05:43:48.960
[Guest 2]: Once Tendulkar told me that at

05:43:48.960 --> 05:43:50.960
[Guest 2]: 30th over, by the

05:43:50.960 --> 05:43:52.960
[Guest 2]: color of the ball, I could

05:43:52.960 --> 05:43:54.960
[Guest 2]: pick at what point Magra would reverse swing.

05:43:54.960 --> 05:43:56.960
[Guest 2]: And that I had done

05:43:56.960 --> 05:43:58.960
[Guest 2]: by observing how color of the ball changes.

05:43:58.960 --> 05:44:00.960
[Guest 2]: This is genius, right?

05:44:00.960 --> 05:44:02.960
[Guest 2]: I mean, how can you figure

05:44:02.960 --> 05:44:04.960
[Guest 2]: out color of the ball and the nature of the reverse swing?

05:44:04.960 --> 05:44:06.960
[Guest 2]: That comes because the guys see

05:44:06.960 --> 05:44:08.960
[Guest 2]: and there is a huge significance

05:44:08.960 --> 05:44:10.960
[Guest 2]: when the commentator says that he is seeing the ball

05:44:10.960 --> 05:44:12.960
[Guest 2]: like a football. We think that

05:44:12.960 --> 05:44:14.960
[Guest 2]: this is it. That big look

05:44:14.960 --> 05:44:16.960
[Guest 2]: means that he is in such a

05:44:16.960 --> 05:44:18.960
[Guest 2]: zone that his pupils are also dilating.

05:44:18.960 --> 05:44:20.960
[Guest 2]: And as they say

05:44:20.960 --> 05:44:22.960
[Guest 2]: when your adrenaline is high,

05:44:22.960 --> 05:44:24.960
[Guest 2]: when you come in a fighter flight,

05:44:24.960 --> 05:44:26.960
[Guest 2]: then your blood pressure

05:44:26.960 --> 05:44:28.960
[Guest 2]: improves and that's when your body

05:44:28.960 --> 05:44:30.960
[Guest 2]: is the best to react.

05:44:30.960 --> 05:44:32.960
[Guest 2]: That's why you are in that state of

05:44:32.960 --> 05:44:34.960
[Guest 2]: and I'll come to that last point of pressure, right?

05:44:34.960 --> 05:44:36.960
[Guest 2]: That the pressure

05:44:36.960 --> 05:44:38.960
[Guest 2]: handling is when the adrenaline

05:44:38.960 --> 05:44:40.960
[Guest 2]: output is the most optimum.

05:44:40.960 --> 05:44:42.960
[Guest 2]: When it is more,

05:44:42.960 --> 05:44:44.960
[Guest 2]: it means you are in over analysis.

05:44:44.960 --> 05:44:46.960
[Guest 2]: When it is less, it means you are not nervous.

05:44:46.960 --> 05:44:48.960
[Guest 2]: So at a stand-up comedian level,

05:44:48.960 --> 05:44:50.960
[Guest 2]: when I am a little nervous, that's when

05:44:50.960 --> 05:44:52.960
[Guest 2]: my best one-liners come.

05:44:52.960 --> 05:44:54.960
[Guest 2]: When I am complacent, my adrenaline is not there

05:44:54.960 --> 05:44:56.960
[Guest 2]: so I have just done this thing.

05:44:56.960 --> 05:44:58.960
[Guest 2]: When I am super nervous and I

05:44:58.960 --> 05:45:00.960
[Guest 2]: prepared so heavily, so the amount

05:45:00.960 --> 05:45:02.960
[Guest 2]: of preparation, which is process and

05:45:02.960 --> 05:45:04.960
[Guest 2]: routine also, it has to be calibrated.

05:45:04.960 --> 05:45:06.960
[Guest 2]: And that is why most sportsmen

05:45:06.960 --> 05:45:08.960
[Guest 2]: say that the best time I have performed

05:45:08.960 --> 05:45:10.960
[Guest 2]: is when I have rested well.

05:45:10.960 --> 05:45:12.960
[Guest 2]: So that combination of how

05:45:12.960 --> 05:45:14.960
[Guest 2]: much output to rest

05:45:14.960 --> 05:45:16.960
[Guest 2]: defines a good sportsperson.

05:45:16.960 --> 05:45:18.960
[Guest 2]: And my last point before the great

05:45:18.960 --> 05:45:20.960
[Guest 2]: Roshan Abbas tells his routine

05:45:20.960 --> 05:45:22.960
[Guest 2]: is the pressure point, right?

05:45:22.960 --> 05:45:24.960
[Guest 2]: That there are two perspectives

05:45:24.960 --> 05:45:26.960
[Guest 2]: of high-performance athletes to pressure.

05:45:26.960 --> 05:45:28.960
[Guest 2]: One is

05:45:28.960 --> 05:45:30.960
[Guest 2]: where they say, shit, tomorrow India-Pakistan

05:45:30.960 --> 05:45:32.960
[Guest 2]: is the game, boss.

05:45:32.960 --> 05:45:34.960
[Guest 2]: And that's nothing to do with your

05:45:34.960 --> 05:45:36.960
[Guest 2]: prowess. Whereas the

05:45:36.960 --> 05:45:38.960
[Guest 2]: other thing which you'll see Virat Kohli

05:45:38.960 --> 05:45:40.960
[Guest 2]: mentioning that I am waiting for an

05:45:40.960 --> 05:45:42.960
[Guest 2]: India-Pakistan game.

05:45:42.960 --> 05:45:44.960
[Guest 2]: Rahul Dravid would say in India

05:45:44.960 --> 05:45:46.960
[Guest 2]: when you met him after a test match,

05:45:46.960 --> 05:45:48.960
[Guest 2]: I am waiting for England to begin.

05:45:48.960 --> 05:45:50.960
[Guest 2]: Now these two perspectives

05:45:50.960 --> 05:45:52.960
[Guest 2]: define a champion.

05:45:52.960 --> 05:45:54.960
[Guest 2]: Because the moment you say

05:45:54.960 --> 05:45:56.960
[Guest 2]: I am looking for pressure,

05:45:56.960 --> 05:45:58.960
[Guest 2]: pressure does not affect you. The moment you

05:45:58.960 --> 05:46:00.960
[Guest 2]: want to run away from pressure is when

05:46:00.960 --> 05:46:02.960
[Guest 2]: you give a catch in the second, slip in the second

05:46:02.960 --> 05:46:04.960
[Guest 2]: over, knowing that this batsman could

05:46:04.960 --> 05:46:06.960
[Guest 2]: be actually better than this batsman.

05:46:06.960 --> 05:46:08.960
[Guest 2]: And that is why the greatest

05:46:08.960 --> 05:46:10.960
[Guest 2]: philosophy I have heard on pressure is

05:46:10.960 --> 05:46:12.960
[Guest 2]: Jimmy Connor's statement when he was

05:46:12.960 --> 05:46:14.960
[Guest 2]: asked, how do you deal with pressure?

05:46:14.960 --> 05:46:16.960
[Guest 2]: He said, I

05:46:16.960 --> 05:46:18.960
[Guest 2]: used to crumble under pressure.

05:46:18.960 --> 05:46:20.960
[Guest 2]: Then I made a perspective for myself

05:46:20.960 --> 05:46:22.960
[Guest 2]: and I said, when is the

05:46:22.960 --> 05:46:24.960
[Guest 2]: time when I became

05:46:24.960 --> 05:46:26.960
[Guest 2]: the richest? When is the time

05:46:26.960 --> 05:46:28.960
[Guest 2]: when I was the happiest ever?

05:46:28.960 --> 05:46:30.960
[Guest 2]: When is the time when I got the most attention?

05:46:30.960 --> 05:46:32.960
[Guest 2]: It was when I performed

05:46:32.960 --> 05:46:34.960
[Guest 2]: after a high-pressure game.

05:46:34.960 --> 05:46:36.960
[Guest 2]: Which means if I have to get rich,

05:46:36.960 --> 05:46:38.960
[Guest 2]: it means I have to be under pressure.

05:46:38.960 --> 05:46:40.960
[Guest 2]: So if there is no pressure, what a boring thing to play.

05:46:40.960 --> 05:46:42.960
[Guest 2]: So he calibrated

05:46:42.960 --> 05:46:44.960
[Guest 2]: his mind in such a way that pressure is

05:46:44.960 --> 05:46:46.960
[Guest 2]: where my incentive will be the highest.

05:46:46.960 --> 05:46:48.960
[Guest 2]: And I'll get the most return

05:46:48.960 --> 05:46:50.960
[Guest 2]: out of my profession. And he said

05:46:50.960 --> 05:46:52.960
[Guest 2]: that the only quest now was, after

05:46:52.960 --> 05:46:54.960
[Guest 2]: I had that perspective, was

05:46:54.960 --> 05:46:56.960
[Guest 2]: wait for a high-pressure game. And that

05:46:56.960 --> 05:46:58.960
[Guest 2]: is why my last submission

05:46:58.960 --> 05:47:00.960
[Guest 2]: is that you see the greatest

05:47:00.960 --> 05:47:02.960
[Guest 2]: players in the world, they don't

05:47:02.960 --> 05:47:04.960
[Guest 2]: perform in Ranji Trophy games.

05:47:04.960 --> 05:47:06.960
[Amit Varma]: There's a great quote by

05:47:06.960 --> 05:47:08.960
[Amit Varma]: Keith Miller, an Australian all-rounder.

05:47:08.960 --> 05:47:10.960
[Amit Varma]: He was in World War II.

05:47:10.960 --> 05:47:12.960
[Amit Varma]: He was a pilot in World War II

05:47:12.960 --> 05:47:14.960
[Amit Varma]: and there's a particular kind of German plane

05:47:14.960 --> 05:47:16.960
[Amit Varma]: called the Messerschmitt. So Michael

05:47:16.960 --> 05:47:18.960
[Amit Varma]: Parkinson once asked Keith Miller about pressure.

05:47:18.960 --> 05:47:20.960
[Amit Varma]: And Keith Miller said, you know what pressure is?

