[Unknown]: Tunak, tunak, tunak, tunak, tunak, tunak, tunak, tunak, tunak.

07:06:00.640 --> 07:06:04.160
[Amit Varma]: Amazing, amazing, amazing.

07:06:04.160 --> 07:06:06.520
[Guest 1]: So Jack and Jill's infinite versions

07:06:06.520 --> 07:06:09.920
[Guest 1]: played until the audience got tired, or we got tired.

07:06:09.920 --> 07:06:12.920
[Guest 1]: Or you could have said, this gentleman, Malaika Arora.

07:06:12.920 --> 07:06:19.400
[Unknown]: These are old stage tactics.

07:06:19.400 --> 07:06:22.000
[Unknown]: What all have we done?

07:06:22.000 --> 07:06:23.560
[Guest 1]: We made a good Christmas for it.

07:06:23.560 --> 07:06:24.720
[Guest 1]: We had a party for New Year's.

07:06:24.720 --> 07:06:25.560
[Amit Varma]: Everything is done.

07:06:25.560 --> 07:06:27.080
[Amit Varma]: Amazing, everything is done for me.

07:06:27.080 --> 07:06:28.960
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, I've taken enough of your time.

07:06:28.960 --> 07:06:32.920
[Amit Varma]: So I think I can finally begin to let you go.

07:06:32.920 --> 07:06:35.320
[Amit Varma]: But, you know, if for people watching this,

07:06:35.320 --> 07:06:36.760
[Amit Varma]: especially young people watching this,

07:06:36.760 --> 07:06:39.560
[Amit Varma]: given that we are old fogies, however much you may disagree,

07:06:39.560 --> 07:06:42.160
[Amit Varma]: Roshan, if you had to, no, I'm kidding.

07:06:42.160 --> 07:06:45.080
[Amit Varma]: But if you had to sort of, from all the things

07:06:45.080 --> 07:06:46.560
[Amit Varma]: that you've learned in your life,

07:06:46.560 --> 07:06:50.000
[Amit Varma]: give advice to young people today, you know,

07:06:50.000 --> 07:06:51.600
[Amit Varma]: what are the, like, if you had to talk

07:06:51.600 --> 07:06:53.760
[Amit Varma]: to a young Roshan, who's 20 years old,

07:06:53.760 --> 07:06:56.280
[Amit Varma]: what advice would you give him?

07:06:56.280 --> 07:06:57.880
[Guest 1]: Honestly, to a young Roshan, though,

07:06:57.880 --> 07:06:59.480
[Guest 1]: it would be do exactly what you did.

07:06:59.480 --> 07:07:03.000
[Guest 1]: Because frankly, I had a very, very fulfilled life.

07:07:03.000 --> 07:07:06.000
[Guest 1]: But if it is to young people at large,

07:07:06.000 --> 07:07:09.840
[Guest 1]: as I said that there is a lot of hope we all

07:07:09.840 --> 07:07:12.640
[Guest 1]: have in this generation for the simple reason

07:07:12.640 --> 07:07:18.120
[Guest 1]: that remain unafraid, keep experimenting, keep doing.

07:07:18.120 --> 07:07:22.560
[Guest 1]: You know, in this digital ether, in this digital world,

07:07:22.560 --> 07:07:26.800
[Guest 1]: that virtual like, that virtual heart, that virtual share

07:07:26.800 --> 07:07:29.280
[Guest 1]: is a small dopamine hit maybe for you

07:07:29.280 --> 07:07:30.360
[Guest 1]: and for others around you.

07:07:30.360 --> 07:07:33.120
[Guest 1]: But if it doesn't get translated into action,

07:07:33.120 --> 07:07:36.320
[Guest 1]: it's a tale full of sound and fury signifying nothing

07:07:36.320 --> 07:07:38.040
[Guest 1]: almost by the end of it.

07:07:38.040 --> 07:07:41.920
[Guest 1]: If you really want to go, there is no better,

07:07:41.920 --> 07:07:45.160
[Guest 1]: there is no generation which will be as empowered as you,

07:07:45.160 --> 07:07:48.600
[Guest 1]: no generation that will have as many tools as you,

07:07:48.600 --> 07:07:51.920
[Guest 1]: no generation where the ability to break down

07:07:51.920 --> 07:07:55.400
[Guest 1]: all those old guardrails, you know,

07:07:55.400 --> 07:07:57.360
[Guest 1]: all those guardrails you can break so easily.

07:07:57.360 --> 07:07:59.960
[Guest 1]: We had to knock on doors of All India Radio,

07:07:59.960 --> 07:08:04.160
[Guest 1]: stand outside film studios, read 20 scripts, do auditions,

07:08:04.160 --> 07:08:05.600
[Guest 1]: do all of those things.

07:08:05.600 --> 07:08:07.720
[Guest 1]: And I did a very small share of it,

07:08:07.720 --> 07:08:10.480
[Guest 1]: but then thankfully the success was incremental.

07:08:10.480 --> 07:08:12.080
[Guest 1]: But do that.

07:08:12.080 --> 07:08:17.440
[Guest 1]: Also in the initial years, work for experience, not for money.

07:08:17.440 --> 07:08:20.240
[Guest 1]: I know this sounds very easy from where I'm sitting today.

07:08:20.240 --> 07:08:22.760
[Guest 1]: But I can tell you about 50% of the jobs

07:08:22.760 --> 07:08:26.040
[Guest 1]: I did in my first seven or eight years of working,

07:08:26.040 --> 07:08:28.760
[Guest 1]: and maybe even more than that, were done for experience,

07:08:28.760 --> 07:08:30.560
[Guest 1]: not for money.

07:08:30.560 --> 07:08:36.120
[Guest 1]: They gave me all the skills I have to make the money.

07:08:36.120 --> 07:08:40.760
[Guest 1]: They gave me all the bad experiences in small doses,

07:08:40.760 --> 07:08:44.360
[Guest 1]: not being paid, not signing contracts, being cheated,

07:08:44.360 --> 07:08:49.040
[Guest 1]: being stood up at an event, having to suddenly, you know,

07:08:49.040 --> 07:08:51.800
[Guest 1]: see be replaced by another person, all of those things.

07:08:51.800 --> 07:08:56.640
[Guest 1]: Everything, those small hurts, because till the age of 25,

07:08:56.640 --> 07:08:59.880
[Guest 1]: maybe your brain is still learning how to process

07:08:59.880 --> 07:09:03.400
[Guest 1]: and how to react and respond to things.

07:09:03.400 --> 07:09:05.720
[Guest 1]: Delve into as many experiences as you can.

07:09:05.720 --> 07:09:08.120
[Guest 1]: Life is there to make money.

07:09:08.120 --> 07:09:12.560
[Guest 1]: Don't fall for this trap of money today, money today.

07:09:12.560 --> 07:09:14.720
[Guest 1]: Don't look at only the success charts.

07:09:14.720 --> 07:09:16.280
[Guest 1]: I genuinely feel that there needs

07:09:16.280 --> 07:09:19.360
[Guest 1]: to be a failure slash stumbling chart as well.

07:09:19.360 --> 07:09:22.480
[Guest 1]: And every stumble is a learning.

07:09:22.480 --> 07:09:25.360
[Guest 1]: Go for those, because there is so much to do that.

07:09:25.360 --> 07:09:31.160
[Guest 1]: Along the way, don't forget the people who build you, ever.

07:09:31.160 --> 07:09:33.800
[Guest 1]: Don't forget your family, ever.

07:09:33.800 --> 07:09:37.920
[Guest 1]: Because in the end, they will be around you.

07:09:37.920 --> 07:09:38.960
[Guest 1]: Whatever you do.

07:09:38.960 --> 07:09:40.240
[Guest 1]: I'm going to end with a line that I just

07:09:40.240 --> 07:09:42.960
[Guest 1]: heard in Tathastu from Zakir, because I absolutely adore it.

07:09:42.960 --> 07:09:47.600
[Guest 1]: He turned and said, professional loss is temporary.

07:09:47.600 --> 07:09:50.120
[Guest 1]: Personal loss is permanent.

07:09:50.120 --> 07:09:53.600
[Guest 1]: Just make sure that you give enough time to those.

07:09:53.600 --> 07:09:55.360
[Guest 1]: And there's another line from his show.

07:09:55.360 --> 07:09:59.120
[Guest 1]: I think he's a soothsayer for this generation to a large degree.

07:09:59.120 --> 07:10:01.960
[Guest 1]: He says, don't ruin anyone's magic.

07:10:01.960 --> 07:10:02.600
[Guest 1]: There's no need.

07:10:02.600 --> 07:10:04.520
[Guest 1]: Be gentle.

07:10:04.520 --> 07:10:06.080
[Guest 1]: Everybody has had a bad day.

07:10:06.080 --> 07:10:07.000
[Guest 1]: Everybody's done that.

07:10:07.000 --> 07:10:10.120
[Guest 1]: If you can, if you can find that empathy within you,

07:10:10.120 --> 07:10:12.360
[Guest 1]: that's all that everybody needs.

07:10:12.360 --> 07:10:13.120
[Guest 1]: Beautiful words.

07:10:13.120 --> 07:10:14.720
[Guest 2]: Amazing.

07:10:14.720 --> 07:10:16.480
[Guest 2]: Don't ruin it.

07:10:16.480 --> 07:10:19.560
[Guest 2]: One thing I've learned is don't give advice to youngsters.

07:10:19.560 --> 07:10:25.240
[Guest 2]: Actually, they may not take it.

07:10:25.240 --> 07:10:29.760
[Guest 2]: But having said that, I would have taken Roshan's advice to myself

07:10:29.760 --> 07:10:33.040
[Guest 2]: if I was young, is that I don't want to change anything, especially

07:10:33.040 --> 07:10:38.480
[Guest 2]: my mental state and the fact that I live without any goal and stuff like that.

07:10:38.480 --> 07:10:43.120
[Guest 2]: But still, I'm curious enough to, I think curiosity is the fundamental thing.

07:10:43.120 --> 07:10:46.760
[Guest 2]: If you're curious, a lot of your anxieties, your stress kind of

07:10:46.760 --> 07:10:49.600
[Guest 2]: gets canceled because you are anyway in the moment.

07:10:49.600 --> 07:10:51.960
[Guest 2]: You're trying to seek out of life and others.

07:10:51.960 --> 07:10:55.760
[Guest 2]: And I would have taken one piece of advice from Roshan to my younger self,

07:10:55.760 --> 07:10:59.440
[Guest 2]: that yes, you live the life that you have chosen to in the way you are doing

07:10:59.440 --> 07:11:03.480
[Guest 2]: right now, but just get a little more execution friendly

07:11:03.480 --> 07:11:06.800
[Guest 2]: and put out more creative in the universe so that,

07:11:06.800 --> 07:11:10.800
[Guest 2]: and take it to the logical conclusion and just don't get away from it.

07:11:10.800 --> 07:11:12.400
[Guest 2]: Beyond that, nothing.

07:11:12.400 --> 07:11:16.440
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, I would just say that I disagree with you in the one sense.

07:11:16.440 --> 07:11:20.000
[Amit Varma]: In the context of my own life, that I would do things differently.

07:11:20.000 --> 07:11:21.200
[Amit Varma]: I would do a lot differently.

07:11:21.200 --> 07:11:23.000
[Amit Varma]: And I think my advice comes from there.

07:11:23.000 --> 07:11:25.880
[Amit Varma]: Advice number one is respect the passing of time.

07:11:25.880 --> 07:11:27.880
[Amit Varma]: Time passes quicker than you know it.

07:11:27.880 --> 07:11:30.720
[Amit Varma]: You know, there's a saying, the days are long, the years are short.

07:11:30.720 --> 07:11:35.240
[Amit Varma]: The years go by before you even realize how fast they are moving.

07:11:35.240 --> 07:11:36.320
[Amit Varma]: So respect that time.

07:11:36.320 --> 07:11:38.360
[Amit Varma]: Don't waste any of it.

07:11:38.360 --> 07:11:41.280
[Amit Varma]: I would also say bet on yourself, right?

07:11:41.280 --> 07:11:43.360
[Amit Varma]: If you grow yourself.

07:11:43.360 --> 07:11:47.760
[Amit Varma]: Kids today are so fortunate, not just kids, we today are so fortunate

07:11:47.760 --> 07:11:49.840
[Amit Varma]: that we live in a world where you can learn anything.

07:11:49.840 --> 07:11:53.800
[Amit Varma]: You can go online and you can pick up any skill and become good at it.

07:11:53.800 --> 07:11:56.640
[Amit Varma]: So respect time, bet on yourself.

07:11:56.640 --> 07:11:59.080
[Amit Varma]: You know, compound yourself, as Sam Altman says.

07:11:59.080 --> 07:12:02.680
[Amit Varma]: You know, always try to figure out ways in which you are getting better

07:12:02.680 --> 07:12:05.400
[Amit Varma]: at something and ask yourself every day, every week,

07:12:05.400 --> 07:12:06.840
[Amit Varma]: what have I learned this week?

07:12:06.840 --> 07:12:08.480
[Amit Varma]: How am I better?

07:12:08.480 --> 07:12:11.640
[Amit Varma]: Also, look within yourself for happiness, not outside.

07:12:11.640 --> 07:12:15.560
[Amit Varma]: I think too many people spend too much time worrying about what other people

07:12:15.560 --> 07:12:18.120
[Amit Varma]: think of them, where really nobody's thinking of anybody else.

07:12:18.120 --> 07:12:20.320
[Amit Varma]: We've all got our heads up our own asses, right?

07:12:20.320 --> 07:12:23.280
[Amit Varma]: So just, you know, look within for happiness.

07:12:23.280 --> 07:12:25.760
[Amit Varma]: Validation doesn't really matter.

07:12:25.760 --> 07:12:29.080
[Amit Varma]: And the words from James Clear and Atomic Habits

07:12:29.880 --> 07:12:33.720
[Amit Varma]: sort of ring really true to me when he says everything you do today

07:12:34.000 --> 07:12:35.920
[Amit Varma]: will impact your future self.

07:12:35.920 --> 07:12:37.720
[Amit Varma]: And I think that's supremely important.

07:12:37.720 --> 07:12:42.000
[Amit Varma]: You know, I'm very angry at the young me because he didn't compound himself

07:12:42.000 --> 07:12:43.600
[Amit Varma]: and he wasted too much time.

07:12:43.600 --> 07:12:45.640
[Amit Varma]: And I think that impacted his future self.

07:12:46.000 --> 07:12:50.520
[Amit Varma]: And what I think we all have to remember is that everything you do today

07:12:50.680 --> 07:12:52.400
[Amit Varma]: builds the person you are tomorrow.

07:12:52.400 --> 07:12:53.320
[Amit Varma]: Think of that person.

07:12:53.320 --> 07:12:54.880
[Amit Varma]: Be compassionate towards him.

07:12:54.880 --> 07:12:57.120
[Amit Varma]: And this doesn't mean that you work, work, work all the time.

07:12:57.360 --> 07:12:59.080
[Amit Varma]: Leisure is also great.

07:12:59.080 --> 07:13:00.720
[Amit Varma]: Being in the moment is great.

07:13:00.720 --> 07:13:03.040
[Amit Varma]: Listening to a piece of music and giving into it

07:13:03.040 --> 07:13:05.640
[Amit Varma]: and not looking at what your calendar says is also great.

07:13:05.640 --> 07:13:10.880
[Amit Varma]: But the point is that overall, you've just got to sort of think about that.

07:13:10.880 --> 07:13:12.040
[Amit Varma]: You know, there are many ways.

07:13:12.040 --> 07:13:15.680
[Amit Varma]: Like one good metric is that if you think of your ideal self,

07:13:16.040 --> 07:13:18.960
[Amit Varma]: what is the perfect version of you doing that you don't do?

07:13:19.280 --> 07:13:22.440
[Amit Varma]: And what is a perfect version of you not doing that you do?

07:13:22.720 --> 07:13:24.800
[Amit Varma]: And if you just, you know, do a journal entry.

07:13:24.800 --> 07:13:27.960
[Amit Varma]: And in fact, writing a journal every day is also great advice that I would give.

07:13:28.360 --> 07:13:30.760
[Amit Varma]: And I would say that, you know, make that your first journal entry

07:13:30.760 --> 07:13:34.320
[Amit Varma]: and write about, you know, that ideal self.

07:13:34.320 --> 07:13:38.640
[Amit Varma]: You know, what are they doing that you are not and what are they not doing

07:13:38.640 --> 07:13:40.080
[Amit Varma]: that you are doing?

07:13:40.080 --> 07:13:42.320
[Amit Varma]: And I think they would also listen to this podcast.

07:13:42.320 --> 07:13:43.280
[Amit Varma]: So it's fine.

07:13:43.280 --> 07:13:46.040
[Amit Varma]: Basically, what you're saying is find your own Baljeet.

07:13:48.280 --> 07:13:51.120
[Amit Varma]: Find your own inner Baljeet and make him your Bhayna.

07:13:53.120 --> 07:13:53.720
[Guest 1]: That's true.

07:13:53.720 --> 07:13:56.640
[Amit Varma]: You know, I sometimes, when I start, he says to me,

07:13:56.640 --> 07:14:03.320
[Guest 1]: you know, he says that you have your Urdu, English, Kashm-Kashm, whatever.

07:14:03.320 --> 07:14:06.320
[Guest 1]: Kashm-Kashm, whatever, whatever, you know, he exploits it a lot.

07:14:33.320 --> 07:14:46.920
[Guest 1]: Right, I was just forgetting two lines in between because it's a, it just,

07:14:46.920 --> 07:14:51.120
[Guest 1]: it's that whole thing of turning and saying that it takes a lot of effort.

07:14:51.120 --> 07:14:53.720
[Guest 1]: And I, you know, how I keep talking about this thing of saying,

07:14:53.720 --> 07:14:57.160
[Guest 1]: karo, karo, karo, karo, you know, karna bahut zaruri hai.

07:14:57.160 --> 07:15:00.160
[Guest 1]: And, you know, and doing to that extent, doing to that extreme,

07:15:00.160 --> 07:15:05.640
[Guest 1]: that pinnacle is, it gets, you know, it gets smaller as you go there.

07:15:05.640 --> 07:15:09.640
[Guest 1]: But if you want to reach there, you have to put in that much effort.

07:15:09.640 --> 07:15:16.640
[Guest 1]: And what you said, what he said as a joke or whatever, ultimately, I think it's the same.

07:15:16.640 --> 07:15:20.640
[Guest 1]: That there's so much to do in life, do it.

07:15:20.640 --> 07:15:22.640
[Guest 1]: You know, go and do it.

07:15:22.640 --> 07:15:25.640
[Guest 1]: You said, do it each day, compound it, do that over and over.

07:15:25.640 --> 07:15:26.640
[Amit Varma]: Bias for action.

07:15:26.640 --> 07:15:29.640
[Guest 1]: Bias for action is something that I just want to reiterate that or whatever.

07:15:29.640 --> 07:15:30.640
[Guest 2]: I wish I had forgotten it.

07:15:30.640 --> 07:15:34.640
[Guest 2]: I was about to spit blood and he said, why is he promoting anemia?

07:15:34.640 --> 07:15:36.640
[Unknown]: Wow, wow.

07:15:36.640 --> 07:15:41.640
[Guest 1]: I mean, you know, one of those, one of those…

07:15:41.640 --> 07:15:44.640
[Guest 2]: However difficult it is, try to find your why.

07:15:44.640 --> 07:15:46.640
[Amit Varma]: It's very difficult.

07:15:46.640 --> 07:15:48.640
[Guest 2]: Do you need to find a why, Vikram?

07:15:48.640 --> 07:15:49.640
[Guest 2]: What is your why?

07:15:49.640 --> 07:15:52.640
[Guest 2]: See, why means whether it is goal setting or what in traditional terms.

07:15:52.640 --> 07:16:00.640
[Guest 2]: But if you get a little meaning that you have to do this, then I have seen that psychological issues are also solved a lot,

07:16:00.640 --> 07:16:02.640
[Guest 2]: which are likely to come in the younger generation.

07:16:02.640 --> 07:16:07.640
[Guest 2]: For that matter, even just, I mean, to this thing, even when my mother was unwell,

07:16:07.640 --> 07:16:12.640
[Guest 2]: when I, she has lived her life, she has taught me the things.

07:16:12.640 --> 07:16:16.640
[Guest 2]: But the moment I triggered that, you know, you should do this and that will this thing,

07:16:16.640 --> 07:16:18.640
[Guest 2]: suddenly her healing process got better.

07:16:18.640 --> 07:16:24.640
[Guest 2]: I know, I don't mean to say the why is a very philosophical construct about your existence in the universe,

07:16:24.640 --> 07:16:30.640
[Guest 2]: but it is that small, that I should do this, that kind of solves a lot of problems before.

07:16:30.640 --> 07:16:31.640
[Amit Varma]: What's your why?

07:16:31.640 --> 07:16:34.640
[Guest 2]: That's what I'm still trying to find.

07:16:34.640 --> 07:16:37.640
[Amit Varma]: It changes.

07:16:37.640 --> 07:16:41.640
[Amit Varma]: Let's hope that in 2023, we all find our why's, all three of us and everyone listening in.

07:16:41.640 --> 07:16:44.640
[Amit Varma]: So thank you guys for your company today.

07:16:44.640 --> 07:16:45.640
[Guest 1]: Thank you.

07:16:45.640 --> 07:16:46.640
[Unknown]: Thank you.

07:16:46.640 --> 07:16:48.640
[Guest 1]: Jai Bilao.

07:17:16.640 --> 07:17:18.640
[Amit Varma]: Jai Bilao.

